label: Chemist, General
description: Conducts chemical experiments, tests and analyses to investigate chemical phenomena, to test, develop or improve materials and products and to control or develop industrial processes.

label: Organic Chemist
description: Conducts chemical experiments, tests and analyses on substances of which main element is carbon, to investigate chemical phenomena, to test, develop or improve materials and products or to control or develop industrial processes.

label: Inorganic Chemist
description: Conducts chemical experiments, tests and analyses on substances free or relatively free of carbon to investigate chemical phenomena, to test, develop or improve materials and products, or to control or develop industrial processes.

label: Physical Chemist
description: Conducts research into relationships between chemical and physical properties of substances to increase knowledge of physical aspects of chemical phenomena or to develop or improve materials, products or industrial processes.

label: Analytical Chemist
description: Carries out chemical tests and analyses of substances and develops and improves analytical methodology and techniques.

label: Other Chemists
description: This group includes chemists not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in the development and technical control of the manufacture of pharmaceutical products. Pharmacologist is classified in 0-52.70 and Pharmacist in 0-67.10.

label: Physicist, General
description: Conducts research into physical phenomena to increase scientific knowledge and to develop and improve materials, products and industrial and other processes.

label: Mechanics Physicist
description: Conducts research in the field of mechanics to investigate physical phenomena or to develop or improve materials, products or industrial and other processes.

label: Heat Physicist
description: Conducts research into nature and effects of heat to increase scientific knowledge or to develop or improve materials, products or industrial and other processes.

label: Light Physicist
description: Conducts research into nature and effects of light to increase scientific knowledge or to develop or improve materials, products or industrial and other processes.

label: Sound Physicist
description: Conducts research into nature and effects of sound to increase scientific knowledge or to develop or improve materials, products or industrial and other processes.

label: Electricity and Magnetism Physicist
description: Conducts research into nature and properties of electricity and magnetism to increase scientific knowledge or to develop or improve materials, products or industrial and other processes.

label: Electronics Physicist
description: Conducts research into nature and behaviour of electrons to increase scientific knowledge or to develop or improve materials, products or industrial or other processes.

label: Nuclear Physicist
description: Conducts research into structure and characteristics of atoms, molecules and nuclei to increase scientific knowledge or to discover practical applications of atomic, molecular and nuclear physics.

label: Other Physicists
description: This group includes physicists not elsewhere classified, for example those who conduct research into structure and properties of matter in solid state; or specialise in pure research and formulate theories based on analysis of established data to explain relationships between observed physical phenomena and to explain previously unobserved phenomena, or predict results of experiments designed to detect and measure them.

label: Geophysical Scientist
description: Conducts research into physical nature of earth, including its atmosphere and hydrosphere, to increase scientific knowledge and to develop practical applications in such fields as radio communications, water conservation, volcanology and mineral exploration.

label: Geological Scientist
description: Conducts research into nature and history of earth's crust to increase scientific knowledge and to develop practical applications in such fields as mineral exploitation and civil engineering.

label: Meteorological Scientist
description: Conducts research into physical nature and properties of the earth's atmosphere and the forces affecting it to increase scientific knowledge and to develop practical applications such as weather forecasts.

label: Astronomical Scientist
description: Observes and interprets celestial phenomena to increase scientific knowledge and to develop practical applications in such fields as navigation and space exploration.

label: Other Physical Scientists
description: This group includes other physical scientists not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in examining, analysing and classifying minerals (including gems and precious stones) or advising on the likely commercial yield from mineral deposits containing gems and precious stones.

label: Physical Science Technician, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 0-14.

label: Chemistry Technician
description: Performs auxiliary technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of chemist, in connection with pure research into chemical phenomena or applied chemical research and development work.

label: Physics Technician
description: Performs auxiliary technical tasks, normally under direction of physicist, in connection with pure research into physical phenomena or applied physics research and development work.

label: Other Physical Science Technicians
description: This group includes physical science technicians not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform auxiliary technical tasks in connection with research and development work conducted by geological, geophysical meteorological and astronomic scientists.

label: Engineers, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities listed in unit groups 0-22 to 0-29.

label: Building Architect
description: Designs buildings and exercises general supervision over their construction. Building construction engineer is classified in 0-22.20.

label: Town Planner
description: Plans layout and co-ordinates development of urban areas.

label: Landscape Architect
description: Plans and designs aesthetic layout of land areas for such projects as parks and other recreational facilities, roads, commercial, industrial and residential sites and public buildings.

label: Civil Engineer, General
description: Carries out research, designs and advises on structures such as bridges, dams, docks, roads, airports, railways, waste disposal and flood control systems and industrial and other large buildings, and plans, organises and supervises their construction, maintenance and repair.

label: Building Construction Engineer
description: Designs structures of large buildings and plans, organises and supervises their erection, maintenance and repair.

label: Highway and Street Construction Engineer
description: Designs highways and streets and plans, organises and supervises their construction, maintenance and repair.

label: Aerodrome Construction Engineer
description: Designs airports and landing strips and plans, organises and supervises their construction, maintenance and repair.

label: Railway Construction Engineer
description: Designs railroads, terminals and other railway structures and plans, organises and supervises their construction, maintenance and repair.

label: Bridge Construction Engineer
description: Designs bridges and plans, organises and supervises their construction, maintenance and repair.

label: Sanitary Engineer
description: Designs engineering structures and equipment related to public health and hygiene, such as are required for water-supply and waste-disposal systems, and plans, organises and supervises their construction, operation, maintenance and repair.

label: Hydraulics Engineer
description: Designs hydro-power, water supply, irrigation, inland waterways and related projects and plans, organises and supervises their construction, maintenance and repair.

label: Soil Mechanics Engineer
description: Examines soils and ascertains their effect on construction work and suitability as building materials.

label: Other Civil Engineers
description: This group includes civil engineers not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform tasks similar to those of Civil engineer, general (0-22.10) but specialise in the design, construction and maintenance of tunnels, wharves, docks and harbour breakwaters, lighthouses, chimney stacks, towers and pylons; or in the dredging of harbours and ship channels.

label: Electrical Engineer, General
description: Carries out research on electrical engineering problems, designs and advises on electrical systems and equipment, and plans and supervises their development, construction, installation, operation, maintenance and repair.

label: Electronics Engineer, General
description: Carries out research on electronics engineering problems, designs and advises on electronic devices and equipment and plans and supervises their development, construction, installation, operation, maintenance and repair.

label: Power Generation Engineer
description: Studies, designs and advises on electricity generating systems and plant and plans and supervises their construction, operation, maintenance and repair.

label: Power Distribution and Transmission Engineer
description: Studies, designs and advises on systems and equipment for transmission and distribution of electric power and plans and supervises their development, construction, maintenance and repair.

label: Telecommunications Engineer
description: Studies, designs and advises on telecommunication systems and equipment and plans and supervises their development, construction, installation, operation, maintenance and repair.

label: Other Electrical and Electronics Engineers
description: This group includes electrical and electronics engineers not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform tasks similar to those of Electrical engineer, general (0-23.05) or Electronics engineer, general (0-23.10) but specialise in the design, production, operation or maintenance of particular apparatus or products such as electronic calculating and data-processing equipment; radar, radio or television; signalling and automatic control systems; electric traction equipment; electric motors; domestic electrical appliances; or other electrical or electronic apparatus (excluding power generation, transmission and distribution and telecommunications equipment).

label: Mechanical Engineer, General
description: Carries out research on, designs and advises on mechanically functioning plant and equipment, and plans and supervises their development, manufacture, construction, installation, operation, maintenance and repair.

label: Industrial Machinery and Tools Engineer
description: Studies, designs and advises on machinery and tools for manufacturing, mining, construction, agricultural work, printing and other industrial purposes, and plans and supervises their development, manufacture, installation, operation, maintenance and repair.

label: Mechanical Engineer (Motors and Engines, except Marine)
description: Studies, designs and advises on steam, internal combustion and other non-electric motors and engines as used for propulsion of railway locomotives, road vehicles or aeroplanes, or for driving industrial and other machinery, and plans and supervises their development, manufacture, installation, maintenance and repair. Engineers specialising in electric motors are classified in 0-23.90.

label: Marine Engineer
description: Studies, designs and advises on ships' propulsion systems, power plants, heating and ventilating systems, steering gear, pumps and other mechanical and electrical equipment, and plans and supervises their development, construction, installation, maintenance and repair. A marine engineer who is a member of a ship's crew is classified in unit group 0-43.

label: Ship Construction Engineer
description: Studies, designs and advises on the hulls and superstructures of ships and other vessels, and plans and supervises their development, construction, maintenance and repair.

label: Aeronautical Engineer
description: Studies, designs and advises on airframes, undercarriages and other equipment for aircraft, and plans and supervises their development, construction, maintenance and repair.

label: Automotive Engineer
description: Studies, designs and advises on road vehicle bodies, suspension systems, brakes and other components, and plans and supervises their development and manufacture.

label: Heating, Ventilation and Refrigeration Engineer
description: Studies, designs and advises on heating, ventilation and refrigeration systems and equipment, and plans and supervises their development, manufacture, installation, maintenance and repair.

label: Nuclear Power Engineer
description: Studies, designs and advises on mechanical plant and equipment for the release, control and utilisation of nuclear energy, and plans and supervises their development, manufacture, installation, maintenance and repair.

label: Other Mechanical Engineers
description: This group includes mechanical engineers not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform tasks similar to those of Mechanical engineer, general (0-24.10) but specialise in the design, production or maintenance of particular apparatus or products such as precision instruments; cameras and projectors; typewriters, desk calculators, cash registers and ticket machines; duplicating and copying machines; mechanically functioning medical equipment; or special space vehicles and mechanical equipment for space exploration and travel.

label: Chemical Engineer, General
description: Carries out research on chemical engineering problems and develops and advises on processes for producing on a commercial scale the chemical or physical transformation of substances, as in the manufacture of chemicals, petroleum derivatives, metals, food products and synthetic materials, designs appropriate manufacturing plant and plans and supervises its construction, operation, maintenance and repair.

label: Chemical Engineer (Petroleum)
description: Studies, develops and advises on processes for the refining of crude oil, designs appropriate plant and plans and supervises its construction, operation, maintenance and repair.

label: Other Chemical Engineers
description: This group includes chemical engineers not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform tasks similar to those of Chemical engineer, general (0-25.10) but specialise in the development and efficient utilisation of fuels; the design, construction, operation and maintenance of plant for the physical and chemical transformation of matter for the manufacture of a particular type of commodity such as antibiotics, plastics, explosives, rubber or pigments, or of plant for production and distribution of fuel gas for industrial, domestic and other purposes.

label: Extractive Metallurgist
description: Studies, develops, advises on and controls the application of processes for the extraction of metals from their ores.

label: Physical Metallurgist
description: Studies properties of metals and alloys, develops new alloys and advises on and supervises technical aspects of metal and alloy manufacture and processing.

label: Other Metallurgists
description: This group includes metallurgists not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in metallurgical problems of radioactive materials.

label: Mining Engineer, General
description: Carries out research on mining engineering problems, advises on the extraction of metallic and solid nonmetallic minerals from the earth, supervises mineral prospecting and plans, organises and supervises mineral mining operations and preparation of minerals for distribution or processing.

label: Coal-Mining Engineer
description: Studies and advises on coal-mining engineering problems and plans, organises and supervises coal-mining operations and preparation of coal for distribution.

label: Metal-Mining Engineer
description: Studies and advises on metal-mining engineering problems and plans, organises and supervises metal-mining operations and preparation of metallic ores for distribution or processing. Engineers who specialise in the extraction of minerals from alluvial deposits by sluicing or dredging are classified in 0-27.90.

label: Petroleum and Natural Gas Engineer
description: Studies and advises on petroleum and natural gas extraction engineering problems, and plans, organises and supervises the extraction, storage, intial treatment and transportation of petroleum and natural gas.

label: Other Mining Engineers
description: This group includes mining engineers not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform tasks similar to those of Mining engineer, general (0-27.10) but specialise in mining or quarrying solid minerals (other than coal and metallic minerals) such as stone, marble, clay, salt, gravel or diamonds; extracting subsurface water or sulphur and other solid minerals by drilling boreholes; or extracting tin, gold, diamonds or other solid minerals from alluvial deposits by sluicing and dredging.

label: Industrial Efficiency Engineer, General
description: Studies and advises on the organisation of production processes and commercial and administrative procedures, plans and supervises time and motion studies and makes recommendations to promote efficiency and supervises their implementation.

label: Methods Engineer
description: Analyses industrial, commercial and other projects and administrative procedures, makes recommendations regarding organisation, methods of work and sequence of operations and supervises their implementation.

label: Time and Motion Study Engineer
description: Studies, develops and advises on work measurement procedures, plans and supervises time and motion studies, makes recommendations to promote efficiency and supervises their implementation.

label: Other Industrial Engineers
description: This group includes industrial engineers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in the prevention of industrial accidents and diseases by identifying potential hazards and developing and introducing safety procedures and devices, and those who specialise in the efficient layout of industrial plant or commercial establishments.

label: Ceramics and Glass Technologist
description: Carries out research and advises on, designs, develops and controls processes and plant for the manufacture of bricks, pottery and glassware.

label: Agricultural Engineer
description: Studies and advises on the application of engineering technology to agricultural problems, designs agricultural machinery, structures and equipment and plans and supervises their manufacture, construction and installation. Engineers specialising in civil, mechanical or other particular types of engineering problems affecting the agricultural industry are classified elsewhere in minor group 0-2/0-3.

label: Food and Drink Technologist
description: Carries out research and advises on, designs, develops and controls processes and plant for the manufacture and processing of foods and beverages.

label: Traffic Planner
description: Studies, plans and advises on the routing and control of road traffic to promote safety and minimise congestion.

label: Other Engineers
description: This group includes engineers not elsewhere classified, for example those who study, design, develop, control and advise on processes and plant for the manufacture or processing of textiles, leather products, wood or paper.

label: Surveyor, General
description: Surveys earth's surface, natural topography and manmade structures, and underground areas to delineate features and determine exact locations and measurements for such purposes as mapmaking, construction work and mining.

label: Land Surveyor
description: Surveys land surfaces to determine boundaries and exact locations, delineate topographic features and man-made structures and otherwise measure land areas for such purposes as mapmaking and construction work.

label: Mine Surveyor
description: Surveys mines and delineates surface and underground features to control direction and extent of mining.

label: Hydrographic Surveyor
description: Surveys sea, river and lake beds to delineate underwater topographic features for such purposes as chart making, determining navigable channels and planning construction and repair of harbours, piers, breakwaters and other marine structures.

label: Photogrammetrist
description: Analyses photographs and survey data to prepare and revise topographic maps and charts.

label: Other Surveyors
description: This group includes surveyors not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in planning and constructing aerial photographic surveys.

label: Draughtsman, General
description: Prepares accurate working plans and detailed drawings for engineering, construction, manufacturing or other projects, based on designer's sketches and specifications, and prepares charts and working drawings for other purposes.

label: Mechanical Draughtsman
description: Prepares engineering working drawings from designer's sketches and specifications for manufacture of machines, mechanical devices and related products.

label: Electrical Draughtsman
description: Prepares working drawings from designer's sketches and specifications for manufacture and installation of electrical and electronic machinery and equipment.

label: Civil Engineering Draughtsman
description: Prepares working drawings from designer's sketches and specifications for use in civil engineering projects.

label: Architectural Draughtsman
description: Prepares working drawings from architect's sketches and specifications for construction of buildings.

label: Cartographical Draughtsman
description: Prepares maps and charts from survey and other data.

label: Technical Illustrator
description: Draws technical illustrations for brochures, reference works and technical manuals dealing with assembly, installation, operation or use, maintenance and repair of machinery and other equipment.

label: Lithographic Artist
description: Sketches designs in black and white or colour for preparation of lithographic stones, photo-engraving and other printing processes.

label: Other Draughtsmen
description: This group includes draughtsmen not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in preparing working drawings for the installation of heating and ventilating systems or preparing maps, diagrams, profiles and cross-sections to show geological stratigraphy and location of mineral deposits.

label: Technician, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit groups 0-14 and 0-33 to 0-39.

label: Civil Engineering Technician, General
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of civil engineer or building architect, contributory to planning and execution of building and civil engineering projects, including new construction, repair and maintenance.

label: Quantity Surveyor
description: Estimates quantities and costs of building materials and labour required for execution of construction projects and prepares bills of quantities.

label: Surveyor's Technician
description: Performs technical tasks under direction and supervision of surveyor contributory to execution of surveys and preparation of survey reports.

label: Clerk of Works
description: Represents building architect on construction site to ensure compliance with design specifications and maintenance of desired standards of materials and workmanship.

label: Other Civil Engineering Technicians
description: This group includes civil engineering technicians not elsewhere classified, for example those who visit different construction sites to make measurements, tests and observations to ensure that work done and materials used conform with specifications, to assist contractor in interpretation of working plans and specifications and arrange deviations from specifications to meet regulations governing construction.

label: Electrical Engineering Technician, General
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of electrical engineer, contributory to design, development, construction, installation, maintenance and repair of electrical systems and equipment.

label: Electronics Engineering Technician, General
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of electronics engineer, contributory to design, development, construction, installation, maintenance and repair of electronic devices and equipment.

label: Electrical Engineering Technician (High Voltage)
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of electrical engineer, contributory to design, development, construction, utilisation, maintenance and repair of high-voltage electrical systems and equipment.

label: Telecommunications Technician
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of telecommunications engineer, contributory to design, development, construction, installation, operation, maintenance and repair of telecommunications systems and equipment.

label: Other Electrical and Electronics Engineering Technicians
description: This group includes electrical and electronic engineering technicians not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform tasks similar to those of Electrical engineering technician, general (0-34.05) or Electronics engineering technician, general (0-34.10) but specialise in technical tasks contributory to the design, development, construction, maintenance and repair of particular apparatus or products such as electronic calculating and data-processing equipment; radar, radio or television equipment; signalling and automatic control systems; electric traction equipment; electric motors; domestic electrical appliances; or other electrical or electronic apparatus (excluding high-voltage equipment and telecommunications systems).

label: Mechanical Engineering Technician, General
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of mechanical engineer, contributory to design, development, manufacture, construction, installation, efficient operation, maintenance and repair of mechanically functioning plant and equipment.

label: Mechanical Engineering Technician (Motors and Engines)
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of mechanical engineer, contributory to design, development, manufacture, installation, maintenance and repair of steam, internal combustion and non-electric motors and engines. Technicians specialising in electric motors are classified in 0-34.90.

label: Aeronautical Engineering Technician
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of aeronautical engineer, contributory to design, development, construction, maintenance and repair of aircraft.

label: Automotive Engineering Technician
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of automotive engineer, contributory to design, development and manufacture of road vehicles.

label: Heating, Ventilation and Refrigeration Engineering Technician
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of heating, ventilation, and refrigeration engineer, contributory to design, development, manufacture, installation, maintenance and repair of systems and equipment for heating, ventilation and refrigeration.

label: Other Mechanical Engineering Technicians
description: This group includes mechanical engineering technicians not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform tasks similar to those of Mechanical engineering technician, general (0-35.10) but specialise in technical tasks contributory to the design, production or maintenance of apparatus or products such as plant and equipment for the release, control and utilisation of nuclear energy; ships' hulls and superstructures; precision instruments; cameras and projectors; typewriters, desk calculators, cash registers and ticket machines; duplicating and copying machines; mechanically functioning medical equipment; or special space vehicles and mechanical equipment for space exploration and travel.

label: Chemical Engineering Technical, General
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of chemical engineer, contributory to development of processes for the chemical or physical transformation of substances on a commercial scale and to design, construction, operation, maintenance and repair of chemical plant.

label: Chemical Engineering Technician (Petroleum)
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of chemical engineer (petroleum), contributory to development of processes for refining crude oil and to design, construction, operation, maintenance and repair of refining plant.

label: Other Chemical Engineering Technicians
description: This group includes chemical engineering technicians not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform tasks similar to those of Chemical engineering technician, general (0-36.10) but specialise in technical tasks contributory to development and efficient utilisation of fuels or to design, construction, operation, maintenance and repair of plant for the chemical and physical transformation of matter for the manufacture of a particular type of commodity such as antibiotics, plastics, explosives, rubber or pigments, or of plant for production and distribution of fuel gas for industrial, domestic and other uses.

label: Metallurgical Technician, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 0-37.

label: Extractive Metallurgy Technician
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of extractive metallurgist, contributory to development and control of processes for the extraction of metals from their ores.

label: Physical Metallurgy Technician
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of physical metallurgist, contributory to research into properties of metals and alloys, development of new alloys and technical supervision of metal and alloy manufacture and processing.

label: Other Metallurgical Technicians
description: This group includes metallurgical technicians not elsewhere classified, for example those who performtechnical tasks similar to those of Extractive and Physical metallurgy technicians (0-37.20 and 0-37.30) to assist metallurgists specialising in radioactive materials.

label: Mining Technician, General
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of mining engineer, contributory to the extraction of metallic and solid non-metallic minerals from the earth and their preparation for distribution or processing.

label: Petroleum and Natural Gas Extraction Technician
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of petroleum and natural gas engineer, contributory to the extraction, storage and transportation of petroleum and natural gas.

label: Other Mining Technicians
description: This group includes mining technicians not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform tasks similar to those of Mining technicians, general (0-38.10) but specialise in technical tasks contributory to the extraction from mines and quarries of a particular solid mineral such as coal, stone, clay, salt, gravel or diamonds; or to extraction of subsurface water or sulphur and other solid minerals by drilling boreholes; or to extraction of tin, gold, diamonds or other solid minerals from alluvial deposits by sluicing and dredging.

label: Production Engineering Technician
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under the direction of production methods engineer, to determine for particular products suitable sequences and timings for production operations.

label: Time and Motion Study Technician
description: Performs time and motion studies under direction and supervision of time and motion study engineer.

label: Other Engineering Technicians
description: This group includes engineering technicians not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in performing technical tasks contributory to technological development of processes and plant, or technical supervision of processing operations, relating to the manufacture of bricks, pottery and glassware; of food and beverages; textiles; paper; leather or wood products; those assisting safety engineers, agricultural engineers, or traffic planners; and those performing other technical tasks in engineering not performed by workers classified elsewhere.

label: Air Transport Pilot
description: Flies aircraft transporting passengers, mail or freight.

label: Aircraft Pilot (Transport or Other Purposes)
description: Flies aircraft for transport of passengers, mail, or freight or for other purposes.

label: Aircraft Pilot (except Transport)
description: Pilots aircraft for purposes other than passenger, mail or freight transportation, such as for testing or delivering aircraft, spraying insecticides and fungicides for pest control, aerial surveys, aerial photography, and exhibitions of flying skill.

label: Flight Navigator
description: Directs course of aircraft in flight according to predetermined flight plan or as directed by pilot-in-command.

label: Flight Engineer
description: Makes pre-flight, in-flight and post-flight inspections, carries out adjustments and minor repairs to ensure safe and efficient operation of aircraft and monitors control panel during flight.

label: Flying Instructor
description: Teaches trainee pilots to operate the controls of an aircraft and instructs them in aircraft piloting techniques and procedures.

label: Ships' Deck Officer or Pilot, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 0-42.

label: Ship's Master (Sea)
description: Takes complete charge of seagoing ship and directs, co-ordinates and supervises shipboard activities.

label: Ship's Master (Sea or Inland Waterways)
description: Takes complete charge of seagoing ship or vessel confined to inland waterways and directs, co-ordinates and supervises shipboard activities.

label: Ship's Master (Inland Waterways)
description: Takes complete charge of vessel confined to inland waterways and directs, co-ordinates and supervises activities on board. Boatman is classified in 9.81.90.

label: Ship's Navigating Officer
description: Plans, supervises and co-ordinates deck and bridge-watch activities on seagoing or inland waterways vessel.

label: Ship Pilot
description: Navigates vessels into and out of ports, in rivers, channels, straits and other waters where special knowledge and skill are required.

label: Marine Superintendent (Deck)
description: Directs or arranges on-shore services such as supply of ships' stores and equipment, ship inspections and overhauls, crew replacements and navigational information for shipping company vessels arriving in port. Marine superintendent (technical) is classified in 0-43.30.

label: Other Ships' Deck Officers and Pilots
description: This group includes ships' deck officers and pilots not elsewhere classified, for example those in charge of seagoing yachts and hovercraft.

label: Ship's Chief Engineer
description: Plans, co-ordinates and directs engine-room department aboard ship and supervises subordinate marine engineer officers and engine-room ratings.

label: Marine Engineer Officer
description: Controls, and participates in, the operation, maintenance and repair of engines, electrical motors, boilers, pumps, compressors, heat exchangers, and other machinery and equipment on board ship under the general direction of chief engineer.

label: Marine Superintendent (Technical)
description: Directs from shore station the maintenance programmes for machinery and equipment on board company's ships, directs or authorises repairs in port and directs replacement programme for shipboard machinery.

label: Biologist, General
description: Conducts research into all forms of life to increase scientific knowledge and develops practical applications in fields such as medicine and agriculture.

label: Botanist
description: Conducts research into all forms of plant life to increase scientific knowledge and develop practical applications in fields such as agriculture and forestry.

label: Zoologist
description: Conducts research into all forms of animal life to increase scientific knowledge and develop practical applications in fields such as agriculture and medicine.

label: Other Biologists, Zoologists and Related Scientists
description: This group includes biologists, zoologists and related scientists not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in marine and freshwater life.

label: Anatomist
description: Conducts research into the form, structure and other anatomical characteristics of humans and animals to increase scientific knowledge and develop practical applications in medical and related fields.

label: Biochemist
description: Conducts research into chemical composition and processes of living organisms to increase scientific knowledge and develop industrial, medical and other practical applications.

label: Physiologist
description: Conducts research into biological functions and activities of human organism under normal and abnormal conditions to increase scientific knowledge and develop practical applications in medical and related fields.

label: Bacteriologist
description: Conducts research into nature and characteristics of bacteria and other micro-organisms to increase scientific knowledge and develop industrial, medical and other practical applications.

label: Medical Pathologist
description: Conducts research into nature, causes and development of human diseases and disorders.

label: Veterinary Pathologist
description: Conducts research into nature, causes and development of animal diseases and disorders.

label: Pharmacologist
description: Conducts research into effects of drugs and other substances on organs, tissues and life processes of humans and animals and develops new and improved medicinal drugs.

label: Animal Scientist
description: Conducts research into animal genetics, advanced animal husbandry methods and related matters and applies scientific knowledge to develop improved strains, improved methods of raising animals and higher yields of animal products.

label: Other Bacteriologists, Pharmacologists and Related Scientists
description: This group includes bacteriologists, pharmacologists and related scientists not elsewhere classified, for example those conducting research in the field of biophysics, relating to such problems as dynamics of seeing and hearing, transmission of electrical impulses along nerves and muscles, effects of light and other radiation on body cells, and developing practical applications for medical or other purposes.

label: Agronomist
description: Conducts research into field crops and grasses and develops new and improved production methods.

label: Horticulturist
description: Conducts research into horticultural crops and develops new and improved production methods.

label: Silviculturist
description: Conducts research into, and develops methods of, tree propagation and culture and plans and directs afforestation, care and exploitation of forest stands.

label: Soil Scientist
description: Conducts research into characteristics, use capabilities and productivity of soils and applies findings to development of improved agricultural, horticultural and forestry practices.

label: Farming Adviser
description: Advises farmers on farming methods and problems.

label: Other Agronomists and Related Scientists
description: This group includes agronomists and related scientists not elsewhere classified, for example those who investigate conditions and problems, make recommendations and develop improved methods relating to conservation of wild life reserves or economic exploitation of grazing lands.

label: Life Science Technician, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 0-54.

label: Biological Technician
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of biological scientist, contributory to biological experiments, tests and analyses to increase scientific knowledge and develop industrial, public health, agricultural and other practical applications.

label: Medical Science Technician
description: Performs technical tasks, normally under direction and supervision of medical scientist, contributory to experiments, tests and analyses for the diagnosis, treatment and prevention of sickness and disease.

label: Other Life Sciences Technicians
description: This group includes life sciences technicians not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in performing technical tasks in connection with the collection, treatment, storage and distribution of semen for artificial breeding of farm animals; performing technical tasks to assist agronomists, horticulturists and silviculturists; or analysing samples of seeds for quality, purity and germination rating.

label: Medical Doctor, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 0-61.

label: General Physician
description: Conducts medical examinations, makes diagnoses, prescribes medicines, and gives other forms of treatment for various kinds of diseases, disorders and injuries of the human body; applies preventive medicine techniques to prevent diseases and promote good health.

label: General Surgeon
description: Performs various kinds of surgical operations in the treatment of injuries, diseases and disorders of the human body.

label: Specialised Physician
description: Specialises in giving medical treatment and advice for particular types of diseases, disorders and injuries of the human body.

label: Specialised Surgeon
description: Specialises in giving surgical treatment and advice for particular types of diseases and disorders of the human body.

label: Public Health Physician
description: Exercises controls and supervision to implement or enforce public health laws and regulations for safeguarding and promoting the health of a community.

label: Other Medical Doctors
description: This group includes medical doctors not elsewhere classified, for example those mainly employed in conducting medical examinations in schools, workplaces or elsewhere; those mainly employed in giving medical advice, for instance in connection with life or other insurance plans, social security funds, medical aspects of occupational risks, or otherwise.

label: Medical Assistant
description: Performs to a limited extent the tasks of General physician (0-61.05) within a public health service or institution, more particularly as regards common diseases of the region, either independently or under the general direction of a fully qualified physician. The workers in this group have not had the full training of General physician (0-61.05).

label: Dentist, General
description: Performs diagnostic, preventive and curative services for dental or oral diseases and disorders.

label: Specialised Dentist
description: Specialises in giving surgical, medical and other forms of treatment for particular types of dental and oral diseases and disorders.

label: Public Health Dentist
description: Plans and directs public action to improve oral health and to control and improve standards of dental care and treatment of oral disorders.

label: Dental Assistant
description: Carries out, but only to a limited extent, diagnostic, preventive and curative tasks in dentistry to assist dentists, or independently. The workers in this group have not had the full training of Dentists (0-63), and may be designated Practical dentist, Unregistered dentist or Dental auxiliary.

label: School Dental Assistant
description: Performs limited diagnostic, preventive and curative duties in dentistry for pre-school and schoolchildren under the direction and control of a dentist.

label: Dental Hygienist
description: Carries out dental prophylactic treatments and instructs groups and individuals in care of teeth and mouth.

label: Veterinarian, General
description: Diagnoses and gives or prescribes medical and surgical treatment of diseases, injuries or other medical conditions of animals and deals with other aspects of animal health.

label: Public Health Veterinarian
description: Exercises surveillance of quality, purity and safety of food of animal origin intended for human consumption and investigates and controls animal diseases hazardous to man.

label: Other Veterinarians
description: This group includes veterinarians not elsewhere classified, for example those controlling import and export of animals and animal products; controlling drugs and vaccines used in veterinary practise; advising on the breeding, transport, care and health problems of laboratory animals; advising on and assisting in epidemiological and other surveillance of zoonoses; collaborating in the preparation of animals for space exploration experiments.

label: Veterinary Assistant
description: Carries out, but only to a limited extent, diagnostic, preventive and curative veterinary duties as described under Veterinarian, general (0-65.10), more particularly as regards common diseases and disorders of animals, either independently or under the general direction of fully qualified veterinarian. The workers in this group have not had the full training of Veterinarians (0-65).

label: Pharmacist
description: Makes and dispenses medicaments and related preparations according to prescriptions or formulae.

label: Pharmaceutical Assistant
description: Assists in a pharmacy, hospital or dispensary to make and dispense medicaments, under the direction of a pharmacist.

label: Dietitian, General
description: Plans and supervises the preparation of therapeutic or other diets for individuals or for groups in hospitals, institutions and other establishments and for workers in particular sectors; gives instruction in selection and proper preparation of food according to dietetic principles; performs duties related to nutrition programmes.

label: Public Health Nutritionist
description: Appraises various factors related to nutrition and food problems in the community and plans and executes nutrition elements of health programmes.

label: Other Dietitians and Public Health Nutritionists
description: This group includes dietitians and public health nutritionists not elsewhere classified, for example those acting as consultants to food processing and distributing firms or to manufacturers of food-processing equipment.

label: Professional Nurse, General
description: Provides professional nursing services and advice in hospitals, clinics or other establishments which provide medical care and treatment.

label: Specialised Nurse
description: Provides specialised professional nursing services in a medical establishment or elsewhere.

label: Public Health Nurse
description: Provides, within a community health service, professional nursing care and advice in private homes, schools, maternal and child health centres and nurseries; performs other nursing tasks associated with the provision of community health services.

label: Occupational Health Nurse
description: Provides professional nursing services and health information for employees in workplaces.

label: Other Professional Nurses
description: This group includes professional nurses not elsewhere classified, for example those specialising in provision of consultant services to industrial and other organisations; or in giving private general nursing care to patients in their homes.

label: Auxiliary Nurse
description: Provides simple nursing services to patients, generally under the supervision of a physician or professional nurse. Nursing aid is classified in 5-99.40.

label: Professional Midwife
description: Gives professional care and advice to women to aid them during pregnancy, childbirth and the postnatal period. A professional nurse specialising in obstetrics is classified as Specialised nurse (0-71.20).

label: Auxiliary Midwife
description: Provides practical care and assistance to women, usually in private homes, to aid them during pregnancy, childbirth and the postnatal period; takes care of the new-born infant. The workers classified in this group do not have the full training and theoretical knowledge of Professional midwife (0-73.10).

label: Optometrist
description: Examines eyes and prescribes spectacles or treatment not involving the use of medicines, surgery or drugs, to conserve or improve vision.

label: Dispensing Optician
description: Assists customer in choice of frames, selects the lenses prescribed, fits lenses in frames and fits frames to customer, or fits contact lenses according to prescription.

label: Physiotherapist
description: Treats sprains, healing fractures, paralysis, circulatory and nervous disorders by physical means, usually as prescribed by a physician.

label: Occupational Therapist
description: Participates in planned medically oriented vocational, educational or recreational activities designed to rehabilitate physically or mentally disabled persons.

label: Masseur
description: Massages clients or patients to improve circulation, soothe or stimulate nerves, facilitate elimination of waste matter, stretch contracted tendons and produce other therapeutic effects.

label: Medical X-Ray Technician
description: Operates X-ray equipment to make radiographs for medical diagnostic purposes or to give therapeutic treatment.

label: Osteopath
description: Diagnoses and treats, mainly by manipulative methods, disorders of bones, muscles, blood vessels and other tissues of the human body.

label: Chiropractor
description: Relieves illness believed due to pressure upon nervous system at the spine by adjusting joints of the spine.

label: Sanitarian
description: Inspects the environment, promotes measures to restore or improve sanitary conditions and supervises their implementation.Sanitary engineers are classified in 0-22.50.

label: Orthopaedic Technician
description: Writes specifications for and fits artificial limbs, braces and other appliances for body deformities and disorders following prescription of physician.

label: Other Medical, Dental, Veterinary and Related Workers
description: This group includes medical, dental, veterinary and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those treating sickness through the application of various herbs and medicinal plants; those treating patients with a system of physical culture and drugless treatment of disease by methods aimed to stimulate or assist nature; those treating body ailments and nervous disorders through mental influence and suggestion; those who treat physical ailments by means of therapeutic baths and other treatments; those carrying out minor surgical procedures connected, for example, with ailments of the human foot; those diagnosing and treating minor ailments of the human foot such as corns, callouses, deformed toenails, flat feet and other disorders and advising patients on further treatment, proper foot care and suitable footwear.

label: Statistician, General
description: Conducts research to develop new and improved statistical methods, advises on practical applications of statistical methods, plans and conducts statistical surveys, and organises, analyses and interprets statistical data.

label: Mathematical Statistician
description: Conducts research into mathematical basis of science of statistics, develops new and improved statistical methodology and advises on practical applications of statistical methods and techniques.

label: Statistician (Applied Statistics)
description: Plans and conducts statistical surveys, evaluates, organises, analyses and interprets statistical data and prepares reports.

label: Mathematician (Pure Mathematics)
description: Conducts research in fundamental mathematics to advance mathematical knowledge and develop and improve mathematical techniques.

label: Mathematician (Applied Mathematics)
description: Advises on practical applications of mathematical principles and techniques and applies them to solution of problems in scientific research, engineering, management and other activities. Workers specialising in operations-research analysis are classified in 0-82.40.

label: Operations-Research Analyst
description: Conducts logical analyses of management problems and formulates mathematical model of each problem for programming and solution by computer.

label: Actuary
description: Applies knowledge of mathematics, statistics and financial affairs to design and operation of pension schemes and life, health, social and casualty insurance systems.

label: Systems Analyst
description: Analyses data-processing needs and problems of client or employer, advises on feasibility of automatic data-processing and develops appropriate systems and procedures. Operations-research analyst is classified in 0-82.40.

label: Computer Programmer
description: Prepares programmes to control automatic processing of data by computer.

label: Other Statistical and Mathematical Technicians
description: This group includes statistical and mathematical technicians not elsewhere classified, for example those who carry out, normally under the direction and supervision of statisticians, mathematicians and actuaries, technical tasks contributory to research in statistical, mathematical and actuarial sciences, to analysis, mathematical formulation and solution of problems, and to other practical applications of statistical, mathematical and actuarial methods and techniques.

label: Economist, General
description: Conducts research and applies the principles and theories of economics to formulate solutions to economic problems.

label: Economist, Specialised
description: Conducts research and advises on economic problems in a particular branch of economics.

label: Market Research Analyst
description: Conducts research to determine existing level of sales for particular products and services and to assess potential market and future trend.

label: Accountant, General
description: Plans and administers accounting services and advises on accountancy problems of private persons, enterprises, institutions and governmental organisations.

label: Auditor
description: Plans and conducts audit of accounts, bookkeeping records and financial statements of private persons, enterprises, institutions and governmental organisations.

label: Other Accountants
description: This group includes accountants not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in cost accounting. The cost accountant applies the principles of accountancy and statistics to plan, install and direct cost-finding and reporting systems designed to inform management of total cost per unit of output, the relative importance of costs for raw materials, labour, fuel, equipment, general overhead and other costs, and the effect of changes in quantities and prices of inputs.

label: Jurist, Specialization Unknown
description: Performs legal functions, specialisation unknown.

label: Lawyer
description: Prepares and pleads cases and conducts prosecutions in courts of justice.

label: Judge
description: Presides over judicial proceedings and pronounces judgements in courts of law.

label: Notary
description: Draws up, records and certifies documents and instruments of legal importance.

label: Solicitor
description: Advises clients in matters of law, draws up contracts, wills, etc., instructs barristers.

label: Jurist (except Lawyer, Judge or Solicitor)
description: Performs legal functions (other than the general advice, preparation and contract work offered by solicitors, the pleading cases, the prosecuting of or the presiding over proceedings in courts or law).

label: Teacher, Level and Subject Unknown
description: Conducts courses of instruction, level unknown.

label: Teacher, Level and Subject Unknown, Not University and Higher Education Level
description: Conducts courses of instruction at the primary or secondary level of education.

label: Teacher, Level and Subject Unknown, Not Primary Education
description: Conducts courses of instruction at the secondary or university and higher education level.

label: University or Higher Education Teacher, Subject Unknown
description: Conducts courses of instruction at the third level of education, subject unknown.

label: Teacher in Physical Sciences (Third Level)
description: Conducts courses of instruction at the third level of education in physical science subjects.

label: Teacher in Engineering and Architecture (Third Level)
description: Conducts courses of instruction at the third level of education in engineering, architecture and town planning. Workers teaching industrial arts at the third (post-secondary) level, who conduct courses mainly of a practical nature for industrial technicians, foremen-supervisors and vocational training instructors in manufacturing, mining, construction and related techniques are classified in 1-31.80.

label: Teacher in Life and Medical Sciences (Third Level)
description: Conducts courses of instruction at the third level of education in life science and medical science subjects. Workers teaching medical therapy, advanced nursing and related arts (including optometry) at the third (post-secondary) level are classified in 1-31.75.

label: Teacher in Mathematics (Third Level)
description: Conducts courses of instruction at the third level of education in mathematics and related subjects.

label: Teacher in Economics and Commerce (Third Level)
description: Conducts courses of instruction at the third level of education in economics, business management and related subjects.

label: Teacher in Law (Third Level)
description: Conducts courses of instruction at the third level of education in law subjects.

label: Teacher in Education (Third Level)
description: Conducts courses of instruction at thethird level of education in the subject of education and supervises practical training in school class work of trainee-teachers.

label: Teacher in Agricultural Science (Third Level)
description: Conducts courses of instruction at the third level of education in agricultural science subjects.

label: Teacher in History, Philosophy, Sociology and Related Social Sciences (Third Level)
description: Conducts courses of instruction at the third level of education in history, philosophy, sociology and related social sciences.

label: Teacher in Languages and Literature (Third Level)
description: Conducts courses of instruction at the third level of education in languages and literature.

label: Teacher in Medical Therapy, Advanced Nursing and Related Arts
description: Conducts courses of instruction at the third level of education in medical therapy, nursing and related subjects.

label: Teacher in Industrial Arts (Third Level)
description: Conducts courses of instruction at the third level of education in techniques of manufacturing, mining and construction.

label: Other University and Higher Education Teachers
description: This group includes university and higher education teachers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in giving instruction, at the third level of education, in advertising, family planning, forensic science, community development, computer programming, co-operatives, home economics, industrial designing, library science, marketing, meteorological observation, military science, music, art painting, sculpture, navigation, public administration, sales methods, social welfare, telecommunications services, transport services, trade unionism or youth leadership. Teachers of music may also be performing musicians.

label: Secondary Education Teacher, Subject Unknown
description: Instructs pupils in an establishment of secondary education, subject unknown.

label: Languages and Literature Teacher (Second Level)
description: Instructs pupils in an establishment of secondary education in languages and literature.

label: Mathematics Teacher (Second Level)
description: Instructs pupils in an establishment of secondary education in mathematics and related subjects.

label: Natural Science Teacher (Second Level)
description: Instructs pupils in an establishment of secondary education in natural science subjects, such as chemistry, physics and biology.

label: Social Studies Teacher (Second Level)
description: Instructs pupils in an establishment of secondary education in social studies such as history, sociology, economics and geography.

label: Fine Arts Teacher (Second Level)
description: Instructs pupils, in an establishment of general or specialised secondary education, in fine arts subjects such as architecture, drawing and painting, music and dramatics. Teachers of music may also ne performing musicians.

label: Commercial and Secretarial Teacher (Second Level)
description: Instructs pupils, in an establishment of general or specialised education, in commercial and secretarial subjects.

label: Agricultural Science Teacher (Second Level)
description: Instructs pupils, in an establishment of general or specialised secondary education, in agronomy, animal husbandry and related subjects.

label: Domestic Science and General Nursing Teacher
description: Instructs pupils, in an establishment of general or specialised secondary education, in domestic science subjects and general nursing.

label: Technical Education Teacher (Second Level)
description: Instructs pupils, in an establishment of general or specialised secondary education, in crafts, industrial arts and other technical subjects.

label: Other Secondary Education Teachers
description: This group includes secondary education teachers not elsewhere classified, for example those occupied primarily in giving instruction, at the second level of education, in philosophy, principles and practice of physical education, pedagogy or other subject areas not covered by teachers described in the preceding definitions, and those occupied mainly in giving private lessons in any subject at the second level of education.

label: First-Level Education Teacher
description: Teaches primary academic subjects and elementary principles of social behaviour to children in an establishment of primary education.

label: Other Primary Education Teachers
description: This group includes primary education teachers not elsewhere classified, for example those mainly occupied in giving private lessons at the first level of education, or in teaching woodwork, basket-weaving, singing, art, sewing, or other arts and crafts in establishments of primary education, or in teaching reading, writing and other primary education subjects to adults who have not completed the first level of education, or in teaching the elements of the national language to newly arrived immigrants.

label: Kindergarten Teacher
description: Trains and organises activities of children in kindergarten to promote their physical, mental and social development.

label: Other Pre-Primary Education Teachers
description: This group includes pre-primary education teachers not elsewhere classified, for example those who organise group and individual activities such as group singing, games, drawing and simple handwork and supervise meal and rest periods in nursery schools for children of pre-kindergarten age.

label: Teacher of the Blind
description: Teaches secondary or primary education subjects to blind pupils, using braille.

label: Teacher of the Deaf
description: Teaches secondary or primary education subjects to deaf pupils, using lip reading and other special aids.

label: Teacher of the Mentally Handicapped
description: Teaches basic academic subjects to mentally handicapped children.

label: Other Special Education Teachers
description: This group includes special education teachers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in teaching physically handicapped children, other than the blind and deaf.

label: Education Methods Adviser
description: Studies curricula, teaching methods and other educational practices and advises on introduction of improvements.

label: Audio-Visual and Other Teaching Aid Specialist
description: Conducts research into audio-visual and other teaching aids and advises on, plans and organises their introduction in educational establishments.

label: Head Teacher
description: Plans, organises and co-ordinates educational curriculum, activities of teaching staff, and clerical and auxiliary services in a school.

label: School Inspector
description: Reviews and examines teachers' work and results achieved in application of curriculum programme of education system.

label: Governess
description: Teaches children in a private household in which she is also resident. May additionally carry out more general  instructional and supervisory duties associated with the care and training of children.

label: Other Teachers
description: This group includes teachers not elsewhere classified, for example those who teach children remanded to establishments for corrective training; those who specialise in visiting homes to assist schoolchildren who have scholastic, behavioural or personality problems and working out with children, parents and teachers ways for overcoming difficulties; and those performing educational therapy work, in collaboration with rehabilitation teams, for patients in hospitals and clinics.

label: Minister of Religion
description: Conducts religious worship, administers rites of faith or denomination and provides spiritual and moral guidance to members.

label: Missionary
description: Works to propagate a religious doctrine in own or foreign country.

label: Religious Worker (Member of Religious Order)
description: Participates as member of a religious order in various religious activities and assists members of the clergy.

label: Other Ministers of Religion and Related Members of Religious Orders
description: This group includes ministers of religion and related members of religious orders not elsewhere classified, for example those attached to a central body which formulates and co-ordinates religious practices, activities and teachings.

label: Faith Healer
description: Endeavours to cure human mental and physical ailments by power of faith.

label: Other Workers in Religion
description: This group includes other workers in religion, for example those who, as layman (not members of religious orders), perform various functions to assist religious leaders such as assisting in religious rites and ceremonial, conducting religious meetings, propagating doctrine and instructing children or other candidates for admittance to a particular faith; carry out research and study on theological questions; or perform other religious functions not elsewhere classified.

label: Author
description: Writes literary works for publication or dramatic presentation.

label: Critic
description: Appraises merits of literary, artistic and musical works and of musical, dramatic and other artistic performances and writes critiques for publication.

label: Author, Journalist or Related Writer, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational tasks listed in unit group 1-59.

label: Journalist
description: Collects, reports and comments on news and current affairs for publication in newspapers and periodicals or broadcasting by radio or television.

label: Editor, Newspapers and Periodicals
description: Selects, revises and arranges material for publication in newspapers and periodicals.

label: Sub-Editor, Newspapers  and Periodicals
description: Assists with editing of newspapers, magazines, trade journals and other publications.

label: Reporter
description: Seeks and reports information of interest to public for publication in newspapers.

label: Radio and Television Journalist
description: Collects reports and comments on news and current affairs for broadcasting over radio or television.

label: Continuity and Script Editor
description: Directs and co-ordinates work of writers preparing programmes, continuity and scripts for motion picture plays and television and radio broadcasts.

label: Book Editor
description: Appraises manuscripts submitted for publication in book form, makes recommendations thereon and edits or supervises editing of the material.

label: Advertising Copywriter
description: Writes advertising copy extolling merits of particular products or services.

label: Public Relations Officer
description: Plans and conducts public relations programmes on behalf of business or other organisations. Public relations manager is classified in 2-19.90.

label: Publicity Writer
description: Selects, assembles and prepares publicity material about business or other organisations for issue through press, radio, television and other media.

label: Technical Writer
description: Designs and writes manuals, brochures, handbooks and similar technical publications.

label: Other Authors, Journalists and Related Writers
description: This group includes journalists and related writers not elsewhere classified, for example those who compile and write material for encyclopaedias; write words for musical works; write scripts for television and radio productions; adapt plays for broadcasting or filming; or specialise in providing extempore commentaries on events of public interest, such as sports meetings, for broadcasting over radio or television.

label: Sculptor, Painter, Photographer or Related Creative Artist, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational tasks listed in unit groups 1-61 to 1-63.

label: Sculptor, Painter or Related Artist, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational tasks listed in unit group 1-61.

label: Sculptor
description: Creates three-dimensional decorative and representational forms by shaping materials such as wood, stone, clay, marble or metal.

label: Painter, Artist
description: Creates pictures, abstract designs and similar artistic compositions employing various media and techniques.

label: Cartoonist
description: Creates cartoons to depict persons and events, often in caricature.

label: Engraver and Etcher (Artistic)
description: Creates original designs and engraves or etches them on metal, wood or other materials for reproduction.

label: Painting Restorer
description: Restores damaged, soiled and faded paintings.

label: Other Sculptors, Painters and Related Artists
description: This group includes sculptors, painters and related artists not elsewhere classified, for example those who paint miniatures from portraits; create original designs for jewellery; create objets d'art in glass or ceramics; and repair objets d'art using same techniques as employed in their original creation.

label: Commercial Artist or Designer, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities listed in 1-62.20 to 1-62.90.

label: Commercial Artist
description: Creates and executes illustrations and designs for books, magazines, advertising and similar purposes.

label: Interior Decoration Designer
description: Designs interior decoration and plans furnishing of homes, public buildings, ships and other places.

label: Industrial and Commercial Products Designer
description: Creates designs for industrial and commercial products, harmonising aesthetic considerations with technical and other requirements. Garment patternmaker is classified in 7-94.20 and Shoe patternmaker in 8-02.15.

label: Display Artist
description: Creates and executes artistic effects for use in show windows and other places of display.

label: Other Commercial Artists and Designers
description: This group includes commercial artists and designers not elsewhere classified, for example those designing and painting stage scenery; designing armorial bearings; and tattooing decorative designs on clients' skins.

label: Photographer, General
description: Takes photographs of persons, places, merchandise and other subjects.

label: Portrait Photographer
description: Takes portrait photographs of persons.

label: Photographer, Commercial Illustrator
description: Takes photographs for commercial and industrial purposes such as advertising and publicity.

label: News Photographer
description: Takes photographs to illustrate stories and articles for publication in newspapers, magazines and similar journals.

label: Director of Photography (Motion Picture)
description: Plans and directs camera work for making motion pictures.

label: Motion Picture Camera Operator
description: Sets and operates motion picture camera to film scenes.

label: Television Camera Operator
description: Operates television camera to photograph scenes for broadcasting.

label: Other Photographers and Cameramen
description: This group includes photographers and cameramen not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in taking scientific, medical or architectural photographs, photographs to aid the police in crime detection, or aerial photographs. Medical X-ray technician is classified in 0-77.10.

label: Composer or Performing Artist, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit groups 1-71 to 1-79.

label: Composer
description: Conceives and writes musical compositions.Writers specialising in writing the words of songs and lyrics for musical works are classified in 1-59.90.

label: Orchestrator
description: Adapts or arranges music to suit particular instrumental groups, instruments or occasions.

label: Orchestra and Band Conductor
description: Conducts instrumental groups such as orchestras and bands.

label: Instrumentalist
description: Plays one or more musical instruments as soloist, accompanist or member of instrumental group.

label: Singer
description: Sings as soloist or member of vocal group.

label: Vocal Group Conductor
description: Conducts vocal groups such as choirs and choruses.

label: Other Composers, Musicians and Singers
description: This group includes composers, musicians and singers not elsewhere classified, for example those who select and arrange programmes of music for stage, film or broadcast productions.

label: Choreographer
description: Creates dances and instructs dancers in their performance.

label: Dancer
description: Performs dances as soloist, with partner or as member of dancing group.

label: Actor
description: Plays parts in dramatic productions.

label: Stage Director
description: Interprets presentation and directs rehearsals of theatrical productions.

label: Motion Picture, Radio and Television Director
description: Interprets presentation, conducts rehearsals and directs filming of motion pictures, or broadcasting of performances by radio and television.

label: Story-Teller
description: Tells stories or reads literary works aloud to educate and entertain listeners.

label: Other Actors and Stage Directors
description: This group includes actors and stage directors not elsewhere classified, for example those who impersonate other persons for the amusement of theatre and television audiences.

label: Theatrical Producer
description: Plans, organises and co-ordinates production of plays and other theatrical presentations.

label: Motion Picture Producer
description: Plans, organises and co-ordinates production of motion pictures.

label: Radio and Television Producer
description: Plans, organises and co-ordinates production of radio or television programmes.

label: Other Producers, Performing Arts
description: This group includes producers, performing arts, not elsewhere classified, for example those who supervise activities of stage crews and organise backstage activities such as allocation of dressing rooms, call systems, wardrobes, scenery and stage property.

label: Clown
description: Performs amusing antics and tricks and tells funny stories to amuse circus audiences.

label: Magician
description: Entertains circus, theatre, television and other audiences by performing tricks of illusion and sleight of hand.

label: Acrobat
description: Entertains circus, theatre, television and other audiences by performing difficult and spectacular acrobatics.

label: Aerialist
description: Entertains circus audiences by performing spectacular gymnastic feats on high trapeze.

label: Other Circus Performers
description: This group includes circus performers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in training and performing with animals such as lions, tigers, elephants, bears, monkeys or dogs; performing balancing feats on tight ropes or high wires; and performing juggling feats with balls, pins, plates and other objects.

label: Radio and Television Announcer
description: Reads news bulletins and makes other announcements for broadcasting over radio and television.

label: Compre
description: Introduces performing artists to music-hall, night-club, television, radio and other audiences.

label: Town cryer
description: Makes public proclamations in streets on behalf of a  local authority.

label: Other Performing Artists
description: This group includes performing artists not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in entertaining audiences by imitating bird and animal noises; performing feats of hypnotism; operating puppet shows; and performing feats of ventriloquism.

label: Professional Sportsman
description: Participates in public competitive sporting events for gain. Workers playing chess, bridge, billiards or similar games for gain are classified in 1-80.90.

label: Sports Coach
description: Coaches sportsmen to develop their knowledge, ability and performance in their sport. Workers teaching chess, bridge and similar games are classified in 1-80.90.

label: Sports Official
description: Participates in regulation of conduct of sporting competitions.

label: Physical Trainer
description: Instructs students and other persons in development and maintenance of their own physical fitness by means of gymnastic and other exercises.

label: Other Athletes, Sportsmen and Related Workers
description: This group includes athletes, sportsmen and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those teaching chess, billiards or card games or playing such games for gain.

label: Librarian
description: Organises develops and maintains systematic collections of books, periodicals and other recorded material and makes them available to library user.

label: Archivist
description: Collects, organises and preserves records and historically valuable documents.

label: Art Gallery and Museum Curator
description: Organises, develops and maintains collections of art objects in an art gallery or historical, scientific or other exhibits in a museum.

label: Other Librarians, Archivists and Curators
