description: This group includes librarians, archivists and curators not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in collecting, appraising, classifying, compiling and indexing information on specific subjects of interest to business or other organisations.

label: Sociologist
description: Studies origin, development, structure, social patterns and interrelationships of human society.

label: Psychologist
description: Studies human behaviour and mental processes and investigates, and recommends treatment for, psychological problems in such fields as medicine, education and industry.

label: Anthropologist
description: Traces origin and evolution of man through study of changes in his physical characteristics, cultural and social institutions, and living conditions.

label: Geographer
description: Studies characteristics of man's physical and climatic environment, the distribution of populations and human activities on the earth.

label: Historian
description: Conducts research into one or more phases or aspects of past human activity. Archivist is classified in 1-91.30.

label: Political Scientist
description: Conducts research into theory, origin, development, operation and interrelationships of political institutions, movements and behaviour.

label: Other Sociologists, Anthropologists and Related Scientists
description: This group includes sociologists, anthropologists and related scientists not elsewhere classified, for example those who trace the genealogical background of particular families.

label: Social Worker, General
description: Helps individuals and families to understand and resolve their personal and social problems.

label: Social Welfare Worker
description: Provides advice and assistance to individuals and families to promote their social welfare.

label: Culture Centre Worker
description: Organises and supervises social, recreational and educational activities in youth clubs, community centres and similar organisations.

label: Social Worker, Delinquency
description: Works to prevent development of juvenile delinquency or to achieve social and moral rehabilitation of juvenile and adult delinquents.

label: Psychiatric Social Worker
description: Helps the mentally ill and maladjusted to submit and respond to psychiatric treatment and to resolve their personal and social problems, and looks after the welfare of the mentally subnormal.

label: Other Social Workers
description: This group includes social workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in the prevention of cruelty to children; helping the physically handicapped, the blind and the deaf to adjust to their disabilities and to cope with any associated personal or social problems; or planning and organising a home-help service for persons unable to cope with the running of their own homes.

label: Personnel Specialist
description: Performs personnel functions relating to employee recruitment, placement, training, promotion, compensation, employee-management relations or other areas of personnel work. Personnel manager is classified in 2-19.80.

label: Vocational Guidance Counsellor
description: Advises individuals concerning career choices and development of work qualifications.

label: Occupational Analyst
description: Analyses occupations to assist personnel, administrative, information and other services of private, public or governmental organisations.

label: Other Personnel and Occupational Specialists
description: This group includes personnel and occupational specialists not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in organising and co-ordinating accident prevention programmes and procedures within an industrial organisation. Workers who specialise in the engineering aspects of industrial accident prevention are classified in unit group 0-28.

label: Philologist
description: Studies origin, development and structure of languages.

label: Translator
description: Translates recorded verbal matter from one language to another.

label: Interpreter
description: Interprets the spoken word from one language into another.

label: Patent Agent
description: Gives advice concerning patents and assists in preparing applications for patents, or examines applications submitted for registration. Workers concerned solely with the technical aspects of patent work are classified according to their field of technical specialisation.

label: Home Economist
description: Carries out research in home economics and interprets and applies principles of home management to promote health and welfare of families, to develop new consumer goods and to promote consumption of household goods.

label: Advertising Account Executive
description: Plans, directs and co-ordinates production of advertising campaigns for particular clients of an advertising agency.

label: Underwriter
description: Reviews applications for insurance, evaluates risks involved and determines the premiums, maximum extent of cover and other conditions to be attached to insurance policies.

label: Astrologer and Fortune Teller
description: Makes forecasts of future events for particular clients or the general public basing predictions either on the positions of stars and planets at specified times or on characteristics of clients' palms, samples of playing cards drawn at random, or other factors. Performers entertaining audiences by mock interpretations of signs in palms, playing cards, crystal balls or other media and by giving demonstrations of professed powers of mental telepathy are classified in 1-79.90.

label: Other Professional, Technical and Related Workers Not Elsewhere Classified
description: This group includes other professional, technical and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who act as agents for writers in the obtaining and negotiation of contracts for the publication of their works, or arrange contracts for performing artists and take care of their business interests.

label: Legislative Official
description: Presides over, or takes part in, the activities of a national, state, provincial or local government legislative body or administrative council as an elected or appointed member.

label: Government Administrator
description: Plans, organises, directs and controls, subject to a broad mandate from political head or governing body, the activities of a national, state, provincial or local government department (or subdepartment), government administrative agency or intergovernmental organisation (or one of its departments); advises political head or governing body on important policy questions; makes decisions within his or her broad discretionary power; performs other high-level functions in connection with government administration.

label: Manager, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in minor group 2-1.

label: General Manager
description: Plans, organises, directs and controls, on proprietors' or on own behalf, an industrial, commercial or other undertaking, establishment or organisation, and coordinates the work of departmental managers or other immediate subordinates. Where the simple, undefined term >Manufacturer= occurs it can be coded to either 2-11.10 or 9-99.99. Where the title indicates a manufacturer of something (e.g. >Fabricant de papier=) it can be coded to either 2-11.10 or the relevant production code in Major Groups 7, 8 or 9 (i.e. in the case of >Fabricant de papier=, 7-34.00). Examples of the latter product-defining titles are not given below but are listed in the alphabetical language-based coding index.

label: Production Manager, Specialization Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 2-12.

label: Production Manager (except Farm)
description: Plans, organises and controls the production activities of an undertaking or establishment, ensuring efficient use of equipment, materials and personnel, and participates in formulating the production policy of the undertaking.

label: Farm Manager
description: Plans, organises and controls the operation of a farm on behalf of private, collective or public owner.

label: Contractor
description: Contracts on predetermined terms to provide labour and materials and to be responsible for the completion of a job or project in accordance with established specifications or plans.

label: Sales Manager, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 2-13.

label: Sales Manager (except Wholesale and Retail Trade)
description: Plans, organises and controls sales activities of an industrial undertaking or other organisation, except a wholesale or retail business, and participates in formulating sales policy.

label: Sales Manager (Wholesale Trade)
description: Plans and organises a business or a branch of a business in wholesale trade and directs workers engaged in selling goods to retailers and to industrial, commercial or other large consumers.

label: Sales Manager (Retail Trade)
description: Plans and organises a business in retail trade and directs workers engaged in selling goods for personal or household consumption or utilisation.

label: Hotel and Restaurant Manager
description: Plans and organises a hotel and restaurant or motel on behalf of the proprietors to provide accommodation and meals for guests and directs and controls staff to ensure efficient and profitable operation.

label: Restaurant Manager
description: Plans and organises a restaurant on behalf of the proprietors to provide food and beverages for guests, and directs and controls staff to ensure efficient and profitable operation.

label: Ship's Purser
description: Supervises and co-ordinates activities of crew members aboard ship concerned with shipboard business matters and social activities of passengers.

label: Other Managers (Catering, Lodging and Leisure Services)
description: This group includes catering, lodging and leisure managers not elsewhere classified, for example those who manage temporary or permanent lodging facilities, such as boarding or guest houses and caravan parks; cafeterias, bars, cafs and canteens; refreshment stands at sporting events, and public gatherings. This group also includes those who manage leisure facilities, such as sports halls, swimming pools, playing fields, recreation rooms and amusement parks.

label: Research and Development Manager
description: Plans, organises and controls research and development work, in an industrial enterprise or other establishment, relating to such matters as development of new or improved technical processes, new or improved products and utilisation of different materials, and participates in formulating research policy.

label: Administration Manager
description: Plans, organises and controls the internal administration of an industrial, commercial or other organisation and participates in formulating the administrative policy of the organisation. Workers sometimes described as "office managers", who are occupied mainly in directly supervising workers in clerical occupations, are classified in unit group 2-21.

label: Budgeting and Accounting Manager
description: Plans, organises and controls, within powers delegated to him, the financial operations of an industrial, commercial or other organisation and participates in formulating the financial policy of the organisation.

label: Transport Operations Managers
description: Plans, organises and controls operational activities in road, rail, air or water transport and participates in formulating policies to ensure the efficient handling of freight and passenger traffic and the best use of transport equipment. Railway station managers are classified in 2-22.10.

label: Operations Manager (Postal or Telecommunications Services)
description: Plans, organises and controls operational activities of a postal or telecommunications service and participates in formulating policy concerning operation and development of the service. Postmasters are classified in 2-22.20.

label: Industrial Relations and Personnel Manager
description: Plans, organises and controls industrial relations and personnel activities of an industrial or commercial undertaking or other organisation and participates in formulating the recruitment, training, wages, safety, welfare and other personnel policies of the undertaking.

label: Other Managers
description: Workers in this group plan, organise, direct and control a department within an undertaking, establishment or organisation, such as departments concerned with the following: buying business and other services or supplies and materials for processing and fabrication; warehouse, bond store or cold store services; pipeline services; advertising, public relations and public information services; investment and loans services; or perform other managerial activities not elsewhere classified.

label: Supervisor, Foremen or Inspector, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in minor group 2-2.

label: Clerical Supervisor, General
description: Supervises and co-ordinates the daily activities of workers engaged in clerical and related duties in the general office of a public or private establishment, or of those engaged in such work in more than one section of an establishment.

label: Other Clerical Supervisors
description: This group includes clerical supervisors not elsewhere classified, for example those who supervise workers engaged in various clerical and related occupations in one particular section of an establishment.

label: Railway Station Master
description: Organises, controls and co-ordinates passenger and related railway services at a railway station and supervises the operation of trains within the station limits.

label: Postmaster
description: Organises, controls and co-ordinates postal and related services in an urban locality or other limited geographical area.

label: Railway Service Supervisor
description: Supervises and co-ordinates one or more of the service activities of the traffic department of a railway undertaking. Railway station master is classified in 2-22.10 and Railway goods agent in 2-22.45.

label: Train Dispatcher
description: Directs the movement of trains within a division or zone of a railway system.

label: Railway Transport Service Inspector
description: Makes field inspections of railway and underground transport services.

label: Railway Goods Agent
description: Directs and controls freight service at a railway yard.

label: Road Transport Service Supervisor
description: Supervises and co-ordinates one or more of the service activities of the traffic department of a road transport undertaking.

label: Road Passenger Transport Service Inspector
description: Makes field inspections of road passenger transport services.

label: Air Transport Service Supervisor
description: Supervises and co-ordinates one or more service activities of an air transport undertaking.

label: Air Traffic Controller
description: Clears aircraft for landings and take-offs at airport and controls aircraft in flight in the vicinity of airport or in a designated sector of airspace.

label: Flight Operations Officer
description: Co-ordinates flight planning and assists in monitoring of en-route operations.

label: Telecommunications Service Supervisor
description: Controls and supervises telecommunications operational services, such as radio, telephone and telegraph. Foremen-supervisors concerned with installation and maintenance of telecommunications equipment are classified in unit group 8-56 and Telecommunications engineers are classified in 0-23.40.

label: Postal Services Supervisor
description: Supervises and co-ordinates mail collection, sorting and distribution services, for a defined geographical area.

label: Other Transport and Communications Supervisors
description: This group includes transport and communications supervisors, dispatchers and controllers not classified elsewhere, for example those supervising and co-ordinating one or more of the operational activities of a barge, ferry or pipeline service and supervising the activities of workers engaged therein.

label: Sales Supervisor (Wholesale Trade)
description: Supervises workers in a wholesale trade establishment engaged in buying goods for resale and selling them to retailers and to industrial, commercial or other large consumers.

label: Sales Supervisor (Retail Trade)
description: Supervises workers in a retail trade establishment engaged in buying goods for resale and selling them for personal or household consumption or other use.

label: Other Sales Supervisors
description: Workers in this group perform sales supervisory duties not elsewhere classified, for example those who supervise canvassing, display or demonstration activities; inspect sales activities in various branches or departments of a retail or wholesale establishment; supervise sales workers employed in the sales department of a manufacturing enterprise; inspect the activities and results of distribution agencies within a specified territorial division engaged in selling the products of an industrial, import or other undertaking; give expert advice on sales production methods.

label: Housekeeper (except Private Service)
description: Plans, organises and supervises the work of domestic staff in hotels and other institutions.

label: Housekeeper (Private Service, in Hotels, or in Other Institutions)
description: Plans, organises and supervises the work of domestic staff in private households, hotels or other institutions.

label: Housekeeper (Private Service)
description: Organises and supervises the work of domestic staff in private households.

label: House Steward
description: Controls the purchase, storage and issue of foodstuffs and kitchen supplies and supervises and co-ordinates the work of pantry, storeroom and kitchen staff not engaged in cooking in hotels, restaurants and clubs.

label: Ship Chief Steward
description: Plans, co-ordinates and supervises the activities of crew engaged in housekeeping and meal serving on board passenger or cargo vessels.

label: Housekeeping Matron
description: Organises and supervises the work of domestic staff and supervises the general welfare and conduct of individuals in residential institutions.

label: Other Housekeeping and Related Service Supervisors
description: This group includes housekeeping supervisors not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform supervisory tasks in establishments providing only shelter, such as tourist camps and lodging houses; act as butler in private households.

label: Farm Supervisor
description: Supervises operations in connection with growing, harvesting and marketing of agricultural produce, and maintenance of machinery, implements and equipment, under the direction of the farm manager.

label: Production Supervisor or Foreman, General
description: Supervises production activities in a distinct unit within an establishment, and controls and co-ordinates activities of workers in this unit engaged in various processing and fabricating occupations.

label: Supervisor and General Foreman (Mining, Quarrying and Well-Drilling)
description: Supervises production activities of a distinct unit in a mine or quarry or at well-drilling site and controls and co-ordinates the activities of workers at this unit engaged in various extracting occupations.

label: Supervisor and General Foreman (Metal Processing)
description: Supervises production activities of a distinct unit within a metal-processing establishment and controls and co-ordinates the activities of workers in this unit engaged in various occupations.

label: Supervisor and General Foreman (Chemical and Related Materials Processing)
description: Supervises production activities of a distinct unit within an establishment concerned with the processing of basic chemical components and related materials, including petroleum refining and preparation of paper pulp, and controls and co-ordinates activities of workers in this unit engaged in various occupations.

label: Supervisor and General Foreman (Manufacturing of Machinery and Metal Products)
description: Supervises production activities of a distinct unit within an establishment concerned with manufacturing and assembly of mechanical equipment and metal products, such as machinery, precision instruments and scientific apparatus, transport equipment and metal parts of various kinds, and controls and co-ordinates the activities of workers in this unit engaged in various occupations.

label: Supervisor and General Foreman (Manufacturing and Installation of Electrical and Electronic Equipment)
description: Supervises production activities of a distinct unit within an establishment concerned with the manufacture of electrical and electronic equipment and controls and co-ordinates the activities of workers in this unit engaged in various occupations.

label: Supervisor and General Foreman (Fabrication of Products of Paper, Plastics, Rubber, Chemical and Synthetic Materials)
description: Supervises production activities of a distinct unit within an establishment concerned with the fabrication of products from paper, rubber, plastics or other synthetic materials or the manufacture of pharmaceutical and chemical products, and controls and co-ordinates the activities of workers in this unit engaged in various occupations.

label: Supervisor and General Foreman (Food and Beverages Processing)
description: Supervises production activities of a distinct unit within an establishment in which foodstuffs and beverages are processed or manufactured on an industrial basis, and controls and co-ordinates the activities of the workers in this unit engaged in various occupations.

label: Supervisor and General Foreman (Production of Textiles and Clothing Manufacturing)
description: Supervises production activities of a distinct unit within an establishment in which textiles are produced or clothing is manufactured, and controls and co-ordinates the activities of the workers in this unit engaged in various occupations.

label: Supervisor and General Foreman (Construction Work)
description: Supervises, on a construction site, activities of a distinct unit of a construction enterprise which executes a construction project, or one or more phases thereof, and controls and co-ordinates the activities of the workers in this unit engaged in various occupations.

label: Supervisor and General Foreman (Production and Distribution of Electricity, Gas and Water)
description: Supervises the activities of a distinct unit within an establishment concerned with the production and distribution of electricity, steam or gas, or with water supply, sewage disposal and treatment, or refrigeration and assimilated services, and controls and co-ordinates the activities of the workers in this unit engaged in various occupations.

label: Other Production Supervisors and General Foremen
description: This group includes other supervisors and general foremen not elsewhere classified. Included are those performing tasks similar to those of Production supervisor or general foreman, general (2-26.10) in a production unit concerned with an activity such as printing; processing non-metallic minerals; processing skins, pelts and leathers; fabricating wood, stone, clay and glass products; fabricating products made from assorted materials.

label: Clerical or Related Worker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) occupational activities described in minor groups 3-1 to 3-9.

label: Government Executive Official, Specialisation Unknown
description: Puts into effect, according to instructions from administrators, the policy decisions of central, state, provincial or local government and implements laws, rules and administrative regulations; takes decisions on matters arising in the detailed implementation of instructions from administrators, subjects to reference of exceptional or important questions or cases for determination at higher level. Specialisation unknown.

label: Tax Collector
description: Receives taxes on behalf of local, regional or central administration. May collect duty and impose penalties for contravention of tax regulations. May do so in person or via correspondence.

label: Tax Assessor
description: Calculates the amount of tax to be paid by individuals or businesses, according to various criteria, such as income, property, profits etc.

label: Customs officers
description: Checks persons, vehicles and goods for legal import allowances. May collect duty and impose penalties for contravention of customs regulations.

label: Government Executive Officials not Elsewhere Classified
description: This group includes government officials not elsewhere classified, such as those who deal with issues such as finance, trade, health, education, social insurance and employment

label: Stenographer-Typist, General
description: Records various kinds of dictated or other matter in shorthand and makes a transcription in typewritten form.

label: Stenographic Secretary
description: Records various kinds of dictated or other matter in shorthand, makes a transcription in typewritten form, and performs certain clerical duties to relieve superior of routine tasks.

label: Verbatim Reporter
description: Makes verbatim records of proceedings by shorthand writing or using a shorthand-writing machine.

label: Typist
description: Transcribes in typewritten form letters, reports, documents, accounts and other material from written or printed sources, from recordings on a dictating machine, or other sources.

label: Teletypist
description: Sends and receives messages by means of a teleprinter. Telegrapher is classified in 3-80.40.

label: Other Stenographers, Typists and Teletypists
description: This group includes stenographers, typists and teletypists not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate typewriters with removable type of various sizes and styles.

label: Card- and Tape-Punching Machine Operator
description: Operates alphabetic or numeric key-punch machine to record data on cards or tapes or to verify the correctness of punching.

label: Other Card- and Tape-Punching Machine Operators
description: This group includes card- and tape-punching machine operators not elsewhere classified, such as those who work on specialised equipment such as flexowriters or on special verifying machines.

label: Bookkeeper, General
description: Maintains complete records of financial transactions of an undertaking. Accountants are classified in unit group 1-10.

label: Bookkeeping Clerk
description: Maintains records of one phase of an undertaking's financial transactions, for example accounts receivable or accounts payable or performs other limited bookkeeping functions. Workers occupied mainly in operating bookkeeping machines are classified in 3-41.20.

label: Office Cashier
description: Takes charge of cash and keeps records of cash transactions incidental to the conduct of a business.

label: Cashier, Office or Cash Desk
description: Takes charge of cash and keeps records of cash transactions incidental to the conduct of a business (3-31.30) or receives cash in payment for goods or services and gives change to clients in a retail store, railway or boat station, theatre or other establishment or performs simple cash-handling operations in a bank (3-31.60).

label: Bank Teller
description: Deals directly with clients of a bank in respect of deposits and withdrawals and related matters. Workers transacting business relating to loans, investments and similar financial matters are classified in 3-39.40.

label: Money Changer
description: Changes money from one currency to another.

label: Cash Desk Cashier
description: Receives cash in payment for goods or services and gives change to clients in a retail store, railway or boat station, theatre or other establishment or performs simple cash-handling operations in a bank. Transport conductors are classified in unit group 3-60.

label: Post Office Counter Clerk
description: Receives letters and parcels, sells postage stamps and conducts other post office counter business such as services for the transfer or banking of money and the payment of accounts or licence fees. Other clerical workers employed by postal organisations are classified elsewhere according to the particular work performed, for example Mail sorting clerk (3-70.20), Correspondence clerk (3-93.20), Filing clerk (3-95.30), etc..

label: Other Bookkeepers and Cashiers
description: This group includes bookkeepers and cashiers not elsewhere classified, for example those who check bookkeeping entries and other financial records to verify their accuracy and completeness.

label: Cost Computing Clerk
description: Calculates wage, material, overhead and other operational costs of an establishment.

label: Wages Clerk
description: Calculates wages due from records of hours worked or work performed by individual employees. Workers whose duties consist mainly of maintaining records of time worked, or periods workers have been on duty, are classified in 3-39.90.

label: Finance Clerk
description: Carries out specialised clerical tasks relating to financial transactions of a bank, investment house or other financial organisation.

label: Other Bookkeepers, Cashiers and Related Workers
description: This group includes bookkeepers, cashiers and other related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those collecting rents or hire purchase payments; keeping records of times of arrival and departure of workers; changing currency units of large denominations into smaller units.

label: Bookkeeping Machine Operator
description: Operates a bookkeeping machine to make records of business transactions.

label: Calculating Machine Operator
description: Operates an electrical or manually actuated machine which makes arithmetical calculations.

label: Electronic Computer Operator
description: Sets and controls electronic computer to process business, scientific, engineering or other data according to operating instructions. Computer programmer is classified in 0-84.20.

label: Punched-Card Machine Operator
description: Operates machines in which cards punched with holes representing statistical or other data are sorted into specific groups, or machines which process data from cards into tabulated and recorded form. Card- and tape-punching machine operator is classified in 3-22.20.

label: Other Automatic Data-Processing Machine Operators
description: This group includes automatic data processing machine operators not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate card-to-tape or tape-to-card converting machines; operate optical scanning equipment for transferring mechanically information represented by specially marked characters to punched cards, tape or other documents; or operate other specialised equipment for use in connection with computers such as high speed printing equipment.

label: Transport Conductor, Specialisation Unknown
description: Takes charge of passengers in either trains, or buses, or other public transport vehicles.

label: Railway Passenger Train Guard
description: Takes charge of passenger train during journey. Railway freight train guards are classified in 9-84.20.

label: Sleeping- or Pullman-Car Attendant
description: Takes charge of sleeping car or pullman car on a railway train. Workers on railway dining, buffet and parlour cars whose duties consist wholly or mainly of preparing or serving meals and alcoholic or other refreshments are classified in minor group 5-3.

label: Bus Conductor
description: Issues tickets and supervises safety and comfort of passengers on buses and trams.

label: Other Transport Conductors
description: This group includes transport conductors not elsewhere classified, for example those in charge of passengers in cable cars, ferries and hovercraft.

label: Mail Distribution Clerk, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) occupational activities described in unit group 3-70.

label: Mail Distribution Clerk, General
description: Sorts, records, dispatches and delivers mail, messages and packages to private homes and/or businesses for public or private postal services.

label: Mail Sorting Clerk
description: Sorts and dispatches mail according to destination and performs associated duties according to employment in postal or other establishment.

label: Postman
description: Delivers mail along a regular route to private homes and business establishments after sorting it according to streets and street numbers.

label: Messenger
description: Delivers messages, packages and other items to offices or other commercial premises within an establishment or elsewhere.

label: Other Mail Distribution Clerks
description: This group includes mail distribution clerks not elsewhere classified, for example those dispatching outgoing mail after calculating required postage and affixing stamps or franking mail in a machine.

label: Telephone or Telegraph Operator, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) occupational activities described in unit group 3-80.

label: Telephone Switchboard Operator
description: Operates a telephone switchboard or a section thereof, dealing with local or long-distance calls.

label: Radio-Telephone Operator (Land-Based)
description: Operates land-based radio telephone equipment to transmit messages to or receive them from ships, aircraft, vehicles, field or other installations.

label: Telegrapher
description: Operates telegraphic equipment to transmit and receive messages by wire or radio.

label: Ship's Radio Officer
description: Operates radio telegraph and radio telephone equipment on board a ship.

label: Flight Radio Operator
description: Operates radio equipment aboard aircraft in flight.

label: Other Telephone and Telegraph Operators
description: This group includes telephone and telegraph operators not elsewhere classified, for example those engaged mainly in receiving and transmitting information and messages by telephone.

label: Stock Clerk, General
description: Receives, weighs, stores, checks, dispatches and maintains records of goods and materials.

label: Dispatching and Receiving Clerk
description: Arranges the transmission of goods, invoices and other related materials and keeps appropriate records.

label: Stock Records Clerk
description: Maintains stock records of an enterprise, verifies issues, estimates needs and requisitions new stocks.

label: Storeroom Clerk
description: Receives, stores and issues tools, merchandise, equipment or other goods and maintains relevant records.

label: Weighing Clerk
description: Weighs goods received, issued, produced or dispatched and maintains relevant clerical records.

label: Other Stock Clerks
description: This group includes stock clerks not elsewhere classified, for example those who compile inventories of furniture and household effects received for storage in depositories.

label: Material Planning Clerk
description: Computes quantities of materials required for the production or construction programme of an undertaking, ascertains stocks, schedules deliveries and verifies execution of orders.

label: Production Planning Clerk
description: Prepares or assists in preparing production operations schedules, using data derived from customers' orders and information on production capacity and performance.

label: Office Clerk, General
description: Performs variety of clerical tasks, depending on nature and size of office in which employed.

label: Correspondence Clerk
description: Composes and sends letters and takes other action necessary to deal with the correspondence of private employers, associations, companies or official bodies.

label: Personnel Clerk
description: Keeps employment records of an organisation's personnel.

label: Legal Clerk
description: Carries out specialised clerical tasks in connection with legal matters.

label: Insurance Clerk
description: Carries out specialised tasks incidental to the transaction of life, fire, marine, automobile or other type of insurance.

label: Other Correspondence and Reporting Clerks
description: This group includes correspondence and reporting clerks not elsewhere classified, for example those who write letters and complete forms on behalf of illiterate persons; prepare or revise mailing lists, telephone directories and other lists of names and addresses from letters, cards, vouchers and other sources.

label: Receptionist, General
description: Receives people coming into an establishment, ascertains their wants and directs them accordingly.

label: Hotel Receptionist
description: Receives guests at hotels and similar establishments and performs a variety of services for them on arrival, departure and during their stay.

label: Doctor's or Dentist's Receptionist
description: Receives patient in doctor's or dentist's consulting rooms, makes appointments and keeps records of patients' visits. Dental chairside attendants are classified in 5-99.40.

label: Travel Agency Clerk
description: Prepares itineraries and makes travel and hotel reservations for customers. Workers mainly employed in the routine issuing of travel tickets for cash are classified in 3-31.60.

label: Other Receptionists and Travel Agency Clerks
description: This group includes receptionists and travel agency clerks not elsewhere classified, for example those who receive air travellers at airport, check their tickets and conduct them to aircraft or customs hall; work at an information desk in a department store and answer customers' inquiries concerning the location of particular goods and other matters.

label: Library Clerk
description: Maintains library records relating to the acquisition, issue and return of books and other publications and performs related duties.

label: Filing Clerk
description: Classifies and systematically files papers, documents and other records.

label: Statistical Clerk
description: Compiles statistical records based on routine or special sources of information. Workers devising and conducting statistical inquiries or evaluating results according to principles of statistical analysis are classified in minor group 0-8.

label: Coding Clerk (Data-Processing)
description: Determines appropriate classifications of items of information and converts data into code form for purposes of data-processing operations.

label: Proof Reader
description: Compares printers' proofs with original material and marks errors for correction.

label: Office Machine Operator (Reproduction Processes)
description: Operates office machines which reproduce copies of documents by photographic, photo-offset, multigraph or similar means or which print, on forms and envelopes, addresses and similar brief entries from prepared plates.

label: Railway Clerk
description: Performs a variety of clerical tasks related to railway business.

label: Other Clerks
description: This group includes clerical workers not elsewhere classified, for example those sorting forms or other documents by hand; making a routine inspection of documents and marking them with identification numbers; addressing circulars and envelopes by hand; operating machines which sort documents for filing or collate sets of pages of reproduced documents.

label: Working Proprietor (Wholesale Trade)
description: Conducts a business in wholesale trade on own behalf or in partnership, buying goods and selling them to retailers and to industrial, commercial or other large consumers.

label: Working Proprietor (Wholesale or Retail Trade)
description: Conducts a business either in wholesale trade (4-10.20) or in retail trade (4-10.30).

label: Working Proprietor (Retail Trade)
description: Conducts a business in retail trade on own behalf or in partnership, buying goods and selling them for personal or household consumption or other use.

label: Working Proprietor (Hiring Out)
description: Conducts a business by hiring services and vehicles.

label: Buyer
description: Buys goods for resale in wholesale and retail trade.

label: Purchasing Agent
description: Buys machinery, equipment, raw materials, services and other supplies for use or consumption by a manufacturing, commercial, government agency or other undertaking.

label: Technical Salesman
description: Sells products and services, such as chemical, mechanical, electrical and electronic supplies, using specialised knowledge of the technology of the composition, utilisation and maintenance of the goods or equipment sold.

label: Technical Service Adviser
description: Advises customers on the application, installation and operation of specialised equipment, supplies and services.

label: Commercial Traveller or Manufacturer's Agent, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not both) of the occupational activities described in unit group 4-32.

label: Commercial Traveller
description: Solicits orders by personally visiting clients and sells goods to retailers, industrial consumers, institutional and professional establishments or wholesale organisations in an allotted geographical area.

label: Manufacturers' Agent
description: Sells products of one or more home or foreign manufacturers to wholesale and retail establishments on a commission basis, in an allotted geographical area. Performs essentially the same duties as a Commercial Traveller (4-32.20) but usually represents several manufacturers of related products.

label: Insurance, Real Estate, Securities or Business Services Salesman or Auctioneer, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) occupational activities described in minor group 4-4.

label: Insurance, Real Estate or Securities Salesmen, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) occupational activities described in unit group 4-41.

label: Insurance Salesman
description: Sells life, accident, endowment, fire, marine and other types of insurance.

label: Estate Agent
description: Sells and leases property, such as building lots, houses, apartments and estates, on a commission basis.

label: Stock Broker
description: Buys or sells stocks and bonds of public or private organisations for customers on a commission basis.

label: Other Insurance, Real Estate and Securities Salesmen
description: This group includes insurance, real estate and securities salesmen not elsewhere classified.

label: Business Services Salesman (except Advertising)
description: Sells one or more business services (except advertising services).

label: Advertising Salesman
description: Sells advertising space in press and periodicals, on poster boards and elsewhere and advertising time on radio and television programmes.

label: Auctioneer
description: Sells by auction various kinds of new or used property and goods, such as real estate, furniture, livestock, farm products and objets d'art.

label: Appraiser
description: Determines value of real estate, industrial equipment, personal and household effects, works of art, gems and other articles, by examining them for condition and authenticity.

label: Wholesale Trade Salesperson
description: Sells goods in a wholesale establishment to retailers and large-scale consumers.

label: Salesperson, Wholesale or Retail Trade
description: Sells goods in a wholesale establishment (4-51.20) or in a shop or similar retail trade establishment (4-51.30).

label: Retail Trade Salesperson
description: Sells goods in a shop or similar retail trade establishment.

label: Fashion Model
description: Wears and displays clothing for sale in showrooms and other places in order to demonstrate style and other characteristics.

label: Demonstrator
description: Gives demonstrations of articles for sale, in wholesale, retail and industrial establishments, at exhibitions, or in private houses.

label: Other Salesmen, Shop Assistants and Demonstrators
description: This group includes salesmen and shop assistants not elsewhere classified, for example those who replenish stocks and assist customers according to written or telephoned requests; conduct and assist customers in their purchasing in a self-service store; those who sell petrol, oil or other motoring requirements in a garage, motor service station or similar establishement to customers.

label: Street Vendor
description: Sells goods such as fruit, vegetables, ice-cream, coal or wood on street or waterway or from door to door.

label: Canvasser
description: Solicits business for an establishment, particularly from households, by going from door to door.

label: News Vendor
description: Sells newspapers on streets or distributes them to regular subscribers.

label: Other Street Vendors, Canvassers and News Vendors
description: This group includes street vendors, canvassers and newsvendors not elsewhere classified, for example those heating foodstuffs, such as chestnuts and frankfurters, and selling them from street stands.

label: Pawnbroker
description: Estimates the value of articles offered as pledges and lends money on deposit of the articles.

label: Waste Collector
description: Collects waste material such as rags, bones or scrap metal for reselling or recycling.

label: Other Sales workers
description: This group includes sales workers not elsewhere classified, for example those selling refreshments and confectionery or programmes in places of entertainment.

label: Working Proprietor (Catering, Lodging or Leisure Services), Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) occupational activities described in unit group 5-10.

label: Working Proprietor (Hotel and Restaurant)
description: Operates a hotel and restaurant or motel on own account or in partnership, to provide accommodation and meals for guests.

label: Working Proprietor (Restaurant)
description: Operates a restaurant on own account or in partnership, to provide food and beverages for guests.

label: Working Proprietor (Guest House)
description: Operates a guest house on own account or in partnership, to provide temporary or permanent accommodation for guests.

label: Working Proprietor (Caf, Bar and Snack Bar)
description: Operates a caf, bar or snack bar on own account or in partnership, to sell food or alcoholic and other beverages to customers.

label: Other Working Proprietors (Catering, Lodging and Leisure Services)
description: This group includes working proprietors of catering and lodging services not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate rooming houses which do not supply meals, cafeterias and canteens, caravan parks, golf courses, swimming pools, billiard halls, and fairground rides.

label: Cook, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in 5-31.20 to 5-31.90.

label: Head Cook
description: Plans meals and supervises and co-ordinates work of cooks and kitchen helpers in hotels, restaurants or other establishments and on railway trains.

label: Cook, Except Private Service
description: Prepares all kinds of hot and cold meals, snacks, pastries, etc. for consumption in hotels, restaurants railway dining-cars, air planes, clubs, schools, cafeterias and other catering facilities.

label: Cook, Private Service
description: Prepares and cooks meals in private households.

label: Ship's Cook
description: Prepares and cooks meals on ships.

label: Other Cooks
description: This group includes cooks not elsewhere classified, for example those who prepare special foods for diets; prepare, cook and serve food on camp sites for construction, mineral exploration, farm and other workers; perform various tasks in preparation of food such as cleaning and peeling vegetables.

label: Waiter, General
description: Serves food and beverages in hotels, restaurants and other catering facilities.

label: Head Waiter
description: Takes charge of dining-room, restaurant or section thereof in hotels, restaurants, clubs, institutions and similar commercial establishments, on board ships and on railway trains, supervising and coordinating the work of employees engaged in providing services to diners.

label: Waiter, Formal Service
description: Serves food and beverages to guests in hotels, restaurants and clubs, working in a formal setting and paying special attention to established rules of service.

label: Wine Waiter
description: Advises on the selection of wines and serves them in commercially operated dining and drinking places and in clubs and institutions.

label: Bartender
description: Serves alcoholic and non-alcoholic drinks at a bar.

label: Other Waiters, Bartenders and Related Workers
description: This group includes waiters, bartenders and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who arrange tables and chairs; show customers to seats; present hors-d'oevres and deserts to tables for selection by guests; remove used linen and dishes from tables; wash and dry glasses and clean bars.

label: Domestic servant, general
description: Cleans rooms, prepares food and serves meals, washes dishes and performs additional domestic duties in private households (5-40.20). May also attend to employer=s personal needs (5-40.30), take care of children (5-40.35), or provide companionship for employer (5-40.40).

label: House servant
description: Cleans rooms, prepares food and serves meals, washes dishes and performs additional domestic duties in private households.  Workers who perform cleaning and related duties only are classified as Charworker (5-52.20). Workers who clean and service guest room in public establishments are classified as Chambermaid (5-40.50).

label: Personal Maid, Valet
description: Attends to employer's personal needs and keeps wardrobe and personal effects in good order, performing a variety of services.

label: Nursemaid
description: Takes care of children and oversees their daily activities.

label: Companion
description: Provides companionship and various other services for employer.

label: Chambermaid and Room Attendant
description: Cleans and services guest rooms in hotels and other lodging establishments. May clean and service public rooms, or rooms in private premises.

label: Hotel Concierge
description: Performs a variety of tasks for guests in hotels and similar establishments, especially at arrival and departure.

label: Ship's Steward
description: Takes care of general needs and comfort of ship's passengers. May perform some or all of the following tasks: serving meals and drinks; servicing cabins; arranging deck furniture and facilities; running errands; delivering messages.

label: Other Maids and Related Housekeeping Service Workers
description: This group includes other maids and related housekeeping service workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who assist in attending children in schools and institutions; take care of needs and comfort of train and bus passengers; render valet and other services to guests and clients of a hotel or other establishments.

label: Building Caretaker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 5-51.

label: Concierge (Apartment House)
description: Attends to the operation of an apartment house as representative of the owner or managing agent.

label: Concierge (Apartment House) or Janitor
description: May perform the occupational activities of a concierge (5-51.20) and/or the activities of a janitor (5-51.30).

label: Janitor
description: Keeps apartment house, hotel, office building or similar building in clean and orderly condition and operates furnaces and boilers to provide heat and hot water for tenants.

label: Verger
description: Takes care of interior and furnishings of a church.

label: Other Building Caretakers
description: This group includes building caretakers not elsewhere classified, for example those who take care of important monuments and historical buildings and of establishments such as clubs, institutes and dance halls.

label: Charworker
description: Cleans and keeps in orderly condition the interiors of public buildings, offices, commercial establishments, and apartment and private houses.

label: Window Cleaner
description: Cleans windows in buildings.

label: Chimney Sweep
description: Removes soot from flues, chimneys and connecting pipes.

label: Other Charworkers, Cleaners and Related Workers
description: This group includes charworkers, cleaners and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform routine tidying-up and lifting duties required in hotel housekeeping; clean walls and ceilings with sponge and soapy water or chemical solution; sweep house yards and other appurtenances; clean railway passenger coaches, buses, trams and aircraft. Cleaners of buildings by sandblasting or steam are classified in unit group 9-59.

label: Launderer, General
description: Performs duties such as washing, drying and ironing clothing, textile fabrics and similar articles in a laundry or in private house.

label: Laundering Machine-Operator
description: Operates mechanical equipment to wash clothing, textile fabrics and similar articles.

label: Dry-Cleaning Machine-Operator
description: Operates mechanical equipment to dry-clean, with a chemical solution, clothing, textile fabrics and similar articles.

label: Dry-Cleaner (Hand)
description: Cleans, by hand and with a chemical solution, clothing, textile fabrics, leather goods and similar articles.

label: Spotter (Dry-Cleaner)
description: Removes, with chemical solution or substance, spots and stains from clothing, textile furnishings, leather goods and similar articles.

label: Laundry Pressing Machine-Operator
description: Smooths and shapes clothing, textile furnishings and similar articles by means of a pressing machine.

label: Presser (Hand or Machine)
description: Smooths and shapes clothing, textile fabrics and similar articles by means of a pressing machine (5-60.60) or by hand (5-60.70).

label: Presser (Hand)
description: Smooths and shapes clothing, textile fabrics and similar articles by pressing with heated flat-iron.

label: Wardrobe Mistress (Stage and Studio)
description: Cares for costumes of members of theatrical, television or motion picture production cast.

label: Other Launderers, Dry-Cleaners and Pressers
description: This group includes launderers, dry-cleaners and pressers not elsewhere classified, for example those who mark for identification articles received for treatment; sort articles according to type and colour of material and fastness of dye; wash delicate or excessively stained articles with a starch solution; press articles with a mangle; clean carpets with a soap or chemical solution.

label: Women's Hairdresser
description: Cuts, washes, tints and waves hair and performs other personal services incidental to women's hairdressing.

label: Women's or Men's Hairdresser
description: May perform the occupational activities of a women=s hairdresser (5-70.20) and/or a men=s hairdresser (5-70.30).

label: Barber Hairdresser
description: Cuts hair, shaves and trims beards and performs other personal services incidental to barbering.

label: Beautician
description: Gives various forms of beauty treatment to customers.

label: Manicurist
description: Cleans, shapes and polishes finger and toe nails.

label: Make-Up Man (Stage and Studio)
description: Applies make-up to faces of actors and other performers to improve or alter their appearance for studio or stage production.

label: Bath Attendant
description: Attends to clients taking baths and may administer elementary massage.

label: Other Barbers, Hairdressers, Beauticians and Related Workers
description: This group includes barbers, hairdressers, beauticians and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who suggest hair styles most becoming to individual customers; wash and rinse hair; fit wigs according to customers' requirements.

label: Fire-Fighter
description: Fights fires as a member of a public fire-fighting force, and rescues people and property.

label: Fire Prevention Specialist
description: Detects and eliminates or reduces fire hazards in industrial plants and other establishments.

label: Fire-Salvage Specialist
description: Protects and salvages goods during and after fires.

label: Aircraft Accident Fire-Fighter
description: Prevents or extinguishes fires in crashed or damaged aircraft and rescues crew and passengers.

label: Policeman and other Maintainers of Law and Order (except Military)
description: Maintains law and order, protects persons and property from hazards and unlawful acts and arrests persons for contraventions of the law.

label: Military Policeman
description: Maintains law and order within the military and arrests service personnel who contravene military law.

label: Detective
description: Uncovers facts concerned with the prevention and solution of crimes and arrests persons for the contravention of the law.

label: Private Police Guard
description: Polices property or parts of establishments, such as industrial plants, banks or museums to prevent theft, violence, infractions of rules or other irregularities, and may make arrests.

label: Military, Specialisation Unknown
description: Workers in this unit group serve in the armed forces as officers (5-83.20), non-commissioned officers (5-83.30) or other ranks (5-83.40).

label: Officer
description: Formulates and implements military strategy. Commands and leads other service personnel.

label: Non-Commissioned Officer
description: Directs and trains other military ranks (5-83.40) under the supervision of officers (5-83.20).

label: Other Military Ranks
description: Performs military service as directed by commissioned and non-commissioned officers.

label: Private Inquiry Agent
description: Conducts private investigations for commercial or other establishments or for individuals.

label: Prison Guard
description: Watches inmates of gaol, reformatory or penitentiary, sees to their needs and maintains discipline.

label: Watchman
description: Guards industrial plant, warehouse or other property against fire, theft and illegal entry. May carry out other duties, such as sweeping floors. Private police guard is classified in 5-82.40.

label: Other Protective Service Workers
description: This group includes other protective service workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who keep watch in a central installation equipped to receive automatic alarm; maintain order in courtrooms; patrol beaches and swimming pools to prevent accidents and to rescue bathers from drowning; perform various underwater tasks generally connected with salvage work or recovering dead bodies.

label: Guide, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any of the occupational activities described in 5-91.20 and 5-91.30.

label: Travel Guide
description: Escorts groups of tourists travelling by motor bus, ship or other means of transportation over pre-planned route.

label: Sightseeing Guide
description: Escorts groups of tourists and others on sightseeing tours within a city, or to places of historical or general interest.

label: Undertaker
description: Makes arrangements for and conducts funerals.

label: Embalmer
description: Embalms bodies of human beings to retard or arrest the process of decay.

label: Other Undertakers and Embalmers
description: This group includes undertakers and embalmers not elsewhere classified, for example those who assist with various duties in connection with funeral arrangements such as preparing corpse for burial; embalm bodies for use in dissecting rooms of medical colleges.

label: Bookmaker (Sport)
description: Determines odds and receives and pays off bets on results of sporting events.

label: Croupier
description: Conducts games of chance in gambling establishments:

label: Nursing Aid
description: Performs simple tasks to assist nursing personnel, physicians or dentists in a consulting room, clinic, hospital or other institution providing medical or dental care.

label: Practical Aid (Pharmacy)
description: Performs non-technical tasks in a pharmacy, under the direction of a pharmacist.

label: Practical Aid (Veterinary)
description: Performs simple tasks to assist a veterinarian in an animal clinic or other veterinary establishment for the treatment and care of animals.

label: Aircraft Cabin Attendant
description: Attends to personal needs, the comfort and safety of aircraft passengers.

label: Prostitute
description: Performs various sexual services for payment, including, but not necessarily, sexual intercourse.

label: Other Service Workers Not Elsewhere Classified
description: This group includes service workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who assist persons at doors of shops, hotels and other establishments; carry hotel guests baggage and run errands for them; take charge of hats and coats in public places; operate passenger lifts; receive patrons at places of entertainment, sporting and other events and conduct them to their seats; cleans and services lavatories and rest rooms; receive check and maintain stock of alcoholic and other beverages in good condition in cellar of licensed establishment; serve as escorts to men and women; dance with partners for a prescribed fee; act as hostesses in bars and other places; pose for paintings, sculptures and other types of art; assist players of games by performing non-playing activities such as carrying golf clubs, setting up pins (skittles) and retrieving balls; paste advertising posters and notices on walls and billboards; exterminate vermin; operate roundabouts and other fairground equipment; collect, care for and feed lost or strayed dogs and other animals.

label: General Farmer
description: Conducts a farm on own behalf, or in partnership, to produce a variety of agricultural and animal husbandry products.

label: Small Subsistence Farmer (Husbandman)
description: Farms a small plot of land to produce a variety of agricultural and animal hubandry primarily for self- or family consumption.

label: Field Crop Farmer
description: Conducts a farm on own behalf, or in partnership, to grow field crops.

label: Orchard and Related Tree and Shrub Crop Farmer
description: Conducts a farm on own behalf, or in partnership, to cultivate trees or shrubs for production of their fruits, leaves or saps. May process these products to make fruit pulp or juice, cider, vinegar, dried fruits or other derived products.

label: Vine Grower
description: Conducts a farm on own behalf, or in partnership, for production of grapes. May process grapes into wine.

label: Livestock Farmer
description: Conducts a farm on own behalf, or in partnership, to breed and raise livestock.

label: Dairy Farmer
description: Conducts a farm on own behalf, or in partnership, primarily for production of milk.

label: Poultry Farmer
description: Conducts a farm on own behalf, or in partnership, to breed and raise poultry for eggs or meat.

label: Horticultural Farmer
description: Conducts a nursery or market garden on own behalf, or in partnership, to propagate trees, shrubs, flowers and other plants or to grow vegetables by intensive cultivation techniques:

label: Other Specialised Farmers
description: This group includes specialised farmers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in growing mushrooms, reeds or spices; or breeding and raising game or pet birds, frogs, snakes, tortoises, alligators, worms, silkworms or bees.

label: Farm Worker, General
description: Performs a variety of tasks in growing crops and breeding and raising livestock.

label: Farm-Helper, General
description: Assists generally on farm, performing a variety of simple farming tasks.

label: Farm Servant
description: Performs a variety of tasks on and around the farm, living as part of the farming household. May concentrate primarily on farming or domestic work.

label: Field Crop Farm Worker
description: Performs, by hand or machine, a variety of tasks in the propagation, cultivation and harvesting of field crops, under the supervision of the farm supervisor.

label: Vegetable Farm Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the growing of vegetables as field crops.

label: Wheat Farm Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the growing of wheat crops.

label: Cotton Farm Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the planting, cultivating and harvesting of cotton.

label: Rice Farm Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the planting, cultivating and harvesting of rice.

label: Sugar-Cane Farm Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the planting, cultivating and harvesting of sugar cane.

label: Other Field Crop and Vegetable Farm Workers
description: This group includes field crop farm workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in planting, cultivating and harvesting a particular field crop (other than vegetables, wheat, cotton, rice and sugar cane) such as barley, rye, colza, sisal, groundnuts, tobacco, flax or jute; and those occupied mainly in harvesting of field crops.

label: Orchard Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the planting and cultivating of fruit and nut trees and the harvesting of their fruits.

label: Vineyard Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the planting and cultivating of grape-vines and the harvesting of grapes.

label: Tea Plantation Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the propagation and cultivation of tea bushes.

label: Rubber Plantation Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the propagation, cultivation and tapping of rubber trees.

label: Other Orchard, Vineyard and Related Tree and Shrub Crop Workers
description: This group includes orchard, vineyard and related tree and shrub crop workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in planting, cultivating and harvesting coffee, cocoa or berries; pruning, budding and grafting fruit trees; harvesting orchard, vineyard and related tree and shrub crops; or tapping rubber trees and collecting the latex.

label: Livestock Worker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational tasks described in unit group 6-24.

label: Livestock Worker, General
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the breeding and raising of two or more species of livestock.

label: Beef Cattle Farm Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the breeding and raising of beef cattle.

label: Sheep Farm Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the breeding and raising of sheep for meat or wool.

label: Pig Farm Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the breeding and raising of pigs.

label: Fur-Bearing Animal Farm Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the breeding and raising of fur-bearing animals for their pelts.

label: Horse Worker
description: Performs one or more of a variety of tasks in the breeding, raising and care of horses.

label: Other Livestock Workers
description: This group includes livestock workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in breeding and raising a particular type of livestock (other than beef cattle, sheep, pigs and fur-bearing animals) such as horses, goats, ostriches, reindeer, llamas, dogs or cats; and those mainly occupied in breeding cattle by artificial insemination, shearing wool from sheep, removing horns from cattle, caring for animals at industrial sites or in livery stables, training and caring for racehorses or race dogs, caring for animals in zoos or menageries, breeding and raising rats, guinea pigs or other animals required by research workers for experimental purposes, and caring for pet animals during absence of owners.

label: Dairy Farm Worker, General
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the breeding, raising and milking of dairy cattle.

label: Milker (Machine)
description: Milks dairy cows by machine.

label: Other Dairy Farm Workers
description: This group includes dairy farm workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialize in raising goats or other animals (except cows) for milk.

label: Poultry Farm Worker, General
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the breeding, raising and tending of poultry.

label: Poultry Hatchery Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the hatching of eggs for commercial purposes.

label: Other Poultry Farm Workers
description: This group includes poultry farm workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in trimming and searing beaks, claws and wings of chicks; collecting semen and artificially inseminating hens; determining the sex of chicks; or minding flocks of turkeys or geese.

label: Nursery and Garden Workers unspecified
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 6-27.

label: Market Garden Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the growing of vegetables by intensive cultivation techniques.

label: Nursery Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the propagation and cultivation of trees, shrubs, flowers and other plants, and the production of bulbs and seeds, for sale.

label: Gardener
description: Cultivates flowers, trees, shrubs and other plants in parks or public or private gardens.

label: Other Nursery Workers and Gardeners
description: This group includes nursery workers and gardeners not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in growing tropical and other plants for exhibition or medicinal purposes; growing plants and shrubs to develop new varieties and colours; or growing plants required by research workers for experimental purposes.

label: Motorised Farm Equipment Operator
description: Operates and services one or more types of motorised farm machinery or equipment.

label: Other Farm Machinery Operators
description: This group includes farm machinery operators not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in operating and servicing one or more types of farm machinery drawn or powered by animals.

label: Apiary Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the establishment and care of beehives and the extraction of honey.

label: Sericulture Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the breeding and raising of silkworms.

label: Tree Tapper (except Rubber)
description: Makes cuts in trunks of certain kinds of trees and gathers exuded gums, resins, or other saps.

label: Irrigator
description: Performs a variety of tasks in irrigating agricultural land.

label: Groundsman
description: Maintains golf courses, race-tracks, cricket, baseball and football fields, tennis courts, and other sports, recreation and park grounds.

label: Peat Worker
description: Extracts peat from uplands and bogs using a shovel. May lay out stods for drying and storage and prepare them for transportation.

label: Other Agricultural and Animal Husbandry Workers
description: This group includes agricultural and animal husbandry workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who mainly perform tasks in breeding and raising frogs, snails, snakes or worms; breeding and raising birds for zoos or for sale as pets; growing mushrooms or spices; or gathering roots, herbs, reeds, osier and other natural forest products.

label: Logger (General)
description: Fells trees, saws them into logs and performs other logging tasks.

label: Tree Feller and Bucker
description: Fells trees and saws them into logs, using axe and manual or powered saw, for timber or fire wood.

label: High-Climber (Logging)
description: Trims and tops anchor trees selected for log hauling operations.

label: River Driver
description: Launches logs into river and guides them downstream to mill or into rafts or booms for further transport.

label: Other Loggers
description: This group includes loggers not elsewhere classified, for example those who are occupied mainly in operating wood-harvesting machines to fell, branch, cross-cut or bark trees to perform other logging operations; loading logs into chutes, or stacking them preparatory to transport out of forest; shaping rough wooden products from logs, such as railway ties and telephone poles, near felling sites; examining logs and grading them according to quality or measuring them to determine their volume of marketable timber.

label: Forest Supervisor
description: Directly supervises and co-ordinates tree cultivation, conservation and harvesting operations and enforces safety and preservation regulations in forest.

label: Forestry Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the establishing and care of forest stands under the direction of the forest supervisor.

label: Timber Cruiser
description: Locates and estimates volume of marketable standing timber in a forest by examining and measuring samples of the trees.

label: Forest Fire-Fighter
description: Patrols or keeps watch to detect forest fires and participates in fire-fighting operations.

label: Other Forestry Workers
description: This group includes forestry workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who are occupied mainly in selecting and marking trees for felling; patrolling a forest to enforce conservation regulations; digging holes and planting tree seedlings; pruning and trimming trees to promote upward growth; removing dead and diseased trees and unwanted species; thinning out dense stands of young trees; clearing undergrowth in forest stands; or stripping bark from cork trees.

label: Fisherman, Deep-Sea or Inland and Coastal Water
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the catching, storing and unloading of fish caught in deep sea (6-41.20) or inland and coastal water (6-41.30).

label: Deep-Sea Fisherman
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the catching, storing and unloading of fish caught in deep sea, usually working as fishing vessel crew member.

label: Inland and Coastal Water Fisherman
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the catching of fish in inland or coastal waters.

label: Fish Farm Worker
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the breeding and raising of fish.

label: Oyster Farm Worker
description: Cultivates oysters in specially prepared sea-water beds.

label: Whale Hunter
description: Works as member of whaler crew performing a variety of tasks in catching whales, cutting them up and processing them at sea.

label: Whale or Seal Hunter
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the catching and processing of whales (6-49.40) or seal (6-49.50).

label: Seal Hunter
description: Performs a variety of tasks in the catching, killing and skinning of seals for their pelts.

label: Trapper and Hunter
description: Traps and hunts wild animals, wild fowl and other game (except seals) for skins, meat, sale alive or to exterminate them as pests.

label: Other Fishermen, Hunters and Related Workers
description: This group includes fishermen, hunters and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in diving to sea bed to gather sponges and harvest pearl oysters; cultivating pearls in oysters; gather sea weed, sea mosses, turtles' eggs, and clams and other molluscs; catching tropical and other fish and sea creatures for aquariums and museums; assisting hunters by building and camouflaging traps and beating to flush game; and protecting and caring for wild animals and birds in game preserves and wild-life sanctuaries.

label: Miner, General
description: Extracts coal or other minerals, such as iron, copper, tin, lead, antimony, jet, gold, silver from underground or surface mines.

label: Quarryman, General
description: Extracts granite, limestone, marble, sandstone, grift or other kinds of stone from quarry.

label: Cutting-Machine Operator (Mine)
description: Sets and operates machine which cuts channels in mine workface.

label: Mining-Machine Operator, Specialisation Unknown
description: Sets and operates machine which cuts channels in mine workface (7-11.20), machine which drills holes into mine or quarry workface (7-11.30), or continuous-mining machine (7-11.40).

label: Drilling-Machine Operator (Mine and Quarry)
description: Sets and operates machine which drills holes into mine or quarry workface for blasting.

label: Continuous Mining-Machine Operator
description: Operates self-propelled continuous-mining machine to mine coal underground.

label: Shot-Firer (Mine and Quarry)
description: Determines positions and force of explosions required, and charges and sets off explosives to dislodge coal, ore, rock or other solid mineral from mine or quarry workface.

label: Underground Timberman
description: Cuts, fits and installs wood or steel props, pillars and arches to support walls and roofs of mines and other underground workings.

label: Sampler (Mine)
description: Collects small amounts of coal or ore from specified locations in mine for laboratory analysis.

label: Other Miners and Quarrymen
description: This group includes miners and quarrymen not elsewhere classified, for example those who remove wood and steel supports from disused workings; direct high-pressure streams of water against gravel banks to force gravel into sluices from which metalliferous minerals are recovered; cut stone from quarry faces with power driven saws; split sample cores for mineral-bearing rock strata removed from diamond core drills for laboratory analysis; or extract chalk, clay, gravel or sand from open pits.

label: Mineral and Stone Treaters, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-12.

label: Stone Splitter
description: Drills holes and drives wedges into quarried stone to break it into slabs or blocks.

label: Mineral-Crushing-Machine Operator
description: Operates machine which crushes and breaks lumps of mineral (except chemicals) to required size.

label: Mineral-Milling-Machine Operator
description: Operates ball mill that pulverises stone mineral-bearing ores or coal for further processing.

label: Jig Tender
description: Operates battery of jigs which separate mineral from gangue.

label: Floatation Man
description: Operates floatation machine which separates mineral from gangue.

label: Precipitator
description: Tends equipment which precipitates gold or silver from cyanide solution onto zinc.

label: Cone Operator (Mine)
description: Tends gravity device (cone) to separate slate and rock from coal.

label: Other Mineral and Stone Treaters
description: This group includes mineral treaters not elsewhere classified, for example those operating equipment to dissolve gold and silver in cyanide solution to separate it from gangue; removing impurities from minerals by means of running water; operating vibrating and oscillating screens or tables to size or separate minerals; tending machines that compress finely ground minerals or coal into briquettes or pellets; and operating machines which separate minerals by magnetism.

label: Well Drillers, Borers and Related Workers, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-13.

label: Derrickman (Oil and Gas Wells)
description: Sets up and operates derrick equipment and pumps to circulate mud through drill hole.

label: Rotary Driller (Oil and Gas Wells)
description: Operates rotary drilling plant to drill oil or gas wells.

label: Cable Driller (Oil and Gas Wells)
description: Operates cable (percussion) drilling plant to drill oil or gas wells.
