label: Cementer (Oil and Gas Wells)
description: Cements openings in walls or casings of oil or gas wells.

label: Well-Puller (Oil and Gas Wells)
description: Cleans and services oil and gas wells and repairs and replaces pumping rods, casings and tubings.

label: Acidiser (Oil and Gas Wells)
description: Treats oil and gas wells with acid to increase their production.

label: Well-Driller and Borer (except Oil and Gas Wells)
description: Sets up and operates drilling plant to drill wells or bores other than for oil or gas.

label: Other Well-Drillers, Borers and Related Workers
description: This group includes well-drillers, borers and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in operating plant to prepare drilling fluid by mixing clay, sand and water to specified viscosity and pumping it into a borehole; using special test equipment to determine productivity of strata; or starting or renewing flow of oil or gas from well by means of explosives.

label: Metal Processor, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in minor group 7-2.

label: Metal Smelting, Converting and Refining Furnacemen, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-21.

label: Blast Furnaceman (Ore Smelting)
description: Controls the operation of a blast furnace to smelt ores for the production of ferrous metal.

label: Open-Hearth Furnaceman (Steel)
description: Operates an open-hearth furnace in which scrap-metal and pig-iron are melted and refined to produce steel.

label: Oxygen Furnaceman (Steel Converting)
description: Operates oxygen furnace and auxiliary equipment to convert pig-iron into steel.

label: Bessemer Furnaceman (Steel Converting)
description: Operates a steel converter in which molten pig-iron is converted into steel.

label: Electric Arc Furnaceman (Steel Refining)
description: Operates an electric-arc furnace in which high-alloy steel is produced by melting and refining scrap steel.

label: Furnaceman, Non-Ferrous Metal Converting and Refining
description: Operates crucible, electric, open-hearth, reverberatory or other furnace for converting or refining non-ferrous metals.

label: Other Metal Smelting, Converting and Refining Furnaceman
description: This group includes metal smelting, converting and refining furnacemen not elsewhere classified, for example those who are mainly engaged in making malleable iron in a pudding furnace, or performing one or more specialised tasks in the operation of a furnace, such as charging, operating blast- and heat-regulating systems, tapping, and pouring molten metal into ladles.

label: Metal Rolling-Mill Workers, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-22.

label: Hot-Roller (Steel)
description: Operates rolling mill to shape hot steel ingots into blooms, slabs, billets or sheet bars for further processing, or to shape heated semi-finished steel pieces into bars, angles, ties, rails, sheets or other finished forms.

label: Continuous-Mill Roller (Steel)
description: Operates continuous mill in which hot steel slabs are passed through a series of rolling (stands) to produce finished plates or sheets in one continuous operation.

label: Cold-Roller (Steel)
description: Operates rolling mill to reduce cold steel strip or sheet to required gauge and impart desired surface finish.

label: Roller, Non-Ferrous Metals
description: Operates rolling mill to reduce or form hot or cold non-ferrous metal into plate, sheet, foil, wire or rod of specified dimensions.

label: Seamless Pipe and Tube Roller
description: Operates rolls to form seamless pipes and tubes from billets which have been pierced longitudinally.

label: Manipulator (Rolling Mill)
description: Manipulates controls of a rolling mill according to signals from roller to position ingots or blooms for entry into roll of mill.

label: Other Metal Rolling-Mill Workers
description: This group includes metal rolling-mill operators not elsewhere classified, for example those who assist in rolling operations by guiding and turning metal on conveyors or tables to, from, and through rolls of rolling machine.

label: Furnaceman, Metal-Melting, except Cupola
description: Operates furnace (except cupola) to melt ferrous metal prior to casting or further processing, and performs related tasks.

label: Cupola Furnaceman
description: Operates a cupola furnace to melt ferrous metal prior to casting or further processing, and performs related tasks.

label: Furnaceman, Metal Reheating
description: Operates furnace to reheat bars, plates and other stock metal forms prior to forging, power-pressing, rolling or other further processing.

label: Other Metal Melters and Reheaters
description: This group includes metal melters and reheaters not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in the production of ferrous or non-ferrous alloys by melting and mixing metals in prescribed percentages; or mainly performing one or more specialised tasks in the operation of a furnace, such as charging, operating blast- and heat regulating systems, tapping, and pouring molten metal into ladles.

label: Metal Pourer
description: Pours molten metal from ladle into moulds to produce metal castings.

label: Centrifugal Casting-Machine Operator
description: Operates centrifugal casting machine to cast pipes, brakedrums, bushings and other cylindrical metal products.

label: Die-Casting-Machine Operator
description: Operates die-casting machine to make castings from non-ferrous metals.

label: Continuous Rod-Casting-Machine-Operator (Non-Ferrous Metal)
description: Sets up and operates continuous casting machine to produce tubes and rods from non-ferrous metal.

label: Other Metal Caster
description: This group includes metal casters not elsewhere classified, for example those casting jewellery, dental forms or other non-ferrous metal products by hand; casting metal moulds for use in the manufacture of jewellery and other articles.

label: Metal Moulder or Coremaker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-25.

label: Bench Moulder (Metal)
description: Makes sand moulds by hand on a bench for small metal castings.

label: Floor and Pit Moulder
description: Makes sand moulds on foundry floor or in pit for large metal castings.

label: Moulder (Machine)
description: Makes sand moulds for metal castings using auxiliary machines.

label: Coremaker (Hand)
description: Makes sand cores by hand for use in metal moulds.

label: Coremaker (Hand or Machine)
description: Makes sand cores by hand (7-25.50) or machine (7-25.60) for use in metal moulds.

label: Coremaker (Machine)
description: Tends turn-over draw-type machine that makes sand cores for use in casting metal.

label: Other Metal Moulders and Core Makers
description: This group includes metal moulders and core makers not elsewhere classified, for example those who verify dimensions and shapes of cores for conformance to specifications; tend core making machines that extrude sand cores having uniform cross section; tend blower-type core making machines to produce sand cores; make clay cores around which ferrous and non-ferrous pipe is cast; those who work as part of a team engaged in the large-scale production of moulds or cores and perform, by hand or machine, only one of the operations involved.

label: Annealer
description: Heats metal objects in furnace and cools them at predetermined rate to relieve internal stresses, restore ductility and refine grain structure.

label: Hardener
description: Hardens steel objects throughout by heating in furnace and quenching them.

label: Case-Hardener
description: Imparts hard skin and tough, ductile core to steel objects by treating them with chemicals, heating and quenching or cooling them.

label: Temperer
description: Reheats hardened steel objects in furnace and quenches them to relieve stresses caused in hardening process and impart toughness.

label: Other Metal Annealers, Temperers and Case-Hardeners
description: This group includes metal annealers, temperers and case hardeners not elsewhere classified, for example those who assist heat treaters by loading furnaces, packing metal objects in chemicals, preparing quenching media, and quenching metal objects.

label: Wire Drawer (Hand)
description: Makes wire of specified diameter by hand on a draw bench.

label: Wire Drawer (Hand or Machine)
description: Makes wire of specified diameter by hand (7-27.20) or machine (7-27.30).

label: Wire Drawer (Machine)
description: Sets and operates machine to make wire of specified diameter.

label: Seamless Pipe and Tube Drawer
description: Sets and operates machine to draw seamless ferrous and non-ferrous tubing of specified diameter.

label: Extruder Operator (Metal)
description: Sets and operates hydraulic extrusion press to make rods, bars and seamless tubing.

label: Other Metal Drawers and Extruders
description: This group includes metal drawers and extruders not elsewhere classified, for example those who assist in the operation of a hydraulic extrusion press by feeding billets to press and positioning upsetting and cut-off devices.

label: Electroplater
description: Sets and controls equipment to coat metal articles with non-ferrous metal by electrolysis.

label: Hot-Dip Plater
description: Operates hot-dip equipment to coat iron and steel products with corrosion-resistant non-ferrous metal.

label: Wire-Coating-Machine Operator
description: Coats wire with non-ferrous metal by automatic machine.

label: Metal Sprayer
description: Sets and operates equipment to spray molten metal on metal products to provide protective or decorative coating or to build up worn or damaged surfaces.

label: Other Metal Platers and Coaters
description: This group includes metal platers and coaters not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in coating, colouring or oxidising surfaces of metal articles by dipping them in acid, gilding, staining or hot chemical solutions; treating aluminium or aluminium alloy articles electrically to produce an oxidised finish (anodising); coating iron or steel products with zinc by heating them in closed boxes containing a powdered zinc compound (sherardising).

label: Metal Bluer
description: Impart blue, rust-resistant, decorative finish to metal articles by treating them with chemicals and heating them.

label: Casting Finisher
description: Semi-finishes the surfaces of cast metal articles by hand and machine.

label: Metal Cleaner
description: Operates equipment to clean metal articles in preparation for electroplating, galvanising, enamelling or similar finishing processes. May operate ultrasonic metal-cleaning equipment and be designated accordingly.

label: Other Metal Processors
description: This group includes other metal processors not elsewhere classified.

label: Wood Treater, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-31.

label: Wood-Seasoning Worker
description: Operates steam-heated kiln to season wood.

label: Wood-Treating Worker
description: Treats wood with chemicals to protect it against decay or parasites.

label: Other Wood Treaters
description: This group includes wood treaters not elsewhere classified, for example those who are mainly engaged in operating incising machines to perforate wood and facilitate penetration of preservatives; or impregnating wood products with fireproofing chemicals.

label: Sawyer, Plywood Maker or Related Wood-Processing Worker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-32.

label: Sawyer, General
description: Sets and operates one or more different kinds of sawing machines or uses hand tools to cut or trim lumber and wood to specified dimensions on a repetitive basis. May work in a sawmill, a workshop, or outside in forests.

label: Edge Sawyer
description: Sets and operates a multiple-blade sawing machine to cut uneven edges of rough boards straight and square.

label: Band-Saw Operator
description: Sets and operates band-saw machine to saw logs into planks or boards.

label: Veneer Cutter
description: Sets and operates rotary lathe, slicer or other woodworking machine to peel or slice veneer from logs.

label: Plywood Core-Laying-Machine Operator
description: Operates machine to lay face and core veneer sheets in sequence and spread glue on core sheets to form plywood panels.

label: Plywood Press-Operator
description: Operates hot-plate press to bond glue-coated veneer sheets together to form plywood.

label: Wood Grader
description: Examines dressed or rough-sawn wood and sorts it according to quality and size.

label: Other Sawyer, Plywood Makers and Related Wood-Processing Workers
description: This group includes sawyers, plywood makers and related wood-processing workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who are mainly occupied in peeling bark from logs preparatory to sawing or veneer-cutting; operating power saws to cut logs into specified barrel stave lengths; operating banks of circular saws to cut out defective sections of boards (trimming); or operating edge-gluing machines to join veneer strips into sheets.

label: Wood Grinder
description: Operates power-driven machine to grind logs or wood blocks into fibre used in making paper pulp.

label: Chipperman
description: Operates chipper machine to reduce logs to chips for making pulp.

label: Digester Operator
description: Operates rotary or stationary boiler (digester) to produce pulp and to remove impurities from materials such as wood, rags, esparto, straw, or waste paper by chemical process in the manufacture of paper pulp.

label: Bleacher Operator
description: Operates machine that bleaches material, such as wood pulp, rags, esparto, straw or waste-paper pulp.

label: Beater Operator
description: Operates machine which mixes, beats and hydrates pulp and other ingredients to prepare stuff for making paper.

label: Other Paper Pulp Preparers
description: This group includes paper pulp prepares not classified elsewhere, for example those mainly occupied in operating machines which cut rags to size for cooking, bleaching or defibring prior to making pulp; screening pulp stock, pumped from digester, to separate coarse fibres from pulp; operating machines which eliminate surplus water and impurities from fibrous material prior to beating; operating machines which refine pulp by brushing out knots and shortening fibres.

label: Paper Maker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in 7-34.20 to 7-34.90.

label: Paper-Making-Machine Operator (Wet End)
description: Operates section of machine in which wet pulp is formed into paper.

label: Paper-Making-Machine Operator (Back End)
description: Operates section of paper-making machine in which paper is dried, calendered, wound, slit and rewound.

label: Supercalender Operator
description: Operates supercalender machine to impart gloss and finish to surface of paper.

label: Coating-Machine Operator
description: Operates machine to glaze or impregnate paper with coating mixture.

label: Paper Maker (Hand)
description: Makes, by hand, paper of high quality and durability for bank notes, documents, account books, drawings and other purposes.

label: Other Paper Makers
description: This group includes paper makers not elsewhere classified, for example those mainly occupied in making paper board or laminated or crepe paper; making imitation hand-made paper on a cylinder mould machine; making sizes of glue, starch, rosin and other materials for surface treatment of paper; operating machines that waterproof paper by coating it with was; coating paper by machine with an ink-wax carbon mixture to make carbon paper.

label: Crusher, Grinder or Mixer, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) occupational activities described in unit group 7-41.

label: Crusher Operator (Chemical and Related Processes)
description: Operates crushing machine in which solid lumps of chemicals or other materials used in chemical and related processes are reduced to size suitable for milling or other further processing.

label: Miller-Grinder (Chemical and Related Processes)
description: Operates mill to grind and pulverise solid chemicals or other materials used in chemical and related processes into particles of specified size.

label: Mixing-and Blending-Machine Operator (Chemical and Related Processes)
description: Operates machine in which solids or liquids used in chemical and related processes are mixed or blended according to formula to make chemical products.

label: Other Crushers, Grinders and Mixers
description: This group includes crushers, grinder and mixers not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate fantype grinding or beating machines in the treatment of asbestos fibres or operate special machines in which plastic resin is compounded or pelletised.

label: Cooker (Chemical and Related Processes)
description: Cooks materials such as bones, fats, molasses, oils, salts, acids and alkalis in open vats, boiling pans, kettles or similar containers to purify, mix or compound them, give them a special property or effect a chemical change in them.

label: Roaster, Chemical and Related Processes
description: Operates oven, rotary-kiln or similar device and auxiliary equipment, such as conveyer, feeders, and dust collectors, to calcine or otherwise effect a chemical change in materials.

label: Drier Operator (Chemical and Related Processes)
description: Operates driers that heat liquids or slurries to remove water or volatile liquid components.

label: Other Cookers, Roasters and Related Heat-Treaters
description: This group includes cookers, roasters and related heat-treaters not elsewhere classified, for example those who dry chemical solutions by a spraying or atomising process to produce powders; dry materials in drying rooms or in drying cabinets fitted with conveying equipment; or operate electrochemical furnaces to graphitise carbon electrodes.

label: Filter-Press Operator
description: Operates filter press to remove sediment, impurities and insoluble materials from liquid concentrations.

label: Rotary-Drum Filterer
description: Operates rotary-drum filter into which solutions are vacuum-drawn to remove sediment, impurities and insoluble material.

label: Centrifugal Separator Operator
description: Operates machine which separates solids from liquids, or liquids of different specific gravity from each other, by centrifugal force.

label: Crude Oil Treater (Oilfield)
description: Operates chemical, electrical or centrifugal equipment at oil well site to remove sediment and water from crude oil.

label: Other Filter and Separator Operators
description: This group includes filter and separator operators not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate other special filter and separator equipment to process specific kinds of chemical materials.

label: Still or Reactor Operator, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-44.

label: Batch-Still Operator (Chemical Processes, except Petroleum)
description: Operates one or more stills in which batches of crude liquid chemicals (other than petroleum) are treated to separate them into, or to refine, their chemical constituents.

label: Continuous-Still Operator (Chemical Processes, except Petroleum)
description: Operates one or more stills in which continuous feed of crude liquid chemical (other than petroleum) is separated into its chemical constituents or in which those constituents are refined.

label: Reactor-Converter Operator (Chemical Processes, except Petroleum)
description: Operates equipment (other than that used for treating petroleum) which performs a sequence of operations in a chemical reaction process: Workers who operate equipment performing only one operation in a reactor-converter process are classified according to the type of equipment operated.

label: Evaporator Operator
description: Operates evaporating tank, vacuum pan or similar device to concentrate solutions and suspensions by driving off excess water.

label: Extractor Operator (Wood Distillation)
description: Operates digester at tree-felling site to obtain crude turpentine from wood chips by steam distillation.

label: Saltmaker
description: Minds and services boiling pans containing brine, and draws or scoops out coarse and fine salt which is precipitated. May also do light and maintain fire under salt pans.

label: Other Still and Reactor Operators
description: This group includes still and reactor operators not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in refining crude wood turpentine; distilling resin into gum turpentine; distilling alcoholic beverages from prepares mixtures; distilling vegetable products with the aid of steam to obtain perfumes and aromatic substances of an oily nature; or assisting in operation of stills.

label: Petroleum-Refining Worker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-45.

label: Desulphurisation Treater (Petroleum Refining)
description: Operates plant in which petrol, paraffin, crude and distilled oils, wax and other petroleum products are treated to remove sulphur and other undesirable impurities.

label: Pumpman (Petroleum Refining)
description: Operates steam or electrically driven pumps to circulate crude, semi-processed and finished petroleum products, water and chemical solutions through processing, storage and shipping departments of refinery.

label: Stillman (Petroleum Refining)
description: Operates one or more stills in which petroleum is distilled to separate it into, or to refine, products such as petrol, paraffin, lubricating oil and fuel oil.

label: Controlman (Petroleum Refining)
description: Operates control panel to regulate temperature, pressure, rate of flow and tank level in petroleum refining, processing and treating units and petrochemical units.

label: Blender (Petroleum Refining)
description: Operates equipment to blend petrol with chemicals and other additives to produce commercial fuel.

label: Paraffin Plant Operator
description: Operates filter presses to separate oil of paraffin distillate from paraffin wax.

label: Other Petroleum-Refining Workers
description: This group includes petroleum-refining workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in blending asphalt for various uses with naphtha, kerosene and other petroleum products; operating equipment to produce liquefied gas.

label: Chemical Bleacher Operator
description: Treats chemical solutions with bleaching reagent to improve their colour.

label: Coke Burner
description: Operates special ovens to produce coke from coal.

label: Coal-Gas Maker
description: Operates one or more retorts in the production of gas from coal.

label: Charcoal Burner
description: Operates kiln to convert wood into charcoal by slow burning process.

label: Synthetic Fibre Maker
description: Tends machine or machine section that extrudes or forms natural or synthetic polymers into synthetic fibres such as rayon or nylon.

label: Chemical Processor (Radioactive Materials)
description: Controls chemical equipment to separate and extract uranium, plutonium and other radioactive materials from their ores, to concentrate radioactive materials and extract them from solution, and to recover unconsumed uranium from spent nuclear fuels.

label: Other Chemical Processors and Related Workers
description: This group includes chemical processors and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who tend electrolytic cells used in the production of chemicals; wash chemicals in the processing of chemical products; coat pills and tablets to make them palatable and to preserve their ingredients; oxidise lead to form red lead; treat lead with acid or heat to form white lead; prepare starches and glucose; treat rubber latex with chemicals to coagulate it; and treat latex with smoke.

label: Spinner, Weaver, Knitter, Dyer or Related Worker, Specialisation Unknown.
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in minor group 7-5

label: Fibre Preparers, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-51.

label: Fibre Grader and Classer
description: Grades and classifies natural textile fibres.

label: Wool Scourer
description: Washes greasy wool (raw wool fibres) preparatory to further processing.

label: Fibre Mixer and Blender
description: Tends machines which mix textile fibres into uniform blends.

label: Fibre Picker
description: Operates picker machines which clean and fluff textile fibres.

label: Fibre Carder
description: Operates carding machine which cleans fibres and transforms them from loosely matted layers (lap) into untwisted strand (sliver).

label: Fibre Lapper
description: Operates machine which combines slivers into one sliver lap, or sliver laps into one ribbon lap, preparatory to combing.

label: Fibre Comber
description: Operates machine which combs out short fibres, removes dirt and delivers long fibres in a sliver for first drawing (twisting).

label: Fibre Drawer
description: Operates drawing frame machine which combines several strands of sliver into one attenuated strand of regular quality and weight.

label: Fibre Rover
description: Operates roving frame machine which transforms sliver into roving.

label: Other Fibre Preparers
description: This group includes fibre prepares not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate machine for softening and beating flax, jute and hemp fibres or for washing raw stock fibres (other than wood).

label: Spinner, Thread and Yarn
description: Operates machines to spin thread and yarn from roving on to spindles or other output packages.

label: Doubler
description: Operates machine which winds two or more threads onto a bobbin without twisting them.

label: Twister
description: Operates machine which twists two or more strands of yarn or thread into a single heavier and stronger strand.

label: Winder
description: Operates machine which winds yarn or thread from one package to another to facilitate further processing or transportation.

label: Other Spinners and Winders
description: This group includes spinners and winders not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform auxiliary operations in spinning and winding.

label: Loom Fixer
description: Sets, inspects and repairs looms of various kinds.

label: Knitting-Machine Setter
description: Sets, adjusts and makes minor repairs to various types of knitting machines.

label: Jacquard Design Copyist
description: Reproduces in diagram form designer=s sketches for weaving by Jacquard loom.

label: Jacquard Card Cutter
description: Operates machine which punches holes in Jacquard cards.

label: Other Weaving- and Knitting-Machine Setters and Pattern-Card Preparers
description: This group includes weaving- and knitting-machine setters and p attern-card preparers not elsewhere classified, for example those who check and correct punched holes in pattern cards; operate machines which produce working copies of pattern cards from master set; place pattern cards together in proper sequence by hand or machine.

label: Weaver, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-54.

label: Beam Warper
description: Operates machine which winds yarn or thread from bobbins directly onto weaver's beam, or onto cylinder or reel and then onto beam.

label: Loom Threader (Hand)
description: Draws warp thread or yarn into loom by hand, in preparation for weaving of fabric.

label: Loom Threader (Hand or Machine)
description: Draws warp thread into loom by hand (7-54.20) or machine (7-54.25) in preparation for weaving.

label: Loom Threader (Machine)
description: Operates machine which draws warp threads into loom in preparation for weaving.

label: Cloth Weaver (Hand)
description: Weaves fabric on hand-operated loom.

label: Cloth Weaver (Hand or Machine)
description: Weaves cloth by hand (7-54.30) or machine (7-54.40).

label: Tapestry Maker (Hand)
description: Makes tapestry on hand-operated loom.

label: Cloth Weaver (Machine, except Jacquard Loom)
description: Operates and tends battery of looms to weave yarn into cloth.

label: Jacquard Weaver
description: Operates Jacquard loom to weave cloth of intricate designs.

label: Lace Weaver (Machine)
description: Operates lace-making machine.

label: Lace Weaver (Hand or Machine)
description: Makes lace by machine (7-54.50) or hand.

label: Carpet Weaver (Hand)
description: Weaves carpet on hand-operated loom.

label: Carpet Weaver (Hand or Machine)
description: Weaves carpet on hand-operated loom (7-54.55) or machine (7-54.60).

label: Carpet Weaver (Machine)
description: Operates loom on which carpets or rugs are woven.

label: Net Maker (Machine)
description: Tends loom on which yarn or twist is intersected and knotted at regular intervals to form mesh.

label: Fabrics Examiner
description: Examines textile fabrics for faults.

label: Fabrics Repairer
description: Repairs faults in textile fabrics.

label: Other Weavers and Related Workers
description: This group includes weavers and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform auxiliary operations in weaving processes.

label: Knitter, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-55.

label: Knitting Machine-Operator (Garment)
description: Operates one or more standard or specialised power-driven machines which knit garments, fabrics and other articles from yarn.

label: Knitting Machine Operator (Hosiery)
description: Operates knitting machines to knit hosiery to shape of foot and leg.

label: Hosiery knitter (Hand)
description: Knits hosiery by hand.

label: Knitter (Hand-Operated Machine)
description: Knits fabrics, garments and other articles from yarn on hand-operated machine.

label: Hand Knitter
description: Knits garments and other articles by hand from yarn according to specifications.

label: Other Knitters
description: This group includes other knitters not elsewhere classified, for example those performing auxiliary operations in knitting processes.

label: Bleacher, Dyer or Textile Product Finisher, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-56.

label: Textile Bleacher
description: Treats fibres, yarn, cloth or other textile goods to make them lighter in colour.

label: Yarn Dyer
description: Treats yarn with dyes to give it required colour.

label: Yarn, Fabric or Garment Dyer
description: Treats yarn (7-56.20), textile fabric (7-56.25) or garment (7-56.30) with dyes to give it required colour.

label: Fabric Dyer
description: Treats textile fabric with dyes to give it required colour.

label: Garment Dyer
description: Re-dyes garments to give them colour desired by customers.

label: Textile Washer
description: Treats yarn, cloth or finished goods to remove impurities or excess chemicals.

label: Silk Degummer
description: Treats silk yarn, cloth or piece goods to remove natural gum.

label: Wool-Carboniser
description: Controls equipment that treats scoured wool fibres, woollen fabric and rags to carbonize and remove cellulosic (vegetable) matter.

label: Textile Shrinker
description: Tends equipment to shrink woven material to required length and width.

label: Textile Fuller
description: Tends equipment to cause fibres of wool to interlock and strengthen the cloth for further processing.

label: Textile Waterproofer
description: Treats textiles with chemical to make them water resistant.

label: Silk Weighter
description: Treats silk with solutions of tin and phosphates to give it weight and body.

label: Textile Calender Operator
description: Operates machine in which textiles are pressed, stretched or given lustre or waterproof or other type of finish by means of friction, heating and rolling.

label: Other Bleachers, Dyers and Textile Product Finishers
description: This group includes bleachers, dyers and textile product finishers not elsewhere classified, for example those who dye unspun fibres, hosiery or knitwear; disentangle skeins of yarn after washing, bleaching, dyeing or other treatment; dry materials at any stage of treatment; remove fibre protrusions; stretch textile goods; press made-up goods; re-waterproof used goods; or size the warp.

label: Rope Maker, General
description: Makes ropes from natural and artificial fibres by hand or machine.

label: Wheel Turner, Rope Making
description: Uses a wheel to twist or braid together strands of fibre into rope.

label: Braid Maker (Hand)
description: Makes braid by hand.

label: Braid Maker (Hand or Machine)
description: Makes braid by hand (7-59.20) or machine (7-59.25).

label: Braid Maker (Machine)
description: Operates one or more machines that interweave threads into tubular cord or narrow band.

label: Crocheter (Hand)
description: Makes trimmings, articles and decorative fabrics with thread or yarn by means of a hooked needle (crochet hook).

label: Crocheter (Machine)
description: Operates machine which crochets trimmings on knitted garments and other knitted goods.

label: Net Maker (Hand)
description: Makes nets by hand.

label: Fur Fibre Mixer (Machine)
description: Operates machine that mixes and purifies fur fibres by blowing air onto them.

label: Felt Hood Former
description: Operates machine which makes hat forms from fur fibres or wool batts.

label: Other Spinners, Weavers, Knitters, Dyers and Related Workers
description: This group includes spinners, weavers, knitters, dyers and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who harden and shrink hat forms or make wool felt sheeting.

label: Tanner or Fellmonger, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-61.

label: Hide and Skin Grader
description: Sorts and grades hides and skins before or after processing. Pelt grader is classified in 7-62.20.

label: Fellmonger
description: Separates residual wool from sheepskins and preserves skins intended for further treatment.

label: Hide Flesher and Dehairer (Hand)
description: Removes flesh and traces of hair from hides with hand knife.

label: Hide Flesher and Dehairer (Machine)
description: Operates machine in which flesh and hair are removed from hides.

label: Hide Splitter
description: Operates a machine in which hides are split edgeways to form two or more pieces or to give uniform thickness, or cuts the same by hand.

label: Tanner
description: Treats hides or skins in solutions to convert them into leather.

label: Leather Currier
description: Dresses and finishes hides after tanning.

label: Leather Dyer and Stainer
description: Prepares colour solutions, dyes and stains and applies them to dressed leather.

label: Other Tanners and Fellmongers
description: This group includes tanners and fellmongers not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate an automatic machine for buffing or polishing leather with brushes or pads; or nails leather on boards or frames.

label: Pelt Dressers, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-62.

label: Pelt Grader
description: Sorts fur- or wool-bearing pelts before or after they have been dressed. Worker occupied in grading and matching furs in connection with fur tailoring are classified in 7-92.40.

label: Pelt Flesher
description: Removes particles of flesh and fat from fur- or wool- bearing pelts prior to curing or other processing: scrapes particles from pelt with knife or by working skin backwards and forwards over fixed steel blade.

label: Pelt Plucker and Trimmer
description: Removes long coarse hair from fur pelts and trims underlying hair to even length.

label: Pelt Dyer (Hand)
description: Applies dyes to fur pelts by hand.

label: Pelt Stretcher
description: Stretches, or smooths and stretches, the skins of dressed pelts.

label: Other Pelt Dressers
description: This group includes pelt dressers not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate machines which remove fur from pelts or skins in pickling, dyeing or other solutions.

label: Grain Miller
description: Operates machinery for processing grain (except rice) to produce flour, meal and animal feed.

label: Rice Miller
description: Operates machinery for processing rice.

label: Spice Miller
description: Grinds spices to specified consistency in a mill.

label: Other Grain Millers and Related Workers
description: This group includes grain millers and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate cleansing, washing and husking equipment to prepare grain and related foods for milling; operate equipment to sift and sort milled products at various stages in milling process; or supervise the storage and conservation of grain in silos.

label: Sugar Processor or Refiner, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-72.

label: Sugar-Cane Grinder
description: Operates equipment to extract juice from sugar-canes by crushing them in series of rollers.

label: Diffuser Operator (Beet Sugar)
description: Tends automatic machine which extracts sugar liquor from beets.

label: Carbonation Man (Sugar Refining)
description: Controls tanks in which impurities in sugar liquor are precipitated by carbonation process.

label: Crystalliser Operator (Sugar Refining)
description: Tends tank in which sugar crystals are produced from hot sugar liquor.

label: Continuous Sugar-Refining Machine Operator
description: Controls series of automatic machines which refine beet or cane sugar by a continuous process.

label: Other Sugar Processors and Refiners
description: This group includes sugar processors and refiners not elsewhere classified, for example those who extract and refine sugar juices from maple, palm and other vegetable sources; operate evaporating equipment to reduce sugar liquor to a specific density; operate equipment to separate sugar crystals from molasses.

label: Butcher, General
description: Slaughters animals, bones and cuts up carcasses and prepares standard meat cuts.

label: Slaughterer
description: Slaughters animals and flays, trims and reduces carcasses.

label: Meat Cutter
description: Cuts meat into portions suitable for sale to individual customers or for use in meat-processing plants.

label: Sausage Maker
description: Prepares ingredients for various kinds of sausages and similar products and operates machines for their manufacture:

label: Other Butchers and Meat Preparers
description: This group includes butchers and meat prepares not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in the productions of pork products or in the treatment and preparation of edible offal for use in meat-product making.

label: Preserving Cook, General
description: Cooks meat, fish, fruit, vegetables or other foods in large quantities preparatory to canning or preserving.

label: Fish-Preserving Cook
description: Cooks fish and other sea or freshwater foods in large quantities preparatory to canning or preserving.

label: Sterilising Cook
description: Operates pressure-cooker or other vessel to sterilise meat, fish, fruit, vegetables or jam prior to canning or bottling.

label: Foodstuffs Freezer
description: Freezes fruit, vegetables and other foods.

label: Foodstuffs Dehydrator
description: Operates drying units to remove moisture from fruit, vegetables and other food.

label: Pickler, Food
description: Cures meat, fish, other foods and food products.

label: Meat and Fish Smoker
description: Operates smoke chambers or ovens to smoke meat, fish and other foodstuffs.

label: Other Food Preservers
description: This group includes food preservers not elsewhere classified, for example those who prepare foods for canning; extract essence from foods by heat processes and make concentrates or powders; whiten or enrich natural colours of fruit or vegetables; or dry fish in the sun.

label: Dairy Product Processor, General
description: Performs one or more tasks in the preparation of various dairy products, setting up and operating equipment to process milk, cream, and other dairy products, following specified methods and formulae.

label: Dairy Product Pasteuriser
description: Operates pasteurising equipment to remove harmful bacteria from milk and other dairy products.

label: Butter Maker
description: Performs one or more tasks in butter making: pasteurises milk to eliminate harmful bacteria; separates cream from milk in centrifuge; adds lactic ferment to ripen cream; pours or pumps cream into mechanical churn; starts churn and controls moisture, temperature and churning time.

label: Cheese Maker
description: Performs one or more tasks in cheese making.

label: Ice-Cream Maker
description: Makes ice-cream from milk, sugar and other ingredients.

label: Other Dairy Product Processors
description: This group includes dairy product processors not elsewhere classified, for example those who salt cheeses by immersing them in brine or rubbing them with dry salt; operate machines which homogenise milk or mould butter or cheese into shape; make condensed or powdered milk; or make bacterial cultures used in butter, cheese and other dairy products making.

label: Baker, General
description: Makes bread, cake, biscuits, pastries, pies and other flour products.

label: Bread Baker
description: Makes all kinds of bread.

label: Pastry Maker
description: Makes tarts, cakes and other pastry products.

label: Macaroni Maker
description: Makes macaroni and similar wheat products.

label: Chocolate Maker
description: Operates grinding, pressing, mixing and other machines to make chocolate.

label: Confectionery Maker
description: Makes confectionery from mixture of sugar, chocolate and other ingredients.

label: Other Bakers, Pastry Cooks and Confectionery Makers
description: This group includes bakers, pastry cooks and confectionery makers not elsewhere classified, for example those who make biscuits and spiced bread; make chewing gum; make fondants, caramels and other sweets; enrobe fondants, caramels, nuts or other foods by hand or machine; operate automatic machines which mould chocolate, soft sweets or jellies; or use tempering machines to maintain correct temperature and grain of liquid chocolate.

label: Coffee and Tea Taster
description: Tastes brewed samples of coffee or tea.

label: Coffee Blender
description: Operates machine which mixes various grades of green coffee.

label: Tea Blender
description: Operates machine which mixes various grades of tea.

label: Coffee Roaster
description: Roasts blended coffee beans or chicory roots in heated revolving cylinders.

label: Cocoa-Bean Roaster
description: Roasts cocoa beans in heated revolving cylinders.

label: Other Tea, Coffee and Cocoa Preparers
description: This group includes tea, coffee and cocoa preparers not elsewhere classified, for example those who break outer coverings of cocoa beans and crush them into nibs; or grind cocoa and coffee.

label: Brewer, General
description: Mixes, presses, malts and ferments grains or fruits to make alcoholic or non-alchoholic beverages.

label: Germination Worker (Malting)
description: Germinates barley or other grain used in making distilled or malt liquors.

label: Kilnman (Malting)
description: Dries germinated grain used in preparing malt for making distilled and malt liquors.

label: Malt Cooker
description: Cooks malt in water to prepare mash used in making distilled or malt liquors.

label: Fermenting-Room Man
description: Controls fermentation process in making distilled or malt liquors.

label: Yeast Maker
description: Makes yeast used in production of distilled and malt liquors.

label: Wine Worker
description: Performs variety of tasks in wine making.

label: Wine and Liquor Taster
description: Tastes samples of wine or liquor.

label: Vinegar Maker
description: Carries out all processes connected with manufacture of vinegar from malt, denatured alcohol, wine or other source.

label: Fruit Press-Operator
description: Extracts juice from fruit pulp using power press.

label: Other Brewers, Wine and Beverage Makers
description: This group includes brewers, wine and beverage makers not elsewhere classified, for example those who add hops and sugar to malt and water mash and cook them; blend wines and distilled liquors; rack and mature wines; clarify wines by turning bottles periodically or by chemical action; treat wine to make champagne; or make non-alcoholic beverages.

label: Oil Presser (Edible Oils)
description: Extracts oil from oil-bearing seeds, fruits and nuts.

label: Refining Machine-Operator (Oils and Fats)
description: Operates machine which refines crude soya bean, cotton seed, peanut and other edible oils.

label: Hydrogenation Operator (Oils and Fats)
description: Operates equipment to process oils and fats used in making margarine.

label: Fish Butcher
description: Prepares fish and other sea and freshwater foods for sale or curing.

label: Other Food and Beverage Processors
description: This group includes food and beverage processors not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform various tasks in the manufacture of margarine or shell, clean, roast, blanch or polish nuts.

label: Tobacco Preparers, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in 7-81.20 to 7-81.90.

label: Tobacco Grader
description: Grades cured tobacco leaves as to type and quality according to colour, texture, size of leaf, and locality grown.

label: Tobacco Blender
description: Mixes various grades and kinds of tobacco leaves in accordance with formula to form blend of distinctive flavour.

label: Tobacco Conditioner Operator
description: Tends vacuum conditioner (steam-pressure chamber) which moistens opened hogsheads of tobacco for further processing.

label: Tobacco Stripper (Hand)
description: Removes midribs and stalks from tobacco leaves by hand.

label: Tobacco Stripper (Hand or Machine)
description: Removes midribs and stalks from tobacco leaves by hand (7-81.50) or machine (7-81.60).

label: Tobacco Stripper (Machine)
description: Removes mid-ribs and stalks from tobacco leaves by machine.

label: Tobacco Cutting Machine-Operator
description: Cuts tobacco leaves into coarse or fine shreds by machine.

label: Other Tobacco Preparers
description: This group includes tobacco preparers not elsewhere classified, for example those who prepare flavouring mixtures and treat tobacco with them; mix and fluff cur or shredded tobacco in a revolving cylinder; dry leaf or cut tobacco in a heating device; cool tobacco as it comes from steamer or drying room.

label: Cigar Maker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-82.

label: Cigar Maker (Hand)
description: Makes complete cigar by hand.

label: Cigar Maker (Machine)
description: Makes complete cigar by machine.

label: Other Cigar Makers
description: This group includes cigar makers not elsewhere classified, for example those for example those who examine wrapper leaves and sort them for colour and size; separate good binder leaves from imperfect ones; lay wrappers on cigar-making machine and patch leaves which have holes in them; examine finished cigars for imperfections and sort for colour and size.

label: Cigarette Maker (Machine)
description: Makes cigarettes by operating an automatic machine.

label: Other Cigarette Makers
description: This group includes cigarette makers not elsewhere classified, for example those who make special sizes and types of cigarettes by hand, or examine cigarettes for proper filling, printing and gluing.

label: Snuff Maker
description: Makes snuff tobacco by pulverising and blending various types of tobacco with machines.

label: Other Tobacco Preparers and Tobacco Products Makers
description: This group includes tobacco preparers and tobacco product makers not elsewhere classified, for example those who form plugs of chewing tobacco by hand; press plugs of chewing tobacco by machine; make plugs of tobacco which are to be sliced for making pipe tobacco.

label: Tailor, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-91.

label: Tailor, Made-to-Measure Garments
description: Makes complete garments or performs the more difficult tasks in making and altering overcoats, suits, skirts and other tailored garments (except fur garments) according to customer's requirements.

label: Tailor, Ready-to-Wear Garments
description: Performs the more difficult hand- or machine-sewing tasks in the manufacture of ready-to-wear overcoats, suits, skirts and other tailored clothing.

label: Dressmaker
description: Makes complete dresses and assimilated garments, and executes alterations and repairs.

label: Other Tailors and Dressmakers
description: This group includes tailors and dressmakers not elsewhere classified, for example those specialising in making shirts, blouses, lingerie or corsetry completely; taking customers' measurements; fitting men's and women's ready-to-wear garments; examining garments for finish and size trimming loose threads.

label: Fur Tailor or Related Worker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-92.

label: Fur Tailor
description: Makes complete fur garments or performs the more difficult tasks in making, altering, renovating and repairing fur garments and other fur articles.

label: Fur Pattern Maker
description: Prepares patterns and makes full-size canvas models of fur garments and other fur articles. Workers specialising in designing fur garments are classified in unit group l-62.

label: Fur Grader and Matcher
description: Sorts, grades and matches furs for individual garments or other articles.

label: Fur Cutter
description: Cuts fur according to pattern for making or repairing garments or other articles.

label: Fur Nailer
description: Stretches and trims dressed furs to conform to pattern outline of garment or other article.

label: Other Fur Tailors and Related Workers
description: This group includes fur tailors and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who rip old fur coats into strips to salvage furs or skins; glue fabric to interior of fur coats to reinforce hide; or trim blocked fur garments to remove excess fur around chalk-marked pattern on inside of garment.

label: Hat Maker, General
description: Makes men's and women's hats, using a variety of materials such as felt, silk, velvet and straw. May operate machine that stretches felt cones to form hat shapes.

label: Milliner, General
description: Makes women's hats completely, using a variety of materials such as felt, silk, velvet and straw.

label: Hat-Blocking-Machine Operator
description: Operates machine that stretches felt cones to form hat shapes.

label: Other Milliners and Hat Makers
description: This group includes milliners and hat makers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in making cork and other sun helmets, silk hats and other headgear for special purposes; buffing and sanding hat bodies to smooth and polish surface; trimming hat brims to specified width.

label: Pattern Maker or Cutter, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-94.

label: Garment Pattern Maker
description: Draws and cuts out patterns of parts of suits, dresses, shirts, blouses, hats, caps and other garments made from materials other than fur.

label: Hat and Cap Pattern Maker
description: Draws and cuts out patterns of parts of hats and caps: performs tasks similar to those of Garment pattern-maker (7-94.20), but specialises in patterns of hats and caps.

label: Garment Marker
description: Marks outlines of patterns on cloth, light leathers, or similar materials used in garment making.

label: Garment Cutter, except Leather
description: Cuts single or multiple layers of material (other than leather) into parts for making up into clothing.

label: Leather Garment Cutter
description: Cuts leather into parts for making leather garments.

label: Glove Cutter, except Leather
description: Cuts material, other than leather, for glove making.

label: Glove Cutter, Leather or other material
description: Cuts Leather (7-94.80) or other material (7-94.70) for glove making.

label: Leather Glove Cutter
description: Cuts leather for making leather gloves.

label: Other Patternmakers and Cutters
description: This group includes patternmakers and cutters not elsewhere classified, for example those who make patterns, or mark or cut materials, for making household linen, upholstery, mattresses, sails, awnings, tents and umbrellas.

label: Sewer or Embroiderer, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 7-95.

label: Hand and Machine Sewer, General
description: Performs various hand- and machine-sewing tasks in making, altering and repairing articles of textile and kindred materials.

label: Garment Hand Sewer (except Leather and Fur)
description: Performs by hand one or more sewing tasks in making sews visible or repairing garments, except those of leather or fur.

label: Leather Garment Hand Sewer
description: Performs hand-sewing tasks in making and repairing leather garments or gloves.

label: Fur Hand Sewer
description: Performs hand-sewing tasks in making, altering, renovating and repairing fur garments and other fur articles.

label: Sewing-Machine Operator
description: Operates standard or specialised single- or multiple- needle sewing machine in making, repairing or renovating garments, gloves and miscellaneous products in textiles and kindred materials.

label: Hand Embroiderer
description: Works decorative designs on garment parts or other materials by hand stitching.

label: Embroiderer, Hand or Machine
description: Works decorative designs on garment parts or other materials by hand stitching (7-95.60) or sewing machine (7-95.70).

label: Machine Embroiderer
description: Reproduces ornamental designs on garment parts or other materials by use of standard or specialised single- or multiple-needle sewing machine.

label: Other Sewers and Embroiderers
description: This group includes sewer and embroiderers not elsewhere classified, for example those specialising in hand-sewing such items as household linen, hats, caps, upholstery, mattresses, sails, awnings, tents or umbrellas.

label: Upholsterer or Related Worker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities decribed in unit group 7-96.

label: Furniture Upholsterer
description: Installs, arranges and secures springs, padding and covering material to furniture frames.

label: Vehicle Upholsterer
description: Fits and installs interior trim and seat cushioning and covering in vehicles, such as motor cars, railway coaches and aircraft.

label: Mattress Maker
description: Makes mattresses completely by hand or machine.

label: Other Upholsterers and Related Workers
description: This group includes upholsterers and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those  making completely or fitting and installing curtains and pelmets wall and furniture covers, quilts or other soft furnishings; those specialising in one operation or an assembly line for upholstering furniture frames, or for making mattresses; and those stripping upholstered furniture for repair or renovation.

label: Sail, Tent and Awning Maker
description: Makes completely sails, tents, awnings and similar products, by hand or machine.

label: Umbrella Maker
description: Assembles and covers umbrellas.

label: Other Tailors, Dressmakers, Sewers, Upholsterers and Related Workers
description: This group includes tailors, dressmakers, sewers, upholsterers and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those making artificial flowers; making decorative trimmings with feathers; making handknotted carpets; making footwear mainly of rope or canvas.

label: Shoe-maker, General
description: Makes leather footwear to requirements of individual customers. May also carry out repairs.

label: Orthopaedic Footwear Maker
description: Makes special leather footwear to individual requirements of customers with foot or leg deformities.

label: Shoe Repairer
description: Repairs leather and other footwear.

label: Other Shoemakers and Shoe Repairers
description: This group includes shoemakers and shoe repairers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in making special types of footwear, such as mountain boots, riding boots and ballet shoes.

label: Shoe Worker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities detailed in unit group 8-02.

label: Shoe Pattern-maker
description: Prepares patterns for use as guides in cutting or trimming parts of footwear or in preparation of cutting dies.

label: Clicker Cutter (Machine)
description: Operates press machine which cuts out upper parts of footwear.

label: Shoe Cutter (Hand or Machine)
description: Cuts out upper parts of footwear by press machine (8-02.20) or hand (8-02.25).

label: Shoe Cutter (Hand)
description: Cuts out upper parts of footwear by hand.

label: Uppers Preparer
description: Prepares and assembles upper parts of footwear for sewing.

label: Sole Pressman
description: Operates press machine which cuts out soles of footwear.

label: Sole Fitter
description: Prepares rough soles for assembling on last.

label: Laster
description: Joins upper parts of footwear to insole in preparation for sewing together.

label: Shoe Sewer (Hand or Machine)
description: Hand sews, or operates hand-, foot- or power-driven sewing machine to join together parts of footwear.

label: Shoe Finisher
description: Examines and finishes footwear.

label: Other Shoe Cutters, Lasters, Sewers and Related Workers
description: This group includes shoe cutters, lasters, sewers and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example, those who specialise in shaping some upper parts; building up heels and fixing them to footwear; removing creases from uppers; giving final polish; sorting and matching footwear for size, grain and colour; inserting thin inner sole in footwear.

label: Leather Goods Maker, General
description: Makes, by hand and machine, a variety of products consisting mainly of real or artificial leather, such as handbags, wallets, luggage, brief cases, belting, footballs and leather novelties.

label: Saddler and Harness Maker
description: Makes, by hand or machine, saddles, collars and harness for use on horses and other animals.

label: Leather Cutter
description: Cuts out leather parts for making a variety of products.

label: Leather Sewer, Hand
description: Sews leather parts together by hand to make a variety of products.

label: Leather Sewer, Machine
description: Operates a hand-, foot- or power-driven machine to sew leather parts together to make a variety of products.

label: Leather Goods Assembler
description: Assembles leather goods, such as luggage, handbags, belting and leather novelties.

label: Other Leather Goods Makers
description: This group includes leather goods makers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in making fetlock covers, knee pads, spur fittings and whips.

label: Woodworker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in minor group 8-1.

label: Cabinetmaker
description: Makes completely and repairs wooden articles, such as cabinets and furniture, using woodworking machines and hand tools.

label: Other Cabinetmakers
description: This groups includes cabinetmakers not elsewhere classified, for example those who make billiard tables, piano shells, small wooden cases for jewellery and instruments, clock cases and similar products.

label: Woodworking Machine Setter, General
description: Sets cutting tools in woodworking machines, such as precision sawing, shaping, planing, turning and carving machines and prepares them for operation by others.

label: Woodworking Machine-Operator, General
description: Operates previously set-up woodworking machines, such as precision sawing, shaping, planing, turning or carving machines.

label: Woodworking Machine Setter-Operator, General
description: Sets up, prepares and operates woodworking machines, such as precision sawing, planing, turning, shaping and carving machines.

label: Precision Sawyer
description: Sets and operates sawing machine which cuts stock lumber to standard or desired shape.

label: Precision Sawyer, Hand or Machine
description: Cuts stock lumber to standard or desired shape using hand tools or sawing machine.

label: Wood Turner
description: Shapes pieces of wood rotating in a lathe, using hand tools.

label: Wood-Lathe Setter-Operator
description: Sets and operates automatic lathe which turns wooden articles from stock.

label: Wood Shaping-Machine Setter-Operator
description: Sets and operates machine which cuts designs of irregular shape in the surface of straight, curved or irregular pieces of wood.

label: Wood-Routing-Machine Setter-Operator
description: Sets and operates machine which cuts depressions or designs of various shapes on wood.

label: Wood-Planing-Machine Setter-Operator
description: Sets and operates single or multiple cutting machine which planes surfaces and reduces thickness of wooden stock.

label: Wood Planer
description: Planes surfaces and reduces thickness of wooden stock using hand tools or machine.

label: Wood-Spindle Carving-Machine Setter- Operator
description: Sets and operates machine which carves artistic and decorative designs on surface of pieces of wood.

label: Other Woodworking-Machine Operators
description: This group includes woodworking-machine operators not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate mortising, universal and sanding machines.

label: Coach-Body Builder
description: Constructs and repairs wooden bodies of vehicles, using hand and power tools.

label: Cartwright
description: Constructs and repairs wooden carts, wagons and wheels, using hand and power tools.

label: Cooper
description: Makes or repairs wooden casks for holding wet or dry goods, using hand or power tools.

label: Wooden Pattern Maker
description: Constructs wooden patterns, using hand or power tools.

label: Wooden Model Maker
description: Constructs to scale wooden reproductions of objects such as buildings, ships and aircraft, and constructs full-size models (mock-ups) of smaller objects, such as mechanical appliances, using hand or power tools.

label: Wood Carver
description: Carves designs in wood for furniture, screens, panelling and other uses, using hand tools.

label: Veneer Applier
description: Faces parts of wooden furniture with veneer.

label: Wooden Furniture Finisher
description: Finishes or refinishes surface of wooden furniture and fittings.

label: Smoking-Pipe Maker
description: Makes smoking pipes and cigar and cigarette holders in wood and kindred materials, using hand or power tools.

label: Marquetry Inlayer
description: Prepares and inlays ornamental wood to form decorative designs in furniture.

label: Other Cabinetmakers and Related Woodworkers
description: This group includes cabinetmakers and related woodworkers not elsewhere classified, for example those marking wood to indicate where it must be cut or shaped; making wooden sports goods, such as skis, tennis racquets, hockey sticks and gymnastic apparatus; making coffins; making wooden shoes; bending wooden parts in steam by hand or machine; assembling wooden products.

label: Stone Cutter or Carver, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 8-20.

label: Stone Cutter and Finisher
description: Sets and operates machines which cut, saw, plane, grind and polish building and monumental stone.

label: Stone Grader
description: Selects blocks of granite, marble or other stone according to order specifications.

label: Stonework Layout Man
description: Makes patterns and marks shapes on stone for subsequent sawing, planing, drilling and other dressing and cutting operations.

label: Stone Lathe-Operator
description: Sets and operates lathes to cut and polish stone columns, pillars and other cylindrical shapes.

label: Stone Letter Cutter (Hand)
description: Cuts incised or raised numbers or letters on stones with pneumatic and other hand tools.

label: Stone Carver (Hand)
description: Carves figures or designs in relief on blocks or slabs of stone with pneumatic and other hand tools.

label: Monument Carver-Setter
description: Carves out simple designs on stone blocks used for monuments, memorials or decorative facings on buildings, and sets stones in the erection of monuments and memorials.

label: Other Stone Cutters and Carvers
description: This group includes stone cutters and carvers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in cutting, lettering and designs on stones by directing a blast of sand or shot against surfaces left exposed by a stencil on a stone face; operating machines with specially shaped abrasive wheels for cutting mouldings, grooves, panels and other decorative designs in stone blocks; polishing curved and irregular surfaces of blocks or slabs of stone to a lustrous finish by hand; drilling holes in finished slabs and blocks of building stone for insertion of wires or rods for mounting and fastening purposes.

label: Blacksmith, Toolmaker or Machine-Tool Operator, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in minor group 8-3.

label: Blacksmith, General
description: Forges and repairs articles of iron and steel, such as hand tools, hooks, chains, agricultural implements and metal structural parts, using hand or power hammers.

label: Hammersmith
description: Shapes heated metal into forgings on power hammer equipped with open dies.

label: Drop-Hammer Operator
description: Operates closed-die drop-hammer to forge metal articles.

label: Forging-Press Operator
description: Operates a power-press machine equipped with closed dies to forge metal articles.

label: Other Blacksmiths, Hammersmiths and Forging-Press Operators
description: This group includes blacksmiths, hammersmiths and forging-press operators not classified elsewhere, for example those hammering, cutting, shaping and punching metal pieces as directed by a blacksmith; starting and stopping power hammers on instructions of a blacksmith or hammersmith; adjusting pressure of forging press on instructions of a forging-press operator.

label: Tool and Die Maker
description: Fits and assembles parts to make and repair metal-working dies, cutting tools, jigs, fixtures, gauges, and machinists= hand tools.

label: Jig and Gauge Maker
description: Lays out, fits and assembles parts to make and repair jigs, fixtures and gauges.

label: Metal Pattern Maker (Foundry)
description: Makes and repairs metal patterns used in making foundry moulds.

label: Metal Marker
description: Lays out lines and reference points on metal stock to guide workers who cut, turn, mill, grind or otherwise shape metal.

label: Other Toolmakers, Metal Pattern Makers and Metal Markers
description: This group includes toolmakers, metal pattern makers and metal markers not elsewhere classified, for example those who set industrial diamonds in grinding tools or in diamond-pointed cutting tools.

label: Toolmaker, Metal Pattern Maker and Metal Marker, General
description: Makes tools, dies, patterns and other metal articles using hand and machine tools.

label: Metalworking Machine Setter, General
description: Sets up various types of power-driven precision metalworking machines, such as lathes, milling, boring, drilling and grinding machines to be operated or attended by other workers.

label: Metalworking Machine Setter-Operator, General
description: Sets up and operates a variety of power-driven precision metal-cutting machines.

label: Lathe Setter-Operator
description: Sets up and operates a power-driven metalworking lathe.

label: Milling-Machine Setter-Operator
description: Sets up and operates a power-driven machine which cuts metal with a multi-toothed rotary cutter.

label: Planing-Machine Setter-Operator
description: Sets up and operates a power-driven machine in which a cutting tool is guided into metal fixed to a reciprocating table.

label: Boring-Machine Setter-Operator
description: Sets up and operates a power-driven machine in which cylindrical holes in metal objects are aligned and enlarged by a rotating cutting tool.

label: Drilling-Machine Setter-Operator
description: Sets up and operates a power-driven machine which drills and reams holes in metal.

label: Precision-Grinding-Machine Setter- Operator
description: Sets up and operates a power-driven machine which grinds and smoothes metal surfaces to close tolerances with a grinding wheel.

label: Honing-Machine Setter-Operator
description: Sets and operates vertical or horizontal honing machine to hone internal or external surfaces of metal objects.

label: Numerical-Control-Machine Setter- Operator
description: Sets up and operates magnetic or punched-tape-controlled machine tools that automatically mill, drill, broach and ream metal parts.

label: Other Machine-Tool Setter-Operators
description: This group includes machine-tool setter-operators who are not classified elsewhere, for example those who set and operate shaping machines or machine tools effecting several different types of metal cutting.

label: Machine-Tool Operator, General
description: Operates various types of automatic or semi-automatic power-driven metal-cutting, boring and grinding machines which have been set up for repetitive work.

label: Lathe Operator
description: Operates a power-driven metal-cutting lathe set up for repetitive work.

label: Milling-Machine Operator
description: Operates a power-driven machine which cuts metal with a multi-toothed rotary cutter and has been set up for repetitive work.

label: Planing Machine-Operator
description: Operates a power-driven planing machine which planes metal fixed to a reciprocating table and has been set up for repetitive work.

label: Boring Machine-Operator
description: Operates a power-driven machine set up for repetitive work, in which cylindrical holes in metal parts are aligned and enlarged to required size by a rotating cutting tool.

label: Drilling-Machine Operator
description: Operates a power-driven machine, set up for repetitive work, to drill or ream single or multiple holes in metal.

label: Precision Grinding-Machine Operator
description: Operates a power-driven precision metal-grinding machine, set up for repetitive work.

label: Honing-Machine Operator
description: Operates previously set up honing machine to hone internal and external surfaces of metal parts, such as cylinders, bearings or connecting rods.

label: Metal-Sawing-Machine Operator
description: Operates a power-driven saw, such as hacksaw, band-saw or friction saw to cut straight, curved or irregular shaped parts from metal.

label: Automatic Transfer-Machine Operator
description: Operates transfer machine consisting of series of machines connected by mechanism that automatically transfers workpieces and performs series of machining operations, such as drilling, boring, tapping, and milling.

label: Other Machine-Tool Operators
description: This group includes machine-tool operators not classified elsewhere, for example those who operate shaping machines, gear hobbing machines or tend machine automatically controlled by magnetic or punched tape programmes.

label: Buffing- and Polishing-Machine Operator
description: Operates a fixed or portable machine for buffing and polishing metal.

label: Tool Grinder, Machine Tools
description: Sharpens cutting tools used in metalworking, wood-working and other machines by means of a power-operated grinding wheel.

label: Cutting Instruments Sharpener
description: Sharpens knives, surgical instruments and other cutting instruments (except machine tools) by means of grinding wheel.

label: Saw Repairer and Sharpener
description: Repairs, sets and sharpens hand, circular and band-saws.

label: Textile Card Grinder
description: Repairs and sharpens the metal teeth of textile carding machines.

label: Other Metal Grinders, Polishers and Tool Sharpeners
description: This group includes metal grinders, polishers and tool sharpeners not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate machines for straightening and grinding toothed wheels; operate lapping machines to lap surfaces of metal objects; polish metal by hand, and sharpen knives and scissors in the street on portable machines.

label: Cutler
description: Forges, assembles, sharpens and repairs cutlery and other edge-tools using hand and machine tools.

label: Gunsmith
description: Makes, repairs and modifies sports guns and other small arms according to customers' specifications.

label: Locksmith
description: Fits lock parts, assembles and repairs locks.

label: Metal Spinner
description: Rotates sheet-metal discs on a special machine (lathe) and presses hand tools against discs to shape them.

label: Metal Former (Hand)
description: Trims, bends and shapes sheet metal and metal rods using hand tools, chucks and forming blocks.

label: Metal-Press Operator
description: Operates a power press (other than a forging press or steel-plate-bending machine) in which dies, punches or other tools trim, punch, shape, notch or otherwise shape metal stock.

label: Metal-Bending-Machine Operator
description: Bends steel plates or rods to desired curvature by means of a bending machine.

label: Power-Shear Operator
description: Operates a power machine to cut hot or cold metal objects such as slabs, billets, plates, bars, strips and sheets to specified dimensions and angles.

label: Other Blacksmiths, Toolmakers and Machine-Tool Operators Not Elsewhere Classified
description: This group includes blacksmiths, toolmakers and machine tool operators not classified elsewhere, for example those making metal articles such as springs, cables, nails, bolts and steel needles.

label: Machinery Fitter or Machine Assembler, Type of Machine Unknown
description: May make or assemble any (but not all) machinery or related equipment described in unit group 8-41.

label: Machinery Fitter, General
description: Makes completely parts and subassemblies of machinery and related equipment, according to specifications or by reproducing original components, using machine tools, and fits, assembles and repairs machine parts.

label: Machinery Fitter-Assembler, General
description: Fits and assembles fabricated parts in the manufacture of machinery, engines and other metal apparatus (except precision instruments and electrical equipment).

label: Internal Combustion Engine Fitter- Assembler (except Aircraft and Marine Engines)
description: Fits and assembles parts in the manufacture of internal combustion engines, except those used for ship or aircraft propulsion.

label: Aircraft Engine Fitter-Assembler
description: Fits and assembles parts in the manufacture of air-craft engines.

label: Marine Engine Fitter-Assembler
description: Fits and assembles parts in the manufacture of marine engines.

label: Turbine Fitter-Assembler (except Aircraft and Marine)
description: Fits and assembles parts in the manufacture of turbines, excluding those used on ships or aircraft.

label: Metalworking Machine-Tool-Fitter- Assembler
description: Fits and assembles parts in the manufacture of metalworking machine tools and related equipment.

label: Mining Machinery Fitter-Assembler
description: Fits and assembles parts in the manufacture of mining machinery.

label: Printing Machinery Fitter-Assembler
description: Fits and assembles parts in the manufacture of printing machinery.

label: Textile Machinery Fitter-Assembler
description: Fits and assembles parts in the manufacture of textile machinery.

label: Woodworking Machinery Fitter-Assembler
description: Fits and assembles parts in the manufacture of machines which cut and shape wood.

label: Agricultural Machinery Fitter-Assembler
description: Fits and assembles parts in the manufacture of agricultural machinery.

label: Earth-Moving Equipment Fitter- Assembler
description: Fits and assembles parts in the manufacture of earth-moving equipment.

label: Office Machinery Fitter-Assembler
description: Fits and assembles mechanical parts in the manufacture of office machinery and equipment.

label: Machinery Erector and Installer
description: Erects and installs, in place of use, machinery and other mechanical equipment (except refrigeration and air-conditioning plant).

label: Refrigeration and Air-Conditioning Plant Mechanic
description: Installs and repairs industrial and commercial refrigeration and cooling systems.

label: Airframe Fitter-Assembler
description: Fits together and builds up the structural members of the fuselage, tail, wings, undercarriage or other structural parts of aircraft.

label: Other Machinery Fitters and Machine Assemblers
description: This group includes machinery fitters and machine assemblers not elsewhere classified, for example those performing tasks in fitting, adjusting and assembling particular types of industrial and other mechanical equipment, which are not performed by workers classified in the preceding groups.

label: Watch and Clock Assembler
description: Fits and assembles parts of watches and clocks. May also make parts.

label: Watch and Clock Assembler or Repairer
description: Fits and assembles (8-42.20) or repairs, cleans and adjusts (8-42.25) watches and clocks. May also make parts.

label: Watch and Clock Repairer
description: Repairs, cleans and adjusts watches and clocks.

label: Precision Instrument Maker
description: Makes, adjusts and repairs mechanical instruments and mechanical portions of electrical and optical instruments.

label: Optical Instrument Maker and Repairer
description: Adjusts and repairs optical instruments and assembles optical parts, incorporating such items as precision lenses, prisms, and mirrors.

label: Precision Instrument Assembler
description: Assembles prepared parts that do not require further tooling, in the manufacture of precision and optical instruments.

label: Orthopaedic Appliance Maker and Repairer
description: Makes and repairs orthopaedic appliances such as artificial limbs and body supports.

label: Dental Prosthesis Maker and Repairer
description: Makes and repairs dentures and other dental aids.

label: Other Watch, Clock and Precision Instrument Makers
