description: This group includes watch, clock and precision instrument makers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in making and repairing particular types of medical or dental instruments, thermostatic control instruments, or panel instruments for vehicles.

label: Motor-Vehicle Mechanics, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 8-43.

label: Automobile Mechanic
description: Repairs, services and overhauls mechanical parts of motor buses, automobiles and assimilated motor vehicles.

label: Motor Truck Mechanic
description: Repairs, services and overhauls trucks and trucking equipment such as trailers.

label: Motor Cycle Mechanic
description: Repairs, services and overhauls motor cycles and motorised pedal cycles.

label: Other Motor-Vehicle Mechanics
description: This groups includes motor-vehicle mechanics not elsewhere classified, for example those specialising in a particular type of motor-vehicle repair, such as repairing automatic transmissions, tuning up engines, or repairing brake systems or motor cooling systems.

label: Aircraft Engine Mechanic, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 8-44.

label: Aircraft Engine Mechanic, General
description: Services, repairs and overhauls aircraft engines, such as jet, turbo-prop and piston engines, and other mechanical equipment of aircraft.

label: Aircraft Engine Service Mechanic
description: Services engines, engine parts and other mechanical equipment of aircraft at line station, making repairs required to keep aircraft in safe operating condition.

label: Other Aircraft Engine Mechanics
description: This group includes aircraft engine mechanics not elsewhere classified, for example those specialising in a particular type of work, such as repairing aircraft engine cylinders or propeller assemblies.

label: Machinery Fitter, Machine Assembler or Precision Instrument Maker (except Electrical) Not Elsewhere Classified, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 8-49.

label: Machinery Mechanic, General
description: Services and repairs various types of machinery, engines and related equipment (except automobile and aircraft engines and electrical apparatus).

label: Reciprocating Steam Engine Mechanic
description: Repairs and services reciprocating steam engines, including those used for ship propulsion.

label: Diesel Engine Mechanic (except Motor Vehicle)
description: Repairs and services diesel engines which drive generators and other stationary equipment, railway locomotives, construction machinery and other mobile equipment, except motor vehicles.

label: Turbine Mechanic (except Aircraft and Marine Turbines)
description: Services and repairs turbines (except aircraft and ship turbines).

label: Metalworking Machine-Tool Mechanic
description: Services and repairs metalworking machine tools which cut, shape and grind metal to fine tolerances.

label: Mining Machinery Mechanic
description: Services and repairs mining machinery.

label: Printing Machinery Mechanic
description: Services and repairs printing machinery.

label: Textile Machinery Mechanic
description: Services and repairs textile machinery.

label: Woodworking Machinery Mechanic
description: Services and repairs machines which cut and shape wood.

label: Agricultural Machinery Mechanic
description: Services and repairs agricultural machinery.

label: Earth-Moving Equipment and Construction Machinery Mechanic
description: Services and repairs earth-moving equipment and construction machinery.

label: Office Machines Mechanic
description: Services and repairs mechanical parts of office machines, such as typewriters and duplicating, addressing, accounting and calculating machines.

label: Plant Maintenance Mechanic
description: Repairs and maintains installed machinery, plumbing and mechanical structures of an industrial or other establishment.

label: Pedal-Cycle Repairer
description: Services and repairs pedal cycles.

label: Oiler and Greaser (except Ships' Engines)
description: Lubricates the moving parts of stationary engines, motor vehicles and machinery (except ships' engines).

label: Mechanical Products Inspector and Tester
description: Inspects and tests machinery and related mechanical equipment for finish, mechanical operation and conformance to manufacturer's standards.

label: Other Machinery Fitters, Machine Assemblers and Precision Instrument Makers (except Electrical)
description: This group includes machinery fitters, machine assemblers and precision instrument makers (except electrical) not elsewhere classified, for example those who assemble metal products from prepared parts not requiring further tooling or adjusting, by fixing the parts together with bolts, clips screws, rivets or similar devices.

label: Electrical Fitter, General
description: Fits, adjusts, assembles and repairs various kinds of electrical machinery and electrical apparatus in factory, workshop or place of use.

label: Electrical Motor and Generator Fitter
description: Fits, adjusts and repairs electrical motors and generators in factory, workshop or place of use.

label: Electrical Transformer Fitter
description: Fits, adjusts and repairs electrical transformers in factory, workshop or place of use.

label: Electrical Switchgear and Control Apparatus Fitter
description: Fits, adjusts, and repairs electric switchgear and control apparatus in factory, workshop or place of use.

label: Electrical Instrument Fitter
description: Fits, adjusts, and repairs electrical instruments and electrical parts of mechanical instruments in factory, workshop or place of use.

label: Electrical Elevator and Related Equipment Fitter
description: Fits, adjusts and repairs electrical parts of elevators and related equipment in factory, workshop or place of use.

label: Other Electrical Fitters
description: This group includes electrical fitters not elsewhere specified, for example those who specialise in fitting, adjusting and repairing electrical components of domestic appliances, office machines, industrial machines and other appliances, aircraft, ships and vehicles. Workers occupied primarily in making simple repairs to electrical apparatus are classified in Electrical repairman (8-55.70).

label: Electronics Fitter
description: Fits, adjusts, installs and repairs parts, assemblies or subassemblies in the manufacture of radio, television and other communications equipment and apparatus in factory, workshop or place of use.

label: Electronics Fitter (Radio, Television and Radar Equipment)
description: Fits, adjusts, installs and repairs radio and television transmitters and radar equipment in factory, workshop or place of use.

label: Electronics Fitter (Medical Equipment)
description: Fits, adjusts and repairs electronic components of medical equipment in factory, workshop or place of use.

label: Electronic Computer and Related Equipment Fitter
description: Fits, adjusts and repairs computers and related electronic equipment in factory, workshop or place of use.

label: Electronics Fitter (Industrial Equipment)
description: Fits, adjusts and repairs electronic components of industrial machinery and related equipment in factory, workshop or place of use.

label: Electronic Signalling Systems Fitter
description: Fits, adjusts and repairs electronic components of signalling systems in factory, workshop or place of use.

label: Other Electronics Fitters
description: This group includes electronics fitters not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in fitting, adjusting and repairing electronic devices and electronic components of a particular type of machine or equipment not referred to in the foregoing.

label: Electrical Equipment Assembler
description: Assembles finished parts of electrical machinery and other electrical apparatus.

label: Electronic Equipment Assembler
description: Assembles previously prepared parts in the batch or mass production assembly of electronic goods or components.

label: Coil Winder (Machine)
description: Winds wire onto bobbins or directly onto cores by machine to make electrical coils.

label: Coil Winder (Hand or Machine)
description: Winds wire onto bobbins or cores by machine (8-53.40) or hand (8-53.50) to make electrical coils.

label: Coil Winder (Hand)
description: Winds wire onto cores by hand to make or rewind electrical coils.

label: Other Electrical and Electronic Equipment Assemblers
description: This group includes electrical and electronic equipment assemblers not elsewhere classified, for example those assembling microelectronic equipment, such as hearing aids and satellite communications devices, using magnifying lens, hand tools and spot welder; assembling flexible electronic leads; winding capacitors; assembling capacitors (condensers); assembling electronic tubes (radio valves).

label: Radio and Television Mechanic
description: Repairs radio and television receivers in workshop or place of use.

label: Other Radio and Television Repairmen
description: This group includes radio and television repairmen not elsewhere classified, for example those installing and repairing radio and television antennas.

label: Electrician, General
description: Installs, maintains and repairs electrical wiring and related equipment in buildings and other structures.

label: Aircraft Electrician
description: Installs and repairs electrical wiring and related equipment in aircraft.

label: Ship's Electrician
description: Installs and repairs electrical wiring and equipment in ships.

label: Vehicle Electrician
description: Installs and repairs electrical wiring and other electrical equipment in vehicles, such as trains, trams and motor vehicles.

label: Stage and Studio Electrician
description: Installs, maintains and repairs electrical equipment and lights used in theatre and studio.

label: Maintenance Electrician
description: Repairs and maintains wiring and electrical equipment in industrial or commercial establishments, institutional buildings such as schools and hospitals, or residential buildings.

label: Electrical Repairman
description: Makes repairs, generally of a simple character, to electrical apparatus, mainly of a domestic kind, in workshop or place of use.

label: Other Electrical Wiremen
description: This group includes electricians and electrical repairers not elsewhere classified, for example those installing and servicing illuminated signs, electrical wiring and related equipment in mines, and accumulators arranged in series to provide electric lighting or power.

label: Building Electrician
description: Installs electrical wiring and related equipment in houses, industrial and commercial establishments and other buildings.

label: Telephone and Telegraph Installer, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 8-56.

label: Telephone and Telegraph Installer
description: Installs manually operated and automatic telephone and telegraph equipment.

label: Telephone and Telegraph Mechanic
description: Services and repairs manually operated and automatic telephone and telegraph equipment.

label: Other Telephone and Telegraph Installers
description: This group includes telephone and telegraph installers and repairers not elsewhere classified, for example those specialising in one particular part of the work, such as adjusting relays or telegraph repeaters, diagnosing faults in equipment and circuits, making operating tests on circuits and relays to check on functioning, or maintaining teletype machines.

label: Electric Lineman or Cable Jointer, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 8-57.

label: Electric power Lineman
description: Installs, maintains and repairs overhead high-tension or low-tension power lines conducting electricity between generating stations, substations and consumers.

label: Electric Traction Lineman
description: Installs and repairs overhead wires to carry electricity for railway trains, trams or trolley buses.

label: Telephone and Telegraph Lineman
description: Installs and repairs overhead and underground wires and cables for telephone and telegraph transmission.

label: Electric Cable Jointer
description: Makes joints in surface and underground cables.

label: Other Electric Linemen and Cable Jointers
description: This group includes electric linemen and cable jointers not elsewhere classified, for example those specialising in laying cables underground, or in maintenance and repair of underground electric power transmission cables.

label: Electrical and Electronic Products Inspector and Tester
description: Inspects and tests electrical or electronic equipment for conformance to manufacturer's standards.

label: Other Electrical Fitters and Related Electrical and Electronics Workers
description: This group includes electrical fitters and related electrical and electronics workers not elsewhere classified.

label: Radio and Television Transmitting Equipment Operator
description: Operates and adjusts equipment of transmitter to broadcast radio and television programmes.

label: Radio and Television Studio Equipment Operator
description: Operates radio and television broadcasting studio equipment.

label: Other Broadcasting Station Operators
description: This group includes broadcasting station operators not elsewhere classified, for example those operating and servicing mobile radio and television broadcasting equipment outdoors, operating video recording equipment to photograph television images being broadcast as shown on video screen, to record the sound accompaniment and prepare film for rebroadcasting.

label: Sound-Recording Equipment Operator
description: Operates electronic equipment which records sound impulses on reels of tape, wire, film or composition discs for motion pictures, gramophone-record production, radio broadcasting and other purposes.

label: Public Address Equipment Operator
description: Installs and operates sound-amplifying equipment.

label: Cinema Projectionist
description: Operates a motion-picture projector and its sound reproducing equipment.

label: Other Sound-Equipment Operators and Cinema Projectionists
description: This group includes sound-equipment operators and cinema projectionists not elsewhere classified, for example those editing tapes to prepare master tape for making multiple copies; testing pressed phonograph records for sound quality, using sound reproduction equipment; editing film to synchronise music and dialogue and to insert sound effects; producing sound effects by artificial means, or form tapes of recordings, to accompany action portrayed by radio or television broadcast; operating a sound-mixing panel backstage during theatrical performance.

label: Plumber, General
description: Assembles, installs and maintains pipes, fittings and fixtures of drainage, heating, water supply and sanitary systems.

label: Pipe Fitter, General
description: Assembles, installs and maintains high-pressure and low-pressure systems of metal pipes, or combining metal and non-metal pipes, for conducting air, gas, steam, oil, water and other fluids.

label: Gas Pipe Fitter
description: Installs, repairs and maintains gas mains and pipes supplying consumers from mains.

label: Marine Pipe Fitter
description: Assembles, installs, maintains and repairs piping systems on ships.

label: Aircraft Pipe and Tube Fitter
description: Assembles, installs and repairs fuel and hydraulic pipelines, instrument tubes, ventilating conduits and other pipes and tubes in aircraft.

label: Other Plumbers and Pipe Fitters
description: This group includes plumbers and pipe fitters not elsewhere classified, for example those specialising in installing and repairing pipes and tubes for chemical processing apparatus, diesel engines, air-brake systems on vehicles or steam distribution, or in fixing of hangers and brackets to support pipes, or assembling sections of steel pipe to be installed by pipe fitters.

label: Welder, General
description: Welds metal parts by means of oxy-acetylene, other gas flame or electric arc.

label: Gas Welder
description: Welds metal parts by means of oxy-acetylene or other gas flame.

label: Electric Arc Welder (Hand)
description: Welds metal parts by means of hand-operated equipment which produces heat from an electric arc.

label: Electric Arc Welder (Hand or Machine)
description: Sets and operates stationary or mobile machine (8-72.25) or uses hand-operated equipment (8-72.20) to weld metal parts by means of an electric arc.

label: Electric Arc Welder (Machine)
description: Sets and operates stationary or mobile machine which welds metal parts by means of an electric arc.

label: Thermite Welder
description: Welds metal parts by means of a thermite compound: prepares and positions parts to be welded; builds clay mould round parts at weld point; pours thermite compound into mould; ignites compound to heat parts and cause iron contained in compound to melt, flow in mould and weld the parts; cleans and smooths welded parts.

label: Resistance Welder
description: Fuses and bonds metal parts by means of a machine in which heat is provided by passing an electric current through the metal parts placed between electrodes or pressed between roller electrodes.

label: Lead Burner
description: Makes, installs and repairs lead and lead alloy tanks, tank linings, pipes, floors and other lead fixtures and equipment by using blow-torch or oxy-acetylene torch and hand tools.

label: Brazer
description: Bonds (brazes) metal parts together, using gas torch, electric arc or other source of heat and applying brazing alloy and flux.

label: Flamecutter (Hand)
description: Cuts metal by means of oxy-acetylene or other gas flame.

label: Flamecutter (Machine)
description: Operates a machine which cuts metal plates and structural shapes to required dimensions by means of oxy-acetylene or other gas flame.

label: Solderer (Hand)
description: Joins metal parts with soft solder by means of a soldering iron.

label: Other Welders and Flame-Cutters
description: This group includes welders and flame-cutters not elsewhere classified, for example those cutting metal by electric arc; operating a jewellery-soldering machine; soldering items together by clamping them after inserting a solder or brazing alloy strip and placing them in special furnace, or on furnace conveyor; soldering items together by clamping them and dipping in molten solder; filling holes, grooves and indentations of motor vehicle body panels with solder, using solder stick and oxy-acetylene torch.

label: Sheet-Metal Worker, General
description: Makes, installs and repairs a variety of sheet-metal articles by hand and machine.

label: Sheet-Metal Marker
description: Marks out sheet metal for cutting and shaping.

label: Coppersmith
description: Makes, installs and repairs articles in copper and light alloys, such as containers, ducts, cowlings and pipes.

label: Tinsmith
description: Makes and repairs kitchen utensils and other articles in tinplate.

label: Boilersmith
description: Makes and repairs boilers, tanks, vats and other containers of sheet and plate steel.

label: Ornamental Sheet-Metal Worker
description: Makes and repairs ornamental articles and fittings of sheet metal, such as house and shop fittings.

label: Vehicle Sheet-Metal Worker
description: Makes, alters and repairs sheet-metal bodywork of vehicles such as automobiles, buses, trucks, wagons and railway coaches.

label: Aircraft Sheet-Metal Worker
description: Assembles, installs and repairs sheet-metal parts of aircraft.

label: Other Sheet-Metal Workers
description: This group includes sheet-metal workers not elsewhere classified, for example those assembling metal furniture and those specialising in installation of sheet-metal fixtures and fittings in ships.

label: Structural Metal Preparer or Erector, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 8-74.

label: Structural Metal Marker
description: Marks metal members and heavy plates to guide workers cutting, drilling and shaping them for use in buildings, ships and other structures.

label: Structural Steel Worker (Workshop)
description: Drills, cuts and shapes steel in workshop for buildings, ships and other structures.

label: Constructional Steel Erector
description: Performs various tasks in the erection of steel members and heavy plates for buildings, bridges and other structures (except ships).

label: Metal Shipwright
description: Assembles and erects framework and other metal parts of ships' structures.

label: Ship Plater
description: Shapes and fits structural steel plates of ships under construction or repair.

label: Hand Riveter
description: Rivets metal members such as plates, girders, columns and parts of smaller articles with hand hammer.

label: Riveter (Hand or Machine)
description: Rivets metal with hand hammer (8-74.60) or hydraulic or other rivet press (8-74.65).

label: Machine Riveter
description: Operates hydraulic or other rivet press which rivets steel plates, bars, beams or castings.

label: Pneumatic Riveter
description: Rivets metal members such as plates and girders using pneumatically operated hand hammer.

label: Other Structural Metal Preparers and Erectors
description: This group includes other structural metal preparers and erectors not elsewhere classified, for example those who heat rivets in a furnace and pass them to rivet catcher or riveter.

label: Jeweller, General
description: Makes complete jewellery articles such as rings, brooches and bracelets.

label: Jewellery Repairer
description: Repairs and remodels jewellery such as rings, brooches and bracelets.

label: Gem Cutter and Polisher
description: Cuts, shapes and polishes precious or semi-precious stones by hand and machine.

label: Gem Setter
description: Sets precious or semi-precious stones in jewellery.

label: Goldsmith and Silversmith
description: Makes and repairs gold, silver, or other precious metal articles, or articles of pewter, such as tableware and artistic objects, using hand or power tools.

label: Precious Metal Roller
description: Operates a rolling machine which rolls ingots of gold or other precious metals into strips of specified thickness.

label: Precious Metal Leaf Roller
description: Beats gold or other precious metal strip to form thin leaves.

label: Jewellery Engraver
description: Cuts letters and ornamental designs on precious metal ware and jewellery.

label: Other Jewellery and Precious Metal Workers
description: This group includes jewellery and precious metal workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who decorate jewellery by colouring or enamelling; make and repair imitation jewellery; make wax and metal models and use these to make plaster moulds for casting items of jewellery.

label: Glass Former, Potter or Related Worker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform almost any (but not all) of the occupational activities in unit group 8-91.

label: Glass Blower
description: Blows molten glass into shape by means of blowpipe.

label: Scientific Glass Blower
description: Shapes glass tubing by blowing and bending to make scientific apparatus such as retorts and flasks, measuring instruments and thermometers.

label: Glass-Blowing-Machine Operator
description: Operates machine which shapes articles such as bottles and glass parts of valves and light-bulbs from molten glass by blowing.

label: Glass Lens Moulder
description: Shapes optical glass stock into lens blanks and shapes similar objects from glass discs by heating, moulding and pressing.

label: Glass-Pressing-Machine
description: Operates a machine which forms glass objects by pressure-moulding.

label: Glass-Drawing-Machine Operator
description: Operates a glass-drawing machine by which molten glass is drawn as a continuous sheet of flat glass.

label: Plate-Glass Rollerman
description: Sets and operates machine to roll molten glass into sheets.

label: Plate-Glass Polisher
description: Operates a machine to polish and level plate-glass surfaces.

label: Float-Glass Bath Operator
description: Controls apparatus in which surface finish is given to a ribbon of glass by floating it on molten metal.

label: Glass Cutter
description: Cuts sheet glass by hand to prescribed dimensions or according to pattern, using a glass-cutting tool.

label: Optical Glass Cutter
description: Cuts shapes from block of optical glass with a diamond-toothed saw, for use as lenses, prisms, mirrors and other optical elements of precision instruments.

label: Smooths and bevels edges of glass.
Lens Grinding-Machine Operator
description: Sets up and operates a battery of machines which grind surfaces of lens blanks to desired specifications.

label: Lens Polishing-Machine Operator
description: Sets up and operates a battery of machines which polish surfaces of lens blanks to a high lustre.

label: Glass Tube Maker
description: Operates a machine to make glass rods and tubes from molten glass by drawing or drawing and blowing.

label: Glass Tube Bender
description: Heats and bends glass tubing for making neon signs and other articles.

label: Other Glass Formers, Cutters, Grinders and Finishers
description: This group includes glass formers, cutters, grinders and finishers not elsewhere classified, for example those ladling molten glass into moulds; gathering required quantities of molten glass on end of metal rod and handing it to other workers; putting legs and feet on glass articles; making laminated glass and vacuum flasks; operating automatic machines that cap (score and break) flat glass into sections of specified dimensions; operating a lathe to grind glass articles for use in laboratory apparatus or to cut, shape and seal glass bulbs used in manufacture of electronic valves or tubes.

label: Potter or Related Clay and Abrasive Former, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 8-92.

label: Potter, General
description: Makes completely pottery and porcelain ware by various methods.

label: Pottery and Porcelain Modeller
description: Makes clay or plaster-of-Paris models of pottery and porcelain ware for use in preparing moulds.

label: Pottery and Porcelain Mould Maker
description: Makes plaster-of-Paris moulds for the manufacture of pottery and porcelain ware.

label: Pottery and Porcelain Thrower
description: Forms pottery or porcelain ware by moulding clay with hands as it revolves on potter's wheel.

label: Pottery and Porcelain Jiggerman
description: Forms pottery ware by operating semi-automatic potter's wheel set up for repetitive work.

label: Pottery and Porcelain Caster (Hand)
description: Forms pottery and porcelain ware by casting semi-liquid clay (slip) in plaster-of-Paris moulds.

label: Brick and Tile Moulder (Hand)
description: Moulds bricks and tiles, particularly those with special shapes, by hand.

label: Brick and Tile Moulder (Hand or Machine)
description: Moulds bricks and tiles by hand (8-92.40) or machine.

label: Pottery and Porcelain Presser (Hand)
description: Forms pottery and porcelain ware by pressing damp, plastic clay by hand into shape of a mould.

label: Pottery and Porcelain Presser (Die- or Hand)
description: Forms pottery and porcelain ware by pressing damp plastic clay by hand into shape of a mould (8-92.45) or by operating a screw-press or hydraulic press (8-92.50).

label: Pottery and Porcelain Die-Presser
description: Operates a screw-press or hydraulic press to make pottery or porcelain ware from clay dust.

label: Clay Extruding-Press Operator
description: Operates a machine in which moist clay is extruded in strips for further processing.

label: Abrasive Wheel Moulder
description: Forms abrasive wheels by moulding and pressing an abrasive mixture by hand or machine.

label: Other Potters and Related Clay and Abrasive Formers
description: This group includes potters and related clay and abrasive formers not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate a hand press to mould clay bricks and tiles; smooth and trim pottery with hand tools; prepare clay blocks for use in presses; drill holes in clay ware; or operate machines to cut strips of clay into bricks or tiles.

label: Glass or Ceramics Kilnman, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform (almost) any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 8-93.

label: Glass-Making Furnaceman
description: Operates furnace to melt and fuse premixed ingredients to make glass.

label: Glass-Annealing Furnaceman
description: Operates annealing kiln or furnace to prevent or remove internal stresses from glass or glassware.

label: Glass Temperer
description: Tempers sheet glass to relieve stresses and harden it.

label: Pottery and Porcelain Kilnman
description: Operates kiln to bake pottery, porcelain ware and other refractory products (other than bricks and tiles) and to rebake them after glazing and decoration.

label: Brick and Tile Kilnman
description: Operates kiln to bake bricks and tiles to proper hardness.

label: Other Glass and Ceramics Kilnmen
description: This group includes glass and ceramics kilnmen not elsewhere classified, for example those who load kilns before and unload kilns after firing pottery, porcelain, sanitary ware and refractory products; assist in the preparation and firing of kilns.

label: Glass Engraver or Etcher, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 8-94.

label: Glass Engraver
description: Engraves monograms and ornamental designs on glass or crystal ware, using copper, steel or stone grinding wheels.

label: Glass Etcher
description: Etches decorative designs, calibration markings, numerals and other figures on glass articles with acid.

label: Glass Sandblaster
description: Cuts designs in surfaces of glass articles with sandblasting equipment.

label: Other Glass Engravers and Etchers
description: This group includes glass engravers and etchers not elsewhere classified, for example those who cover glass with wax prior to etching operations; operate pantograph devices to cut designs in surface of glass articles; cut glass into decorative shapes; mark out glass objects for cutters and other workers; immerse glass articles in acid bath to give clear polish to decorations; or etch patterns and borders on glazed ware.

label: Glass or Ceramics Painter or Decorator, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 8-95.

label: Glass Painter
description: Paints decorative designs on glass articles with a brush.

label: Ceramics Painter
description: Paints designs on pottery, porcelain ware and tiles with a brush.

label: Ceramics Decorator
description: Transfers designs onto pottery and porcelain ware by using stencils, transfers, rubber stamps and other means.

label: Ceramics Spray-Painter
description: Sprays paint on pottery, porcelain ware, bricks and tiles, or sprays liquid glaze on large pieces not suitable for dipping.

label: Ceramics Dipper
description: Covers biscuit ware with glaze solution by dipping.

label: Mirror Silverer
description: Coats new and old mirror glass with silvering solutions.

label: Other Glass and Ceramics Painters and Decorators
description: This group includes glass and ceramics painters and decorators not elsewhere classified, for example those who coat ware or parts of ware with oil and dust oiled surface with powder colour; draw lines on ceramic ware to guide other workers in applying coloured glaze and other decorations; polish gold-decorated ware by scouring with fine sand and finishing it with agate or bloodstone; or tend machines conveying ware through glaze sprays, dipping troughs and drying rooms.

label: Glass Mixer
description: Weighs and mixes sand, soda, potash and other materials used in glass making.

label: Clay Mixer
description: Operates machine in which clay is ground, mixed and tempered for use in ceramics manufacture.

label: Clay Slip Maker
description: Operates a machine in which clays are mixed into a semi-liquid form (slip) for making ceramic products.

label: Glaze Maker
description: Mixes, grinds, fuses and regrinds ingredients such as borax, lead, sand and lime to make glaze.

label: Abrasives Mixer
description: Mixes ingredients by machine to make grinding or polishing compounds.

label: Fibreglass Maker
description: Operates a machine to extrude molten glass through a die to form fibreglass filaments.

label: Other Glass Formers, Potters and Related Workers
description: This group includes glass formers, potters and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate filter-presses to remove excess water from clay; operate and supervise loading of battery of pans and screens used for grinding and sifting clay; or tend machines which remove air bubbles from wet clay.

label: Rubber Product Maker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupations described in unit group 9-01.

label: Rubber Millman
description: Operates a machine which kneads, mixes, blends or warms raw rubber or rubber compounds for further processing.

label: Rubber Calender Operator
description: Operates a machine which produces sheets of rubber or rubberised fabric by a rolling process.

label: Rubber Extruding-Machine Operator
description: Sets up and operates a machine in which compounded rubber is extruded through heated die to form continuous shaped strip.

label: Rubber Moulding-Press Operator
description: Operates a machine in which soft, uncured rubber is shaped in mould and vulcanised by steam heat. Tire moulder is classified in 9-02.30.

label: Rubber Goods Assembler
description: Assembles rubber goods such as water bottles, ice bags, toys, ring cushions and sports articles from fabricated parts.

label: Plastics Injection-Moulding Machine- Operator
description: Sets up and operates machine in which plastic materials are shaped by injection-moulding.

label: Plastics Compression-Moulding Machine-Operator
description: Sets up and operates machine in which plastic materials are shaped by compression-moulding.

label: Plastics Extruding-Machine-Operator
description: Sets up and operates a machine in which plastic materials are extruded through a die to form continuous rods, tubes, strips and other products.

label: Plastics Laminator
description: Operates a machine in which layers of plastics or plastic-impregnated materials are heated and pressed to form a solid laminated product.

label: Plastics Products Assembler
description: Performs marking, cutting, sealing and trimming tasks in the assembly of plastics products, such as bags and inflatable toys.

label: Plastics Products Fabricator
description: Fabricates plastics articles, such as signs, aircraft parts and window awnings.

label: Other Rubber and Plastics Products Makers (except Tire Makers and Tire Vulcanisers)
description: This group includes rubber and plastics product makers (except tire makers and tire vulcanisers) not elsewhere classified, for example those who coat fabric and other products with rubber by rubber-spreading machine or by immersing them in rubber solutions; operate presses which emboss rubber or cut it to shape; operate machines for the fabrication of foam rubber or latex articles; operate machines for cold vulcanisation processes; grind, buff, burr, polish, drill and otherwise finish plastics by hand or machine; operate and control ovens (curing pots) to vulcanise rubber goods (except tires) by means of pressurised steam; operate other specialised equipment for fabrication particular rubber or plastics products.

label: Tire maker or Vulcaniser, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 9-02.

label: Tire Builder
description: Builds up pneumatic tires on a form.

label: Tire Moulder
description: Moulds and cures (vulcanises) pneumatic rubber tires in pot heater or watchcase mould. Moulders of reconditioned tires are classified in 9-02.40.

label: Tire Rebuilder
description: Operates machines to recap or retread used tire casings.

label: Other Tire Makers and Vulcanisers
description: This group includes tire makers and vulcanisers not elsewhere classified, who perform specialised tasks in fabrication of pneumatic tires, other than tire moulding, building or rebuilding.

label: Paper Box Maker (Hand)
description: Makes and decorates paper boxes by hand.

label: Paper Box Maker (Hand or Machine)
description: Makes paper boxes by hand (9-10.20) or machine (9-10.30).

label: Paper Box Maker (Machine)
description: Sets and operates various machines which cut, fold, and glue or clip paper and cardboard to make boxes and other articles.

label: Cardboard Lining-Machine Operator
description: Sets and operates machine which glues paper to cardboard and cuts it to required length.

label: Paper Box Cutting- and Creasing-Press Operator
description: Sets and operates machine which cuts and creases cardboard and paperboard sheets to form box blanks.

label: Cardboard-Press Operator
description: Operates machine which presses paper to form drinking cups and other containers.

label: Paper Bag and Envelope Maker (Machine)
description: Sets and operates machine which cuts, glues and folds paper to make envelopes and paper bags.

label: Paper Bag and Envelope Maker (Hand or Machine)
description: Makes envelopes and paper bags by hand (9-10.90) or machine (9-10.70).

label: Cellophane Bag Maker (Machine)
description: Sets and operates machine which forms bags from cellophane, special types of paper and similar materials.

label: Other Paper and Paperboard Products Makers
description: This group includes paper and paperboard products makers not elsewhere classified, for example those who make suitcases with specially treated cardboard; operate machines making paper caps, garlands and other paper novelties and paper tubes; make envelopes by hand; glue decorative and protective paper on surfaces of completed boxes; check and put together sets of playing cards.

label: Printer, General
description: Sets type and operates a small printing machine.

label: Hand Compositor
description: Sets type by hand for printing.

label: Linotype Operator
description: Operates keyboard of machine which selects corresponding matrices of letters from magazines, assembles them in lines and automatically casts a strip of type (slug), for each line.

label: Monotype Keyboard Operator
description: Operates keyboard of machine which perforates strips of paper for use in a monotype casting machine.

label: Type-casting Machine-Operator
description: Sets up and operates machine which automatically casts lines of type for printing.

label: Printing Maker-Up
description: Arranges set-up type, spacing material and illustration blocks to form pages for printing.

label: Imposer
description: Arranges pages of set-up type in predetermined order and locks them in chase in readiness for printing.

label: Photo-Type-Setting Machine Operator
description: Operates keyboard of machine which reproduces letters on film or sensitised paper for eventual reproduction on printing plates.

label: Other Compositors and Type-Setters
description: This group includes compositors, type-setters and photo type-setters not elsewhere classified, for example those who take proofs of set-up type by means of proof presses; impress metal sheets in making braille type; and arrange photo-compose type-film on paper (positive) for reproduction on printing plates.

label: Cylinder Pressman
description: Sets and operates a printing machine in which separate sheets of paper are pressed by means of cylinder on inked type locked on flat surface.

label: Platen Pressman
description: Sets and operates platen-type printing press to produce printed material.

label: Rotary Pressman
description: Sets and operates a printing machine in which continuous roll of paper (web) is printed by means of stereotype plates locked in revolving cylinder.

label: Offset Pressman
description: Sets and operates a machine in which separate sheets of paper, tin plate or other materials are printed by roller which obtains an ink impression from engraved (lithographic) plate.

label: Direct Lithographic Pressman
description: Sets and operates machine in which sheets of paper, tin plate or other materials are printed directly from prepared lithographic stone.

label: Rotogravure Pressman
description: Sets and operates machine that prints on continuous roll of paper from photo-engraved plates or cylinders upon which the subject-matter is etched below the surface.

label: Wallpaper Printer
description: Sets and operates a machine in which patterns of various designs and colours are printed on wallpaper or other decorative papers by series of engraved rollers.

label: Other Printing Pressmen
description: This group includes other printing pressmen not elsewhere classified, for example those who assist printing machine operators to prepare, feed, tend and clean presses.

label: Stereotyper
description: Performs all or several of the tasks involved in making printing plates from set-up type by stereotyping process.

label: Electrotyper
description: Performs all or several tasks in making printing plates from set-up type by electroplating process.

label: Other Stereotypers and Electrotypers
description: This group includes stereotypers and electrotypers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in making quantities of copies of original stereotype plates in plastic.

label: Printing Engraver, Specialisation Unknown (except Photo-Engraver)
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 9-24.

label: Lithographer
description: Prepares lithographic stones by coating them and cutting away surface film according to design.

label: Metal Printing Plate, Roller and Die Engraver (Hand)
description: Engraves steel or copper plates, rollers and metal dies with hand tools for use in printing on paper, textiles, metal, plastics, porcelain or other materials.

label: Wood, Rubber or Linoleum Block Engraver (Hand)
description: Engraves wood, rubber or linoleum blocks for use in printing on wallpaper, textiles or other materials.

label: Metal Printing Roller Engraver (Machine)
description: Operates machine which engraves copper or other soft metal printing rollers by pressing with an embossed hard metal roller.

label: Engraving Pantograph Operator
description: Engraves metal printing plates or rollers with pantograph machine.

label: Lithographic Direct Transferrer
description: Transfers designs from prepared lithographic stones to metal plates for use in printing.

label: Metal Engraving Etcher
description: Etches printing plates or rollers with acid.

label: Other Printing Engravers (except Photo-Engravers)
description: This group includes printing engravers (except photoengravers) not elsewhere classified, for example those copying designs on lithographic stones prior to engraving; engraving wooden rollers; cutting metal stencils.

label: Photo-Engraver, General
description: Prepares metal printing plates by photogravure process.

label: Photogravure Cameraman
description: Photographs illustrations and textual materials to obtain negatives for use in making metal printing plates.

label: Photogravure Retoucher
description: Retouches photographic negatives to make them more suitable for use in preparing metal printing plates.

label: Photo-Mechanical Transferrer
description: Reproduces matter from photographic negatives on metal plates for use in printing.

label: Photogravure Etcher
description: Etches photo-printed metal plates with acid for use in printing.

label: Printing Plate Retoucher
description: Corrects imperfections in etched printing plates to make them ready for use.

label: Other Photo-Engravers
description: This group includes photo-engravers not elsewhere classified, for example those who grain metal plates prior to coating them with photo-sensitive material; mount printing plates on wooden blocks; prepare monochromatic or polychromatic photo-engraving plates or films by electronic process.

label: Bookbinder (Hand)
description: Binds printed material together by hand to make complete books, collections of documents and series of periodicals, fixes them in covers and performs book finishing operations.

label: Bookbinder (Hand or Machine)
description: Binds printed material together by hand (9-26.20) or machine (9-26.30).

label: Bookbinder (Machine)
description: Performs series of tasks in binding books with machines.

label: Book Embosser (Hand)
description: Embosses designs or titles on book covers with hand tools.

label: Book Embosser (Hand or Machine)
description: Embosses designs or titles on book covers with hand tools (9-26.40) or an electrical pressing machine (9-26.50).

label: Book Embosser (Machine)
description: Sets up and operates electrical pressing machine to emboss designs or titles on book covers.

label: Other Bookbinders and Related Workers
description: This group includes bookbinders and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who decorate book edges with plain or mixed colours, or with gold leaf, by hand.

label: Colour Developer
description: Treats exposed colour film with series of timed chemical and water baths and diffused light in dark-room to prepare coloured negatives and transparent positives.

label: Black-and-White Developer
description: Treats exposed black-and-white film and photographic plates with series of timed chemical and water baths in dark-room to prepare black-and-white negatives and positives.

label: Photograph Printer
description: Prints and develops black-and-white and colour photographs with contact-printing machine in dark room.

label: Photograph Enlarger
description: Enlarges or reduces photographs with projection printer in dark room.

label: Other Photographic Dark-Room Workers
description: This group includes photographic darkroom workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate automatic printing and developing machines which produce photographic prints in large quantities; operate machines for developing and drying motion picture films; inspect reels of developed colour film for defects; operate photographic print-washing machines; and operate X-ray film developing machines.

label: Silk-Screen Stencil Cutter
description: Cuts stencils, according to design, for use in silkscreen printing.

label: Silk-Screen Printer
description: Prints on paper, metal, textile and other materials by silk-screen process.

label: Block Printer
description: Prints designs on cloth and wallpaper with engraved blocks of wood, rubber or other material.

label: Textile Printer
description: Sets and operates machine which prints patterns of various designs and colours on textile material by means of engraved printing rollers.

label: Other Printers and Related Workers
description: This group includes printing workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who specialise in making silk-screen printing stencils by photographic process; operating paper-embossing press or relief-printing press.

label: Building Painter
description: Applies coats of paint, varnish, shellac and similar materials to exterior and interior surfaces, trimmings and fixtures of buildings to protect and decorate them.

label: Structural Steel and Ship Painter
description: Applies coatings of paint, red lead, bituminous emulsion and similar protective materials on bridges, ships, hulls and metal superstructure, steel framework of buildings, storage tanks and other metal structures.

label: Other Painters, Construction
description: This group includes construction painters not elsewhere classified, for example those who paint imitation building exteriors or interiors and similar pieces of stage and film sets; specialise in a particular type of finish such as graining or marbling; prepare surfaces for painting; paint ships= woodwork and interior fittings; paint railway coaches and wagons.

label: Brush-Painter (except Construction)
description: Applies decorative and protective coatings of paint, enamel and lacquer on wooden, metal and other manufactured articles (except glass and ceramics) with brush and hand rollers.

label: Spray-Painter (except Construction)
description: Applies decorative and protective coatings of paint, enamel and lacquer on metal, wooden and other manufactured articles with a hand-spraying device.

label: Hand Dipper
description: Immerses articles (except ceramics) in paint, enamel, stain, varnish, lacquer and similar liquids to impart a protective or decorative coating.

label: Sign Painter
description: Plans, lays out and paints letters and designs to make signs.

label: Automobile Painter
description: Paints automotive vehicles such as automobiles, buses and trucks.

label: Other Painters
description: This group includes painters not elsewhere classified, for example those who touch up blemishes in new paintwork to perfect the finish of manufactured articles; operate automatic spray-painting devices to coat (dip or spray) new motor vehicle bodies or other articles on a conveyor; operate a paint-stripping machine to paint stripes on street and highway surfaces; operate other types of painting machines or paint-drying and paint-baking devices.

label: Musical Instrument Maker or Tuner, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 9-41.

label: Stringed Instrument Maker
description: Makes and repairs stringed instruments of wood, ebonite, metal and other materials, using hand and power tools.

label: Woodwind Instrument Maker
description: Makes and repairs wind instruments, mainly of wood, using hand and power tools.

label: Metal Wind Instrument Maker
description: Makes and repairs metal wind instruments, using hand and power tools.

label: Accordion Maker
description: Makes and repairs accordions of wood, paper, plastics, artificial leather, metal and other materials, using hand and power tools.

label: Organ Builder
description: Makes the instrumental parts of organs of wood, metal, leather and other materials, using hand and power tools, and builds and repairs organs.

label: Piano Maker
description: Makes, assembles and repairs instrumental parts of pianos of wood, felt, wire and other materials, using hand and power tools.

label: Musical Instrument Tuner
description: Tests and adjusts musical instruments, such as pianos and organs, to produce correct tones and keep instrument in good condition.

label: Other Musical Instrument Makers and Tuners
description: This group includes musical instrument makers and tuners not elsewhere classified, for example those making drums and xylophones.

label: Basket Maker
description: Makes baskets and other basketry articles by interlacing osier, willow, rattan and similar materials by hand.

label: Brush Maker (Hand)
description: Selects and prepares brush materials, such as bristles, fibre, nylon and wire and sets them in brush base.

label: Broom Maker (Hand)
description: Selects and prepares materials, such as broom corn, bass, whisker and fibre and fastens them to broom handles by hand.

label: Wicker Furniture Maker
description: Makes wicker furniture from peeled and softened rattan, reeds, rushes, willow sticks and similar materials by hand.

label: Other Basketry Weavers and Brush Makers
description: This group includes basketry weavers and brush makers not elsewhere classified, for example those who plait braids of grass, reed and similar material for making mats and other articles; staple rims of basket cover mats by machine; split canes or willow rods by hand or machine; operate machines which automatically drill holes and insert bristles in brushes; operate mixing machine to clean and mix bristles used in brush manufacture; stitch brooms by machine to shape and strengthen them; make flue, bottle and similar brushes by placing bristles or similar material between wires and twisting the wires by hand or machine to clamp the bristles.

label: Cast Concrete Product Maker
description: Performs one or more tasks in the manufacture of precast concrete products, such as kerbstones, flagstones, fencing posts, moulded pipe sections and trench liners, lintels, blocks, concrete bricks and tiles, composite building units, walling and partition slabs, segmented tunnel linings and foundation piling.

label: Asbestos Cement Products Machine-Operator
description: Performs one or more tasks in the manufacture of asbestos cement products such as building sheets, slates, pipes, cable conduits, ventilators, fume and dust extraction conduits.

label: Cast-Stone Maker
description: Performs one or more tasks in the manufacture of cast stone for building purposes.

label: Other Non-Metallic Mineral Product Makers
description: This group includes non-metallic mineral product makers not elsewhere classified, for example those making abrasive-coated cloth and paper.

label: Other Production or Related Worker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities in unit group 9-49.

label: Taxidermist
description: Prepares, stuffs and mounts skins of animals and birds in life-like form.

label: Linoleum Maker
description: Performs one or more tasks in the making of linoleum.

label: Doll Toy and Stuffed Maker
description: Performs one or more hand or machine tasks in the making and repairing of dolls or stuffed toys.

label: Rubber Stamp Maker
description: Makes rubber stamps to order and mounts them for use.

label: Candle Maker
description: Performs one or more tasks in the manufacture of candles by dipping or moulding.

label: Photographic Film and Paper Maker
description: Performs one or more tasks in the making of photographic film and paper.

label: Quality Inspector
description: Inspects finished products or parts for conformance to manufacturer's standards, finish and appearance.

label: Other Production and Related Workers Not Elsewhere Classified
description: This group includes other production and related workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who make footwear from raffia, straw or similar material; operate machines in the making of matches; operate machines in the making of wood-encased pencil

label: Construction Worker, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in minor group 9-5.

label: Bricklayer (Construction)
description: Lays bricks, hollow tiles and similar building blocks (except stone) to construct walls, partitions, arches, interior fireplaces and chimneys, and other structures.

label: Bricklayer (Chimney Building)
description: Lays bricks or tiles to construct tapering chimneys of great height.

label: Firebrick Layer
description: Lays firebricks and refractory blocks and tiles to build or repair fireboxes, casings, linings and insulation of high-temperature equipment such as furnaces, steam boilers, converters and ovens.

label: Bricklayer or Stonemason
description: Lays bricks, hollow tiles and similar building blocks to construct walls, partitions, arches, interior fireplaces and chimneys (9-51.20) or builds stone structures (9-51.40).

label: Stonemason (Construction)
description: Builds stone structures such as walls, piers and abutments, lays walks and constructs other types of stonemasonry. Stone cutter and finisher is classified in 8-20.20.

label: Marble Setter
description: Prepares and sets marble blocks and slabs to construct and cover floors, walls and other surfaces.

label: Tile Setter
description: Sets tiles to surface walls and floors.

label: Mosaic Cutter and Setter
description: Constructs and lays mosaic panels to decorate floors, walls and other surfaces.

label: Paviour
description: Lays wood blocks, paving stones, slabs, bricks and kerbstones on sand or other type of bed to make roads, pavements and open drains.

label: Other Bricklayers, Stonemasons and Tile Setters
description: This group includes bricklayers, stonemasons and tile setters not elsewhere classified, for example those who lay bricks, concrete blocks or shaped tiles to construct sewers or manholes or chambers for enclosing waterline valves; lay tile conduits to insulate and protect water and steam lines; rebuild and repair surface or constructional stonework for monuments; lay stone in embankments or water drains to prevent soil erosion; line ingot mould covers with firebrick mortar.

label: Reinforced Concreter, General
description: Builds reinforced concrete structures and structural parts such as pillars, beams, floors and walls.

label: Concrete Shutterer
description: Builds, assembles, places in position and dismantles rough wooden structures (shuttering) into which concrete is poured and allowed to set.

label: Reinforcing Iron Worker
description: Cuts and bends metal rods and fixes them in concrete forms (shuttering) to reinforce concrete.

label: Cement Finisher
description: Finishes surfaces of concrete structures and smoothes surfaces of freshly poured concrete sections.

label: Terrazzo Worker
description: Applies to floors a durable, smooth surfacing composed of cement, sand, pigment and marble particles.

label: Other Reinforced Concreters, Cement Finishers and Terazzo Workers
description: This group includes reinforced concreters, cement finishers and terazzo workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who repair floors, walls, tanks, vats and other concrete structural parts and equipment; cut, shape and fasten wire mesh for reinforcing concrete embankments and road surfaces; set expansion joints in concrete paving; cure new concrete by covering with mat and sprinkling water to prevent too rapid drying; operate machine to mix and spray concrete by compressed air to apply a protective coating through nozzle to steel, masonry or other surfaces.

label: Roofer, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 9-53.

label: Slate and Tile Roofer
description: Applies and fastens slates and tiles to roof frameworks.

label: Composition Roofer
description: Covers roof frameworks with various kinds of synthetic material such as asbestos composition, fibro-cement, and corrugated plastic sheet.

label: Asphalt Roofer
description: Covers top side (roof) of buildings with several layers of roofing paper and hot tar and final surface layer of gravel.

label: Metal Roofer
description: Covers roof with sheets of metal, such as galvanised iron, lead, copper and zinc.

label: Roof Thatcher
description: Constructs a thick roof covering with material such as straw, reeds, rushes and heather.

label: Other Roofers
description: This group includes roofers not elsewhere classified, for example those who cover roofs and walls with wood shingles and those spraying asphalt, tar and gravel roofs with vinyl plastic solution to improve insulation.

label: Carpenter, General
description: Cuts out, assembles, erects and repairs structural and other woodwork at work bench and on construction site.

label: Construction Carpenter
description: Cuts out, assembles and installs wooden frameworks of buildings, flooring, and other heavy-framed woodwork, such as pouring chutes and scaffolding, at building sites.

label: Construction Joiner
description: Fits, assembles and installs wooden internal and external fixtures of buildings such as door and window frames, facings and panelling.

label: Stage and Studio Carpenter
description: Makes, erects, alters and repairs stage sets and scenery fixtures for theatrical performances and motion picture productions.

label: Wood Shipwright
description: Erects temporary structures to support ship under construction or repair, checks fairing, makes and fits wooden parts of ship, prepares launching way and handles launching.

label: Ship Joiner
description: Constructs, assembles and installs wooden fittings such as deck-houses, bridge shelters, skylights, guard-rails, cabinets and berths in ships under construction or repair.

label: Wooden Boatbuilder
description: Constructs and repairs small wooden craft such as sail boats, motor boats, floats and pontoons.

label: Ship's Carpenter
description: Repairs and builds woodwork on board ship as member of crew.

label: Aircraft Joiner
description: Constructs, assembles and repairs wooden parts of aircraft.

label: Bench Carpenter
description: Cuts out, shapes, fits and assembles wooden parts, mainly working at bench, to make and repair woodwork and wooden fixtures, such as doors, windows, staircases, panelling and simple furniture.

label: Parquetry Worker
description: Installs and repairs parquet flooring.

label: Other Carpenters, Joiners and Parquetry Workers
description: This group includes other carpenters and joiners not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform rough carpentry work in tunnels and mines or construct wooden bridges and wharves.

label: Plasterer, General
description: Applies one or more coats of plaster to interior walls and ceilings of buildings to produce a finished surface.

label: Ornamental Plasterer
description: Moulds and installs ornamental plaster panels and trims and casts ornamental plaster cornices.

label: Stucco Plasterer
description: Applies protective and decorative covering of cement, plaster or other material to exterior building surfaces.

label: Fibrous Plasterer
description: Makes and installs decorative plaster fixtures of fibrous plaster.

label: Other Plasterers
description: This group includes plasterers not elsewhere classified, for example those who maintain plaster work in good repair; apply special plaster for acoustical purposes; fasten metal or wooden laths to walls, ceilings and partitions to provide supporting base for plaster.

label: Building Insulator (Hand)
description: Applies slabs and sheets (bats) of insulating material, such as cork and spun glass, to walls, floors and ceilings of buildings.

label: Building Insulator (Machine)
description: Blows and packs insulating material such as mineral wool, shredded cork or asbestos into cavities between walls, floors and ceilings of buildings with a power-driven machine.

label: Acoustical Insulator
description: Applies adhesive, sound-absorbing material to ceilings and other surfaces with power-driven machine to prevent sound reverberation.

label: Boiler and Pipe Insulator
description: Applies insulating material such as asbestos, cork, felt or mineral wool to exposed surfaces of equipment such as boilers, pipes and tanks.

label: Refrigeration and Air-conditioning Equipment Insulator
description: Insulates refrigeration and air-conditioning equipment with materials such as cork and asbestos.

label: Other Insulators
description: This group includes insulators not elsewhere classified, for example those cutting asbestos cloth, making it into blankets and fixing them to turbines to prevent loss of heat.

label: Building Glazier
description: Cuts and fixes glass panes in windows, doors and partitions of buildings.

label: Patent Roofing Glazier
description: Fastens glass panes into puttyless roof lights.

label: Plate-Glass Glazier
description: Installs flat and curved plate glass in shop fronts, dividing walls, swing doors, show-cases, portholes and other openings.

label: Leaded Glass Glazier
description: Cuts, assembles and installs glass in lead or copper framework to form decorative windows and glass panels.

label: Vehicle Glazier
description: Installs ordinary and shatter-proof glass panels in windows, doors and windscreens of vehicles such as trucks, buses, automobiles, railway coaches, tramcars and aircraft.

label: Other Glaziers
description: This group includes glaziers not elsewhere classified, for example those who install glass panels to form decorative facings on buildings.

label: Housebuilder, General
description: Constructs, alters and repairs small structures such as houses, barns, shops and private garages, performing tasks in several different building trades.

label: Building Maintenance Man
description: Keeps structures such as office buildings, apartment houses, hotels and factory buildings in good repair.

label: Paperhanger
description: Covers interior walls and ceilings of buildings with wallpaper.

label: Carpet planner
description: Measures rooms to ascertain coverage of carpet required and cuts and fits material accordingly.

label: Steeplejack
description: Performs maintenance, repair and construction work at unusual heights, such as painting smokestacks, flagstaffs or water tanks and repairing roofs, stonework or other parts of steeples and towers.

label: Scaffolder
description: Erects temporary metal or wooden scaffolding on building sites for construction, renovation, exterior painting and similar purposes.

label: Demolition Worker
description: Demolishes buildings with picks, crowbars, pneumatic hammers and other tools and salvages usable materials such as bricks, structural steel and timber.

label: Pipe Layer
description: Lays pipes of glazed and unglazed clay, concrete, cast iron and other materials in ditches to form sewers, drains, water mains and conduits for cables and other purposes.

label: Well Digger
description: Excavates water wells and deep pits for structural footings.

label: Underwater Worker
description: Works under water, dressed in diving suit, to inspect, repair, remove and install equipment and structures.

label: Composition Tile Layer
description: Fixes composition tiles in building interiors for shock absorbing, sound-deadening, floor-surfacing and decorative purposes.

label: Building Exterior Cleaner
description: Cleans exterior surfaces of stone, brick and metal structures by means of a jet of steam or sand from a hose nozzle.

label: Other Construction Workers
description: This group includes construction workers not elsewhere classified, for example those who shore up buildings in course of alteration, and adjoining buildings if necessary, with metal tubing, metal or wood beams and chocks; apply a durable asphalt, clay, sand, bituminous or asbestos-fibre surface to floors; pull sections of heavy cables through underground channels using winches and other equipment; specialise in placing and fixing in position assembled prefabricated building sections such as wall, ceiling and floor units.

label: Power-Generating Machinery Operator, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 9-61.

label: Steam Power Plant Operator
description: Controls and operates boilers, turbines, generators and auxiliary equipment at electricity generating plant.

label: Hydroelectric Station Operator
description: Controls electrical generating units and related mechanical and hydraulic equipment at hydroelectric generating station.

label: Power-Reactor Operator
description: Controls nuclear reactor to produce steam power to drive electricity-generating equipment or other machinery.

label: Turbine Operator (Power Station)
description: Operates a steam or water-powered turbine which drives generators for producing electricity.

label: Power-Switchboard Operator
description: Regulates the amount of electricity generated in a power station according to demand.

label: Load Dispatcher (Electric Power)
description: Controls the supply and distribution of electricity from power stations to ensure that consumers' demands are met.

label: Other Power-Generating Machinery Operators
description: This group includes other power-generating machinery operators not elsewhere classified, for example those who assist power-generating plant operators in power stations; control feeder switchboards in power substations; operate power-generating plant servicing an individual or other establishment.

label: Stationary Engine Operator, General
description: Operates and services various types of stationary engines and related mechanical equipment such as prime movers to drive machinery (other than generators), compressor units, pumps, refrigeration and ventilation equipment and similar installations.

label: Air Compressor Operator
description: Operates and services a compressor which generates and supplies compressed air to pneumatic tools, hoists or other equipment.

label: Gas Compressor Operator
description: Operates steam or internal combustion engines to transmit, compress or recover gases, such as butane, nitrogen, hydrogen and natural gas, in various production processes.

label: Boiler Fireman
description: Tends one or more boilers which produce steam for heat or power.

label: Pumping-Station Operator
description: Operates pumping and siphoning equipment to transfer liquids, gases, semi-liquids and powdered substances from one location to another.

label: Water Treatment Plant Operator (Waterworks)
description: Controls treatment plant equipment to purify and clarify water for human consumption and industrial use.

label: Incinerator Plant Operator
description: Controls equipment to burn garbage and other refuse in incinerator plant.

label: Refrigeration System Operator
description: Operates a refrigeration system for preserving foods, providing cooling media for industrial processes, cooling buildings or for other purposes.

label: Heating and Ventilation Equipment Operator
description: Controls and services electric motors, fans and other equipment in heating and ventilation systems.

label: Other Stationary Engine and Related Equipment Operators
description: This group includes stationary engine and related equipment operators not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate watersheds by controlling gates and valves in aqueducts and dams to regulate flow of water; operate sewage plant equipment to purify waste water; operate and maintain desilting basin to remove silt from water entering irrigation system; operate a cremation furnace to dispose of human bodies.

label: Docker
description: Loads and unloads ships' cargoes.

label: Loader of ship, truck, wagon or airplane
description: Loads and unloads ships' cargoes (9-71.20), railway wagons truck and other vehicles (9-71.30), or airplane (9-71.35).

label: Railway and Road Vehicle Loader
description: Loads and unloads goods, material or equipment carried in railway wagons truck and other vehicles.

label: Aircraft Loader
description: Loads and unloads aircraft cargoes.

label: Boat Loader (Liquids and Gases)
description: Connects hoses between pipes of main shore installation and tanks of barges, tankers and other ships to load and unload petroleum, liquefied gases and other liquids.

label: Warehouse Porter
description: Carries and stacks goods in warehouse, market or similar establishment. Stock clerks are classified in unit group 3-91.

label: Hand Packer
description: Packs materials or products by hand in cartons, wooden boxes, crates, kegs and other containers for shipment or storage.

label: Packer, Hand or Machine
description: Packs materials or products by hand (9-71.50) or machine (9-71.55).

label: Machine Packer
description: Operates a machine to carry out one or more tasks in wrapping objects or packing articles and liquids in containers for shipment or storage.

label: Machine Labeller
description: Operates a machine which glues labels and revenue stamps on articles and containers.

label: Bale-Press Operator
description: Operates machine to compress and bind loose materials into bales to facilitate handling.

label: Other Dockers and Freight Handlers
description: This group includes dockers and freight handers not elsewhere classified, for example those who carry hand baggage at railway stations, airports and piers; pack and load furniture and other household effects into vans and carry these items from vans into living quarters.

label: Hoisting Equipment Rigger, General
description: Sets up various types of lifting tackle and directs its use in moving machinery and other heavy objects about factories, shipyards or other locations.

label: Rope and Cable Splicer, General
description: Joins, repairs and fits attachments to wire and hemp ropes and cables by splicing.

label: Hoisting Equipment Rigger (Construction)
description: Sets up lifting cages, mobile platforms and other hoists for raising and lowering materials and workers employed on construction work.

label: Ship Rigger
description: Installs and repairs ropes, wires and cables on ships.

label: Aircraft Rigger
description: Installs cable connections between cabin controls of aircraft and ailerons, rudder, fins and other parts.

label: Oil and Gas Well-Drilling Rigger
description: Works as member of crew in erecting and repairing derricks used for drilling oil and gas wells and installing cables, hoisting and drilling equipment.

label: Suspension Bridge Cable Worker
description: Works as member of cable crew to build up, fit and install wire cables in the construction of suspension bridges.

label: Other Riggers and Cable Splicers
description: This group includes riggers and cable splicers not elsewhere classified, for example those erecting and installing cable systems for overhead cable railways and other aerial ropeways; those performing rigging tasks in connection with logging operations.

label: Crane Driver (Bridge- or Gantry Crane, Jib-Crane, Tower-Crane or Mobile Crane).
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in 9-7320 to 9-7330

label: Bridge- or Gantry-Crane Operator
description: Operates power-driven crane in which lifting gear can be moved along an overhead bridge which moves on rails.

label: Stationary Jib-Crane Operator
description: Operates a stationary crane equipped with a mobile jib (boom).

label: Tower-Crane Operator
description: Operates a crane consisting of a turning metal tower which moves on rails, equipped at the top with a mobile jib (boom) or a fixed jib along which a car supporting the hoisting equipment moves.

label: Mobile-Crane Operator
description: Operates a crane mounted on wheels or crawler tracks which can be moved under its own power in any direction. Operators of excavating, pile-driving and similar machines are classified in unit group 9-74.

label: Hoist Operator (Construction)
description: Operates power-driven hoisting equipment, usually consisting of mobile cage or platform, to raise and lower materials and workers employed on construction work.

label: Hoist Operator (Mine)
description: Operates power-driven equipment to raise and lower mine cages carrying workers and full or empty cars (skips).

label: Mine Cageman
description: Gives signals for movement of cage used to raise and lower men, cars and supplies between various levels and surface of mine and loads and unloads cage.

label: Winch Operator
description: Operates a hauling or lifting device consisting essentially of a cable and winding drum rotated by hand or power unit.

label: Opening-Bridge Operator
description: Operates controls to open bridge for the passage of water traffic and close bridge for use by road vehicles.

label: Other Crane and Hoist Operators
description: This group includes crane and hoist operators not elsewhere classified, for example those operating cranes mounted on railcars or floating platforms.

label: Excavator, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in 9-74.20 to 9-74.90.

label: Exacavator (Hand Tools)
description: Excavates, grades, levels and compacts earth and similar materials for road, canal, rail and tram construction.

label: Excavating-Machine Operator
description: Operates a power-driven machine, mounted on wheels or crawler tracks, equipped with movable shovel, grab bucket or dragline bucket to excavate and move earth, rock, sand, gravel and similar material.

label: Trench-Digging-Machine Operator
description: Operates power-driven machine equipped with an endless bucket-chain to dig trenches for sewer, drainage, water, oil, gas and similar pipelines.

label: Bulldozer Operator
description: Operates mobile power-driven machine equipped with concave steel blade to move, distribute and level earth.

label: Dredge Operator
description: Operates various kinds of excavating equipment, mounted on a dredge, to remove sand, gravel and mud from bottom of body of water.

label: Pile-Driver Operator
description: Operates a power-driven machine equipped with power hammer or drop-hammer to drive wooden, concrete or steel piles into dry ground or bottom of body of water.

label: Road-Grader and Scraper Operator
description: Operates a tractor-drawn or elf-propelled scraper or scoop to level ground for construction of buildings, roadways, airport runways and other purposes.

label: Road-Roller Operator
description: Operates power-driven roller to compact and smooth layers of material such as rock, gravel, earth, concrete and asphalt to construct roads, pavements and runways and for other purposes.

label: Concrete Paving-Machine Operator
description: Operates a mobile paving machine to spread and smooth freshly poured concrete surfaces for concrete roadways under construction.

label: Tar-Spreading Machine Operator
description: Operates a tractor-drawn or self-propelled machine to spread bituminous or tar preparations on road surfaces.

label: Concrete-Mixer Operator
description: Operates a transportable machine which mixes sand, gravel, cement and water to make concrete on construction site.

label: Concrete-Mixing-Plant Operator
description: Operates central concrete mixing plant to prepare batches of concrete according to orders.

label: Other Earth-Moving and Related Machinery Operators
description: This group includes earth-moving and other related machinery operators not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate machines to bore holes for posts or poles.

label: Material Handling Equipment Operators Not Elsewhere Classified, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 9-79.

label: Lifting-Truck Operator
description: Operates power-driven truck equipped with fork lift or lifting platform to pick up, transport and raise or mechanically stack bales, crates, cartons and similar objects in warehouse, storeroom, factory or other establishment.

label: Dumper Driver
description: Operates motorised tip-wagon (dump truck, not intended for transport by road) to transfer bulk materials such as earth, gravel, stone and minerals from one location to another on a construction site, mining area or dumping site.

label: Shuttle-Car Operator (Mine)
description: Operates self-propelled truck (shuttle-car) to transport minerals from working face in mine to conveyor or rail car (skip) loading chute.

label: Timber-Carrier Driver
description: Drives a straddle truck to carry, beneath its elevated frame, logs, sawn timber or similar loads for short distances, usually within a timber yard, sawmill or other industrial establishment.

label: Other Material Handling Equipment Operators
