description: This group includes material handling operators not elsewhere classified, for example those who operate elevating, endless-belt, bucket, and chain conveyors, aerial ropeways and similar equipment.

label: Ships' Deck Rating, Barge Crew or Boatman, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 9-81.

label: Boatswain
description: Supervises deck ratings engaged on cleaning and maintenance work aboard ship (except engine room).

label: Able Seaman
description: Serves as skilled deck-rating on seagoing vessels, performing various operation and maintenance duties, under the direction of the boatswain or ship's deck officer of the watch.

label: Seaman, Able or Ordinary
description: Serves as ordinary deck hand (9-81.40) or skilled deck-rating (9-81.30) on seagoing vessels.

label: Ordinary Seaman
description: Serves as ordinary deck hand on seagoing vessel.

label: Other Ships' Deck Ratings, Barge Crews and Boatmen
description: This group includes other ships= deck ratings, barge crews and boatmen not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform tasks of deck-hands on harbour vessels, canal barges, river boats, ferries and yachts; serve as crewmen on tugboats, cable ships, lightships and dredges; serve as members of land-based lifeboat crew; drive launches and motorboats.

label: Ship's Fireman
description: Tends one or more boilers producing steam for ship's main and auxiliary engines.

label: Ship's Oiler and Greaser
description: Lubricates bearings and moving parts of engines and other mechanical equipment on vessel afloat.

label: Other Ships' Engine-Room Ratings
description: This group includes other ships= engine-room ratings not elsewhere classified, for example those who perform cleaning tasks in engine and boiler rooms.

label: Railway Engine-Driver or Firemen, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 9-83.

label: Railway Engine Driver
description: Drives steam, electric or diesel-electric engine to haul passenger or freight trains.

label: Railway Steam-Engine Fireman
description: Fires and attends to boiler of steam locomotive.

label: Assistant Railway Engine Driver
description: Assists driver of electric or diesel railway engine.

label: Underground or Elevated Train Driver
description: Drives an underground or elevated train to transport passengers.

label: Engine-Driver (Mine and Quarry)
description: Drives an electric, diesel or compressed-air driven locomotive to haul cars underground or on surface of mine or in quarry.

label: Other Railway Engine-Drivers and Firemen
description: This group includes other railway engine-drivers and firemen not elsewhere classified, for example those who drive shunting engines.

label: Railway Brakeman (Freight Train)
description: Takes charge of and safeguards freight train during trip.

label: Railway Signaller
description: Controls flow of railway traffic over section of line within his jurisdiction by operating signals and switches from control tower or signal box.

label: Railway Shunter
description: Switches rolling-stock in railway yards and sidings in accordance with orders about loading, unloading and make-up of trains, and couples and uncouples rolling stock.

label: Mine and Quarry Brakeman
description: Makes up trains of cars for hauling by locomotive or cable and directs their movement along haulage ways in mine or quarry.

label: Motor Vehicle Driver, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 9-85.

label: Tram Driver
description: Drives street railway car transporting passengers.

label: Taxi Driver
description: Drives motor car or three-wheeled motorised vehicle to transport passengers on demand at a charge usually based on a fixed tariff.

label: Motor Bus Driver
description: Drives single- or double-deckered motor bus over fixed or predetermined route to transport local or long-distance passengers.

label: Lorry and Van Driver (Local Transport)
description: Drives a motor truck to transport materials, merchandise, equipment, etc. to and from specified destinations over short distances (excluding roundsmen).

label: Lorry and Van Driver (Local or Long-Distance Transport)
description: Drives a motor truck to transport goods or liquids over short (9-85.50) or long (9-85.60) distances.

label: Lorry and Van Driver (Long-Distance Transport)
description: Drives heavy motor truck, with or without trailer, to transport goods or liquids over long distances.

label: Motor-Cyclist
description: Drives motor-cycle or motorised tricycle equipped to transport goods.

label: Other Motor-Vehicle Drivers
description: This group includes motor vehicle-drivers not elsewhere classified, for example private chauffeurs, hire-car drivers, drivers of cars attached to a governmental or other organisation=s car pool, drivers delivering new motor vehicles from factory to ports, sales depots or other places, drivers of ambulances and motor-car driving instructors.

label: Animal or Animal-Drawn Vehicle Driver, Specialisation Unknown
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities described in unit group 9-86.

label: Animal-Drawn Vehicle Driver (Road)
description: Drives one or more animals pulling road vehicles to transport passengers or freight.

label: Animal-Drawn Vehicle Driver (Mine and Quarry)
description: Drives animals to haul wagons underground or on surface of a mine or in a quarry.

label: Other Animal and Animal-Drawn Vehicle Drivers
description: This group includes animal and animal-drawn vehicle drivers not elsewhere classified, for example those who drive working elephants, or drive one animal, or pack-animal train, to transport passengers or freight.

label: Dockmaster, Dry-Dock
description: Supervises and co-ordinates activities of workers engaged in dry-docking vessels for cleaning, painting and repair.

label: Lock Operator (Canal or Port)
description: Opens and closes lock gates to permit the passage of water-borne craft. Opening-bridge operator is classified in 9-73.55.

label: Lighthouse-Man
description: Operates warning light and signal apparatus of lighthouse or lightship.

label: Pedal-Vehicle Driver
description: Propels cycle equipped to transport passengers or goods.

label: Other Transport Equipment Operators
description: This group includes transport equipment operators not elsewhere classified, for example those who attend to gates, sluices and pumping machinery connected with the dry-docking of vessels, pull rickshaws to transport passengers, or handcarts to transport goods by road, open and close gates to railway level-crossings.

label: Worker, No Further Information
description: May perform any (but not all) of the occupational activities listed in unit group 9-99, but is described only by the single term >worker=.

label: Labourer
description: Performs lifting, carrying, stacking, shovelling, digging, cleaning and similar tasks by hand, using simple labouring tools such as pick, shovel, wheelbarrow and street broom where necessary.

label: Day-Labourer
description: Performs the same range of tasks, using the same types of tools as a labourer (9-99.10), but is specifically hired and paid by the day.

label: Factory Worker
description: Performs unspecified tasks in a factory. This code is used where no product is mentioned, or where there is uncertainty as to whether the individual so described was actually involved in making the factory=s products rather than performing cleaning or maintenance work within the factory environment.
